WEBVTT

cue-1
00:00:01.340 --> 00:00:02.800
A Miracle of Modern Missions:

cue-2
00:00:03.480 --> 00:00:05.920
The Story of Matula, a Congo Convert

cue-3
00:00:07.060 --> 00:00:09.660
God our Father, full of kindness,

cue-4
00:00:10.540 --> 00:00:11.720
look upon our country,

cue-5
00:00:12.540 --> 00:00:17.120
every land which sin has cursed and where
deep darkness still remains.

cue-6
00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:19.060
God our Father,

cue-7
00:00:19.820 --> 00:00:20.720
full of kindness,

cue-8
00:00:21.580 --> 00:00:22.880
look upon our country.

cue-9
00:00:24.460 --> 00:00:25.919
By John Bell,

cue-10
00:00:25.920 --> 00:00:26.900
Baptist Missionary.

cue-11
00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:32.520
Originally published in 1900, revised for
easier readability in 2025,

cue-12
00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:33.530
but not abridged.

cue-13
00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:36.760
Audiobook produced by scrollreader.com.

cue-14
00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:42.340
Introductory note by J.B. Wathen,
Secretary of the Baptist Missionary

cue-15
00:00:42.340 --> 00:00:42.840
Society.

cue-16
00:00:44.520 --> 00:00:49.480
Not long before he died, Alfred Saker, one
of Africa's earliest missionaries, wrote

cue-17
00:00:49.480 --> 00:00:54.460
that nothing brings a missionary more joy
or strength than seeing God's grace

cue-18
00:00:54.460 --> 00:00:56.800
at work in the lives of the people he
serves.

cue-19
00:00:57.420 --> 00:00:59.340
He called these miracles of missions,

cue-20
00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:04.960
old ways passing away and everything
becoming new, and found in them proof that

cue-21
00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:06.580
God's promise never fails.

cue-22
00:01:07.300 --> 00:01:11.900
My word will not return to me empty, but
will accomplish what I desire and achieve

cue-23
00:01:11.900 --> 00:01:14.120
the purpose for which I sent it.

cue-24
00:01:15.050 --> 00:01:19.759
The story of Matula, told here by Mr. Bell
from Wathen Station on the Lower Congo

cue-25
00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:24.720
River, is another remarkable example of
the gospel's power to transform even

cue-26
00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:27.360
the most broken and uneducated lives.

cue-27
00:01:28.460 --> 00:01:32.240
Few accounts in modern missions are as
moving and inspiring as the work among the

cue-28
00:01:32.240 --> 00:01:36.140
Congo's formerly cannibal tribes over the
past 24 years.

cue-29
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.940
Their dramatic turn to faith makes a
strong case for sending the lamp of life

cue-30
00:01:40.940 --> 00:01:43.400
into every dark corner of Central Africa.

cue-31
00:01:44.260 --> 00:01:48.259
Matula stayed true to his savior even
under the harshest persecution.

cue-32
00:01:48.940 --> 00:01:53.560
He trusted God completely when he faced
certain death at the hands of powerful

cue-33
00:01:53.560 --> 00:01:58.440
enemies, never doubting that his father in
heaven was in control. He showed no fear,

cue-34
00:01:58.440 --> 00:02:03.220
despite the spite and treachery of those
who hunted him. We can thank

cue-35
00:02:03.220 --> 00:02:06.680
God that his grace shone so clearly in
Matula's life.

cue-36
00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:10.759
Today, his bold witness has changed his
hometown of Mongo.

cue-37
00:02:11.450 --> 00:02:16.260
A prayer house now stands there. Chief
Lunenga has been baptized, and 60 to

cue-38
00:02:16.260 --> 00:02:20.280
70 children attend school, taught by a
local Christian teacher.

cue-39
00:02:21.560 --> 00:02:25.780
Few mission fields have seen local
believers lead such wide outreach as the

cue-40
00:02:25.780 --> 00:02:26.500
Congo mission.

cue-41
00:02:27.320 --> 00:02:31.300
From the start, every church member has
taken on a personal share of service.

cue-42
00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:36.540
At Wathen Station, the native church
supports 15 local evangelists.

cue-43
00:02:37.260 --> 00:02:41.180
44 outstations are visited by native
workers. Schools have

cue-44
00:02:41.180 --> 00:02:45.920
1,507 day students and 807 Sunday
students,

cue-45
00:02:45.920 --> 00:02:49.140
and 15 people form the Wathen Temperance
Society.

cue-46
00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:54.160
All costs for this evangelistic and
educational work are covered by the native

cue-47
00:02:54.160 --> 00:02:55.320
Christians themselves.

cue-48
00:02:56.160 --> 00:03:00.720
Mr. Bell's sympathetic portrait of Matula
will surely fuel more missionary passion.

cue-49
00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:05.440
It may inspire many young men to dedicate
their lives to bringing Africa to

cue-50
00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:05.820
Christ.

cue-51
00:03:06.670 --> 00:03:11.000
To most readers, it may seem I've become
overly enthusiastic about the life of a

cue-52
00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:12.260
simple Congolese man.

cue-53
00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:17.880
Yet we should value truth, sincerity, and
honesty wherever they appear,

cue-54
00:03:17.880 --> 00:03:20.750
remembering that God made all nations from
one family,

cue-55
00:03:21.420 --> 00:03:22.840
and we are all his children.

cue-56
00:03:24.140 --> 00:03:27.980
Africans have rightly been judged harshly
for habits of submission, cunning, and

cue-57
00:03:27.980 --> 00:03:28.500
cruelty.

cue-58
00:03:29.180 --> 00:03:33.740
But when in such a setting, we find an
African gentleman despised by his peers

cue-59
00:03:33.740 --> 00:03:38.640
for his honesty, sincerity, and kindness,
and know he represents many more,

cue-60
00:03:38.640 --> 00:03:43.620
we owe it to him to give thanks to God
and be encouraged. The tale of Matula's

cue-61
00:03:43.620 --> 00:03:48.160
remarkable escape was told across England,
Ireland, and America by the Reverend

cue-62
00:03:48.160 --> 00:03:52.880
R.H.C. Graham of San Salvador during his
furloughs in 1898 and

cue-63
00:03:52.880 --> 00:03:53.920
1899.

cue-64
00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:58.500
Many urged him to publish it as a
pamphlet. He hoped it would fit into Mr.

cue-65
00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:03.220
Bentley's then-in-progress Pioneering on
the Congo, but Bentley ultimately could

cue-66
00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:04.400
not make room for it.

cue-67
00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:09.200
I, too, had intended to write Matula's
story after his return to Ngombe.

cue-68
00:04:10.080 --> 00:04:14.440
Soon afterward, I went home on furlough,
and other duties filled my time until I

cue-69
00:04:14.440 --> 00:04:15.200
nearly forgot.

cue-70
00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:19.180
In 1901, I met Matula traveling to the
station.

cue-71
00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:20.519
He looked frail.

cue-72
00:04:21.180 --> 00:04:22.380
We feared sleep sickness,

cue-73
00:04:23.080 --> 00:04:24.480
and we thought he might not live long,

cue-74
00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:26.280
taking his story with him.

cue-75
00:04:27.100 --> 00:04:31.140
I arranged to meet him and his wife the
next morning and over the following days,

cue-76
00:04:31.140 --> 00:04:34.140
and from their accounts, I gathered the
key facts of his life.

cue-77
00:04:35.140 --> 00:04:39.700
When I told Mr. Graham about my plan, he
kindly urged me to go ahead and succeed,

cue-78
00:04:39.700 --> 00:04:44.360
and he sent the full report of Matula's
trial, which he witnessed himself.

cue-79
00:04:45.160 --> 00:04:46.380
I am deeply grateful to him.

cue-80
00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:51.360
I'm sure everyone who heard parts of
Matula's story from Mr. Graham or me

cue-81
00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:55.960
during deputation will welcome this brief
yet complete account of his life.

cue-82
00:04:56.800 --> 00:05:01.720
This little book is dedicated to all who
have shared, even in the smallest way,

cue-83
00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:04.800
in bringing the gospel to the dark land of
the Congo.

cue-84
00:05:09.860 --> 00:05:11.440
Chapter 1. Without Hope

cue-85
00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:18.560
Before 1871, no one really knew what lay
deep inside the Congo.

cue-86
00:05:19.320 --> 00:05:23.540
People thought it could never be explored
because the forests, rivers, and swamps

cue-87
00:05:23.540 --> 00:05:24.620
were so hard to cross.

cue-88
00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:30.260
Many tried and failed, and for years the
heart of Africa remained a blank spot on

cue-89
00:05:30.260 --> 00:05:30.660
the map.

cue-90
00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:36.440
Then Henry Stanley made his daring
journey. He started at Zanzibar on the

cue-91
00:05:36.440 --> 00:05:40.860
east coast, traveled across the continent,
and finally reached the mouth of the

cue-92
00:05:40.860 --> 00:05:42.920
Congo River on the west coast.

cue-93
00:05:43.700 --> 00:05:48.180
His trip let the world see the land's
rivers, forests, and mountains, and meet

cue-94
00:05:48.180 --> 00:05:52.360
some of the people who lived there. Yet
most of their story stayed hidden,

cue-95
00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:54.740
and for the most part, still is.

cue-96
00:05:55.660 --> 00:06:00.180
Still, we can notice some general things
about the Congo peoples. All their

cue-97
00:06:00.180 --> 00:06:05.180
dialects share a simple, clear structure,
and they nearly use the same word for

cue-98
00:06:05.180 --> 00:06:10.180
God.Long ago, their ancestors built huts,
made spears, forged

cue-99
00:06:10.180 --> 00:06:13.200
hoes, and farmed the land with skill and
care.

cue-100
00:06:14.080 --> 00:06:18.980
Over time, however, they stopped inventing
new tools or ideas. They copied old ways

cue-101
00:06:18.980 --> 00:06:20.340
without creating anything new.

cue-102
00:06:21.040 --> 00:06:22.720
Action and thought feed each other.

cue-103
00:06:23.460 --> 00:06:27.600
But when people turn away from what is
good and give in to their lowest desires,

cue-104
00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:29.120
their minds grow dull.

cue-105
00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:33.959
They find it hard even to imagine pure
thoughts, let alone live by them.

cue-106
00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:39.420
As the Bible says, when people are given
over to vile passions, they ignore God's

cue-107
00:06:39.420 --> 00:06:42.020
creation and focus only on themselves.

cue-108
00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:47.020
We don't know exactly when or how the
Congo peoples lost the light they once

cue-109
00:06:47.020 --> 00:06:51.200
had, but the darkness closed in because
they refused to acknowledge God.

cue-110
00:06:52.920 --> 00:06:57.270
In their present state, these people know
God's name but are so bound by

cue-111
00:06:57.270 --> 00:07:01.600
superstition that anyone who speaks of him
is called a sorcerer. They refuse to

cue-112
00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:04.920
listen about God, and mentioning him marks
you as a witch.

cue-113
00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:08.190
Expecting widespread progress among them
is useless.

cue-114
00:07:08.840 --> 00:07:13.100
Yet occasionally in such a setting, you
meet someone utterly different from those

cue-115
00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:16.920
around him. He lives in that world but
rises above it.

cue-116
00:07:18.160 --> 00:07:20.320
For him, we must accept a simple truth.

cue-117
00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:25.340
Even in the darkest places and among the
most degraded, God always leaves a

cue-118
00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:25.720
witness.

cue-119
00:07:26.410 --> 00:07:30.860
That person often doesn't understand his
own conflict. He joins the crowd watching

cue-120
00:07:30.860 --> 00:07:34.680
horrors that his whole being rejects while
others cheer murder.

cue-121
00:07:35.580 --> 00:07:39.760
At times, he may take part in their wild
rites, but he is never happy and hides his

cue-122
00:07:39.760 --> 00:07:41.880
feelings, knowing they will be
misunderstood.

cue-123
00:07:42.540 --> 00:07:46.530
The people call him a witch and feel
uneasy around him, though they can't say

cue-124
00:07:46.530 --> 00:07:46.800
why.

cue-125
00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:52.420
He has no clear light to guide him and
doesn't know where to find it. Many such

cue-126
00:07:52.420 --> 00:07:57.220
souls have lived and died in the Congo
through the ages. Their quiet resistance

cue-127
00:07:57.220 --> 00:08:00.000
held back total evil, but only just.

cue-128
00:08:00.760 --> 00:08:05.140
Matula was one of these until the gospel
came. Without the work of Christian

cue-129
00:08:05.140 --> 00:08:09.680
missionaries, he would have lived and
died, hated by his peers and misunderstood

cue-130
00:08:09.680 --> 00:08:14.440
by his friends, simply because his
gentle, humble nature clashed with

cue-131
00:08:14.440 --> 00:08:15.540
everything around him.

cue-132
00:08:16.950 --> 00:08:21.779
Much of this may seem exaggerated or hard
to believe, but it helps to remember how

cue-133
00:08:21.780 --> 00:08:26.500
simple and how trusting the average Congo
native can be. He

cue-134
00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:29.020
dreams often and believes his dreams are
real.

cue-135
00:08:29.760 --> 00:08:30.970
He echoes Tennyson's line,

cue-136
00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:36.499
Dreams are true while they last, and adds,
And we must take revenge for our dreams.

cue-137
00:08:37.480 --> 00:08:41.100
I wouldn't be surprised if many people in
the Congo have been murdered because

cue-138
00:08:41.100 --> 00:08:45.820
someone, convinced by a dream, believed
their enemy had done them harm

cue-139
00:08:45.820 --> 00:08:50.300
there. To them, a dream is as real as any
waking event.

cue-140
00:08:51.010 --> 00:08:55.440
They live surrounded by powerful
superstitions. A rustling leaf might be a

cue-141
00:08:55.440 --> 00:08:59.900
spirit moving nearby, and anything unusual
is blamed on witchcraft.

cue-142
00:09:00.720 --> 00:09:05.540
Anyone who shines at a craft or excels in
trade is suspected of having a spirit's

cue-143
00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:08.440
help and might be killed to stop future
harm.

cue-144
00:09:09.190 --> 00:09:12.840
They believe deeply in fate and feel
powerless to avoid disaster.

cue-145
00:09:13.520 --> 00:09:17.500
A person accused of witchcraft usually
accepts the challenge to prove their

cue-146
00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.000
innocence, certain they will pass the
test.

cue-147
00:09:20.600 --> 00:09:23.880
If they fail, the community feels
justified in punishing them.

cue-148
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:29.060
They think a stranger can't bewitch them,
so when illness or death strikes, they

cue-149
00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:32.120
search only among the victim's own people
for a witch.

cue-150
00:09:32.820 --> 00:09:37.500
Every sickness, every death is blamed on
sorcery. In hunting or

cue-151
00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:42.140
fighting, they believe no one can be
harmed or no animal taken unless they

cue-152
00:09:42.140 --> 00:09:43.280
first honor their fetish.

cue-153
00:09:44.160 --> 00:09:49.080
Even in war, if a warrior falls, they say
he was hit by the enemy's fetish but

cue-154
00:09:49.080 --> 00:09:53.860
actually killed by a witch among his own
side. In almost every part of life,

cue-155
00:09:53.860 --> 00:09:58.600
people feel controlled either by fetishism
or by witchcraft, sometimes both at

cue-156
00:09:58.600 --> 00:09:58.900
once.

cue-157
00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:04.100
For instance, if a disease won't yield to
a fetish's power, they turn to witchcraft,

cue-158
00:10:04.700 --> 00:10:07.620
or in war they may use both methods
together.

cue-159
00:10:08.620 --> 00:10:10.620
Families are also defined very broadly.

cue-160
00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:15.780
All members of a clan, or even everyone
from the same town, call each other

cue-161
00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:16.800
brothers and sisters.

cue-162
00:10:17.440 --> 00:10:21.400
A mother's brothers and sisters are all
called mothers, and a father's brothers

cue-163
00:10:21.400 --> 00:10:23.100
and sisters are all fathers.

cue-164
00:10:23.840 --> 00:10:28.520
With so many mothers and fathers, it can
be nearly impossible to tell who someone's

cue-165
00:10:28.520 --> 00:10:29.590
real parents are,

cue-166
00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:35.200
and so children end up with many mothers
and many fathers. This book isn't meant to

cue-167
00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:38.290
explain all the customs and beliefs of
the Congolese people.

cue-168
00:10:39.140 --> 00:10:41.760
I mention them only when they help tell
Matula's story.

cue-169
00:10:42.460 --> 00:10:47.280
My goal is simply to share the life of one
of our kindest and most devoted native

cue-170
00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:47.820
Christians.

cue-171
00:10:48.680 --> 00:10:52.880
I hope readers will trust its truth and
thank God, who wonderfully guided and

cue-172
00:10:52.880 --> 00:10:55.260
protected Matula in his darkest times.

cue-173
00:10:58.980 --> 00:10:59.680
Chapter 2.

cue-174
00:11:00.320 --> 00:11:01.140
Birth of Matula.

cue-175
00:11:03.520 --> 00:11:05.480
For ages, the Congo lay in darkness,

cue-176
00:11:06.160 --> 00:11:08.580
so dark that no one knew when it began.

cue-177
00:11:09.560 --> 00:11:14.240
After a long pitch-black stretch, people
on the coast shouted, The dawn is here!

cue-178
00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:15.260
The dawn is here!

cue-179
00:11:16.020 --> 00:11:19.760
They meant the first missionaries from
Rome had arrived to share Christianity.

cue-180
00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:24.200
But their visit was like a single flash of
lightning in a stormy sky,

cue-181
00:11:24.840 --> 00:11:27.180
brief and leaving no real light.

cue-182
00:11:27.860 --> 00:11:31.560
That true dawn would not come for nearly
two hundred more years.

cue-183
00:11:32.460 --> 00:11:36.980
By then, the people had fallen into the
lowest level of cruelty and chaos one can

cue-184
00:11:36.980 --> 00:11:41.620
imagine. There was no law or order. The
strong enslaved the weak,

cue-185
00:11:41.620 --> 00:11:43.800
even selling their former masters.

cue-186
00:11:44.540 --> 00:11:49.500
Bands of raiders captured anyone traveling
alone and sold them as slaves. Would-be

cue-187
00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:54.120
rulers filled their towns with stolen
people. No one could seek help or

cue-188
00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:58.660
justice. Everyone lived in fear. Yet even
in that disorder, a few

cue-189
00:11:58.660 --> 00:11:59.680
crafts survived.

cue-190
00:12:00.350 --> 00:12:04.400
Blacksmiths still worked iron, and potters
shaped clay into pots.

cue-191
00:12:05.220 --> 00:12:08.640
When Europeans settled on the coast
hundreds of years earlier, they brought

cue-192
00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:13.349
new tools and goods.Those items reached
the interior by trading hands.

cue-193
00:12:13.970 --> 00:12:18.410
The Congolese people, skilled at copying,
made rough versions of what they saw:

cue-194
00:12:19.140 --> 00:12:23.820
simple clothes, basic wooden furniture,
doing their best to carry on these

cue-195
00:12:23.820 --> 00:12:26.120
trades despite the darkness around them.

cue-196
00:12:26.980 --> 00:12:31.640
They couldn't make guns themselves, so
they bought them at very high prices. The

cue-197
00:12:31.640 --> 00:12:33.720
farther inland you went, the fewer you
saw.

cue-198
00:12:34.340 --> 00:12:38.480
Many blacksmiths did a good business
making bullets and slugs for hunting and

cue-199
00:12:38.480 --> 00:12:38.740
war.

cue-200
00:12:39.580 --> 00:12:43.680
People knew how to work iron well, even
though they didn't mine it

cue-201
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:48.460
deeply. When one spot's surface ore ran
out, they simply moved on to a

cue-202
00:12:48.460 --> 00:12:53.120
richer one. About twenty years before
Comber and Hartland

cue-203
00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:57.720
arrived at Mbanza Makuta in 1880, there
was a town nearby called Mongo.

cue-204
00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:03.070
It was founded by four brothers, Nimu and
his siblings, who were skilled smiths.

cue-205
00:13:03.070 --> 00:13:05.160
They were prosperous and owned many
slaves.

cue-206
00:13:05.800 --> 00:13:09.980
Supplying bullets and slugs across the
countryside made them wealthy, but as they

cue-207
00:13:09.980 --> 00:13:14.640
had to go farther for ore, they decided
to settle on a prime site and named it

cue-208
00:13:14.640 --> 00:13:15.160
Mongo.

cue-209
00:13:16.140 --> 00:13:20.940
Nimu, the eldest, became chief, and a
harsh one at that. He feared any nephew

cue-210
00:13:20.940 --> 00:13:22.540
might grow up to challenge him.

cue-211
00:13:23.250 --> 00:13:27.000
Whenever one of his brothers had a baby,
he demanded to know its sex.

cue-212
00:13:27.660 --> 00:13:30.520
If it was a boy, he killed the child with
a blow to the head.

cue-213
00:13:31.180 --> 00:13:35.600
Girls, however, increased his wealth.
Their future husbands paid a high bride

cue-214
00:13:35.600 --> 00:13:39.880
price, often right after birth. His
brothers could not stand his cruelty

cue-215
00:13:39.880 --> 00:13:40.200
forever.

cue-216
00:13:40.990 --> 00:13:42.560
They each built their own towns.

cue-217
00:13:43.180 --> 00:13:46.840
One brother, Mpanzu, founded Nsamba just a
short distance away.

cue-218
00:13:47.500 --> 00:13:49.210
But Nimu kept tormenting them,

cue-219
00:13:49.820 --> 00:13:51.110
so they plotted to remove him.

cue-220
00:13:51.900 --> 00:13:56.100
On a market day, they accused him of
witchcraft and forced him to drink poison.

cue-221
00:13:56.100 --> 00:14:00.520
As he weakened, they clubbed him to death
and looted all his possessions. About the

cue-222
00:14:00.520 --> 00:14:04.680
time Nimu was killed, another blacksmith
named Nku settled a little south of Mongo.

cue-223
00:14:04.680 --> 00:14:09.480
He brought his favorite young wife,
Mundele, a name borrowed from the word for

cue-224
00:14:09.480 --> 00:14:14.399
white man, since cloth first came from
Europeans, along with their slaves

cue-225
00:14:14.400 --> 00:14:15.120
and belongings.

cue-226
00:14:15.750 --> 00:14:18.660
They had come from a district over sixty
miles to the southeast.

cue-227
00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:23.560
Nku was well known for the anklets,
bracelets, and necklets he forged, and he

cue-228
00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:28.159
often traveled far to sell them. He found
a great market in the Makuta area, where

cue-229
00:14:28.160 --> 00:14:32.500
he also smelted iron ore. There he struck
up a strong friendship with

cue-230
00:14:32.500 --> 00:14:34.080
Mpanzu of Nsamba.

cue-231
00:14:34.740 --> 00:14:39.180
On returning from one profitable trip, Nku
discovered his household nearly starving.

cue-232
00:14:39.820 --> 00:14:44.300
So he decided to move closer to Mpanzu,
hoping for better security and trade.

cue-233
00:14:45.120 --> 00:14:49.100
His wife and the other women were uneasy.
If anything happened to Nku among

cue-234
00:14:49.100 --> 00:14:51.820
strangers, they feared being sold as
slaves.

cue-235
00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:56.160
But the promise of a safer, more
prosperous life won them over.

cue-236
00:14:56.980 --> 00:15:01.620
They built their new home about an hour or
two south of Mongo, not far from Nsamba.

cue-237
00:15:02.290 --> 00:15:07.000
Mpanzu was delighted to have his friend so
close. To the north ruled Lunyanga,

cue-238
00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:11.780
the proud and cruel chief of Nkondo. He
was known to execute anyone who offended

cue-239
00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:12.780
him, even slightly.

cue-240
00:15:13.520 --> 00:15:18.260
As Nku's fame and skill spread, Lunyanga
grew jealous and looked for a reason to

cue-241
00:15:18.260 --> 00:15:18.580
strike.

cue-242
00:15:19.260 --> 00:15:23.600
His harsh rule soon drew the ire of
neighboring chiefs, who fined him slaves

cue-243
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:26.360
and a large sum of shell money for
mistreating his people.

cue-244
00:15:27.140 --> 00:15:32.020
Unwilling to pay, Lunyanga devised a
darker plan. He would kill Nku and

cue-245
00:15:32.020 --> 00:15:34.040
seize his wealth to cover the fine.

cue-246
00:15:34.820 --> 00:15:38.480
He whispered his scheme to his own slaves,
promising them rich rewards,

cue-247
00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:43.420
and they eagerly agreed, for they had
joined him on such raids before. They

cue-248
00:15:43.420 --> 00:15:48.240
planned to strike that very night so word
wouldn't spread. As soon as darkness

cue-249
00:15:48.240 --> 00:15:49.700
fell, Lunyanga's men,

cue-250
00:15:50.340 --> 00:15:55.240
guns loaded, ammunition ready, slipped
past Mongo and Nsamba and crept

cue-251
00:15:55.240 --> 00:16:00.050
into Kinzembo, where Nku's village lay in
deep sleep. They surrounded the chief's

cue-252
00:16:00.050 --> 00:16:04.980
compound, posted lookouts by every exit,
and then, at a signal, opened fire

cue-253
00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:05.620
into the huts.

cue-254
00:16:06.420 --> 00:16:10.680
The men who rushed out were shot. The
women and girls were seized as captives.

cue-255
00:16:11.520 --> 00:16:15.700
In barely an hour, they looted everything
of value and marched their prisoners back

cue-256
00:16:15.700 --> 00:16:17.680
to Nkondo, arriving before dawn.

cue-257
00:16:18.380 --> 00:16:23.140
By morning, the massacre was known
everywhere, yet no one dared seek justice.

cue-258
00:16:23.140 --> 00:16:24.960
Many even celebrated.

cue-259
00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:27.220
"This land is ours,"

cue-260
00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:31.620
they proclaimed, and Lunyanga's pride and
power grew.

cue-261
00:16:32.350 --> 00:16:36.100
Those who had fined him earlier lost the
courage to demand their payment.

cue-262
00:16:37.700 --> 00:16:41.160
Mpanzu grieved for Nku but had no means to
punish Lunyanga.

cue-263
00:16:41.900 --> 00:16:46.630
To protect Nku's beloved young wife,
Mundele, from slavery at strange hands,

cue-264
00:16:46.630 --> 00:16:49.540
he bought her freedom and married her
himself.

cue-265
00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:54.460
He treated her with deep affection and
stored all his precious goods in her home,

cue-266
00:16:54.460 --> 00:16:59.420
a high mark of his esteem. As a wealthy
trader wanting an heir of his own blood,

cue-267
00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:05.079
Mpanzu prized Mundele above his other
wives, since children born to free women

cue-268
00:17:05.080 --> 00:17:09.780
belonged to their mother's family. Only a
son by Mundele would carry on Mpanzu's

cue-269
00:17:09.780 --> 00:17:14.520
name and inheritance. Mundele and Mpanzu
soon had a child, but it died

cue-270
00:17:14.520 --> 00:17:15.400
very young.

cue-271
00:17:16.020 --> 00:17:19.520
They were heartbroken. When another baby
came, it also died.

cue-272
00:17:20.320 --> 00:17:23.600
Mpanzu mourned deeply, but Mundele
suffered even more.

cue-273
00:17:24.220 --> 00:17:28.280
She accused him of casting spells on their
children. She could not forget that she

cue-274
00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:30.780
had once been free and respected among
women.

cue-275
00:17:31.480 --> 00:17:34.260
Now she was a slave, her first husband
dead,

cue-276
00:17:34.900 --> 00:17:37.940
her babies gone. The grief nearly drove
her mad.

cue-277
00:17:38.740 --> 00:17:40.660
One day her friends noticed she was
missing.

cue-278
00:17:41.400 --> 00:17:45.500
After searching, they found her in the
woods, lying in a small pool of blood.

cue-279
00:17:46.520 --> 00:17:47.720
She was almost unconscious.

cue-280
00:17:48.540 --> 00:17:51.540
They carried her home, and after several
days she recovered.

cue-281
00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:55.280
In her despair, she had cut her own throat
to end her life.

cue-282
00:17:56.600 --> 00:18:00.440
Poor Mundele knew nothing of why people
suffer or where comfort comes from.

cue-283
00:18:01.060 --> 00:18:04.880
She only knew God's name, and she called
on it again and again, crying,

cue-284
00:18:05.520 --> 00:18:08.020
"Nzambi ovanga-kansi kaze ye vanga ko."

cue-285
00:18:09.020 --> 00:18:09.640
God creates,

cue-286
00:18:10.320 --> 00:18:15.220
but he does not know how to create.Her
heart was dark with pain, and she

cue-287
00:18:15.220 --> 00:18:19.840
did not realize that God hears and answers
even the most anguished cries.

cue-288
00:18:20.620 --> 00:18:25.180
Yet in truth, her desperate prayer looked
for a dawn after that long night of

cue-289
00:18:25.180 --> 00:18:25.480
sorrow.

cue-290
00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:30.960
And God did answer. Her husband's family
and even she herself thought her

cue-291
00:18:30.960 --> 00:18:35.640
outburst was pagan superstition, but
before long she gave birth to a daughter

cue-292
00:18:35.640 --> 00:18:36.140
who lived.

cue-293
00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:39.679
Soon after came a son, whom they named
Matula.

cue-294
00:18:40.280 --> 00:18:45.280
Brighter days had arrived. In time she
bore seven healthy children, an almost

cue-295
00:18:45.280 --> 00:18:49.840
unheard-of blessing in the Congo. She
would live to see the light of a new day

cue-296
00:18:49.840 --> 00:18:54.020
for her land, and four or five of her
children would grow up to be earnest,

cue-297
00:18:54.020 --> 00:18:55.140
faithful Christians.

cue-298
00:18:59.120 --> 00:19:01.160
Chapter 3. Childhood of Matula

cue-299
00:19:03.220 --> 00:19:07.860
Childhood in the Congo can seem full of
freedom, but it is often harsh and lonely.

cue-300
00:19:08.780 --> 00:19:13.760
From dawn to dusk, children roam outdoors,
chasing insects or whatever catches their

cue-301
00:19:13.760 --> 00:19:17.000
eye, with nobody to call them home or
tell them to go to bed.

cue-302
00:19:17.880 --> 00:19:22.020
Even before they can crawl, a Congo baby
is tied to its mother's back each morning

cue-303
00:19:22.020 --> 00:19:23.220
and carried into the fields.

cue-304
00:19:23.900 --> 00:19:28.280
The infant's first view is the load
balanced on her head, sometimes baskets of

cue-305
00:19:28.280 --> 00:19:32.780
vegetables, a bundle of firewood, or a
heavy pot of water. As the child

cue-306
00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:37.619
grows, it learns to carry awkward loads on
its own head, since no one in the

cue-307
00:19:37.620 --> 00:19:40.640
Congo would carry on their arm what they
can hold on their head.

cue-308
00:19:41.500 --> 00:19:45.400
Once in the garden, the little one is set
down under a bush while the mother hoes

cue-309
00:19:45.400 --> 00:19:45.840
the earth.

cue-310
00:19:46.460 --> 00:19:51.240
If the baby cries, she stops to nurse it.
Then either the child falls asleep or she

cue-311
00:19:51.240 --> 00:19:56.210
straps it back onto her back, where it
finds a cradle of safety. Soon it begins

cue-312
00:19:56.210 --> 00:20:00.920
to crawl, exploring and sampling whatever
it can reach, fruits,

cue-313
00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:05.240
leaves, insects, learning by trial which
things are safe to eat.

cue-314
00:20:06.260 --> 00:20:09.800
The mother only intervenes when the child
touches a poisonous plant.

cue-315
00:20:10.720 --> 00:20:15.230
As they grow, children chase caterpillars,
frogs, and rats, and in doing so they

cue-316
00:20:15.230 --> 00:20:19.820
learn for themselves which creatures make
good food. They also pick up practical

cue-317
00:20:19.820 --> 00:20:23.680
knowledge of plants, which ones feed them,
which heal, and which harm.

cue-318
00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:29.140
Girls stay with their mothers, learning to
weed, hoe, sow, plant, and cook

cue-319
00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:30.840
all the way into young womanhood.

cue-320
00:20:31.760 --> 00:20:35.420
Boys spend only the first four or five
years by their mother's side.

cue-321
00:20:36.060 --> 00:20:38.280
After that, they must look after
themselves.

cue-322
00:20:39.080 --> 00:20:43.300
When a boy is old enough, he joins the
older boys in the woods all day. No

cue-323
00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:46.420
school, no punishments, just freedom
unless they start a fight.

cue-324
00:20:47.060 --> 00:20:49.920
Then the village holds a palaver to sort
out who was wrong.

cue-325
00:20:50.620 --> 00:20:55.060
As they wander, they watch ants,
squirrels, monkeys, and track antelope

cue-326
00:20:55.060 --> 00:20:59.380
through the undergrowth. Their favorite
pastime is rat hunting, and when they

cue-327
00:20:59.380 --> 00:21:03.440
bring home a good catch, their mother has
no trouble serving meat with their cassava

cue-328
00:21:03.440 --> 00:21:08.159
pudding. When a boy reaches about eight
years old, he may build a small hut for

cue-329
00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:10.260
himself or go live with some older boys.

cue-330
00:21:10.920 --> 00:21:13.890
By that age, he feels too grown up to stay
close to his mother,

cue-331
00:21:14.540 --> 00:21:16.120
except perhaps when he's hungry.

cue-332
00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:20.960
Around this time, he begins wearing a
cloth, and the men of the village may

cue-333
00:21:20.960 --> 00:21:21.880
start to notice him.

cue-334
00:21:22.680 --> 00:21:26.480
They might take him on trading trips and
use him for heavy work, though they give

cue-335
00:21:26.480 --> 00:21:27.340
him a small payment.

cue-336
00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:32.520
Some of my younger readers might think,
what a fun life those Congo boys must

cue-337
00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:37.040
have. No one to call them, no one to
bother them, no one to punish them.

cue-338
00:21:37.040 --> 00:21:39.120
Wouldn't it be great to live like that for
a while?

cue-339
00:21:40.320 --> 00:21:41.400
Yes, perhaps it would,

cue-340
00:21:42.080 --> 00:21:42.900
for a short time.

cue-341
00:21:43.580 --> 00:21:47.340
But when I felt very lonely, I would want
someone to keep me in check.

cue-342
00:21:48.200 --> 00:21:52.020
When I was tired and weary of always
having my own way, I would want someone to

cue-343
00:21:52.020 --> 00:21:53.520
care enough to bother with me.

cue-344
00:21:54.260 --> 00:21:56.250
And when I did something I knew was very
wrong,

cue-345
00:21:56.980 --> 00:22:00.660
I would want someone to correct me,
because that would bring peace to my

cue-346
00:22:00.660 --> 00:22:01.160
conscience.

cue-347
00:22:01.860 --> 00:22:04.760
It's sad how quickly these children grow
tired of wandering.

cue-348
00:22:05.420 --> 00:22:06.560
It gives them no purpose.

cue-349
00:22:07.320 --> 00:22:11.820
Soon they are left standing around the
village, looking dull and alone, with no

cue-350
00:22:11.820 --> 00:22:16.300
one to guide them and nothing to interest
them. When they fall sick, there is no one

cue-351
00:22:16.300 --> 00:22:16.700
to help,

cue-352
00:22:17.360 --> 00:22:17.680
because,

cue-353
00:22:18.500 --> 00:22:22.840
poor little ones, no one knows how to care
for the sick or give proper treatment.

cue-354
00:22:23.560 --> 00:22:26.520
If a child becomes ill, a local healer
might be called.

cue-355
00:22:27.189 --> 00:22:30.039
He will rub his hand over the child's body
and say some words.

cue-356
00:22:30.680 --> 00:22:34.900
But when the illness becomes serious,
there is no one to cool the hot forehead,

cue-357
00:22:34.940 --> 00:22:39.740
no one to moisten dry lips, no one to sing
a gentle song to comfort the child.

cue-358
00:22:39.740 --> 00:22:44.540
Drums may be beaten, and traditional
dances may begin, but these

cue-359
00:22:44.540 --> 00:22:46.600
only disturb the suffering child.

cue-360
00:22:47.360 --> 00:22:52.160
As the fever rises, the child's covering
may be taken off, and the dancers become

cue-361
00:22:52.160 --> 00:22:55.200
louder, dancing, shouting, and calling
out,

cue-362
00:22:55.830 --> 00:22:59.460
until the little one may pass away, killed
by exposure and cold.

cue-363
00:23:00.120 --> 00:23:03.460
Not from cruelty, but from a deep, dark
ignorance.

cue-364
00:23:05.120 --> 00:23:08.820
Those who grow up in the Congo really live
by survival of the fittest.

cue-365
00:23:11.440 --> 00:23:14.020
It was in that setting that Matula was
born and raised.

cue-366
00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:17.980
His childhood was much like what I have
already described for any boy.

cue-367
00:23:18.700 --> 00:23:22.940
When he was about eight, his father gave
him a small drum. Many days he would play

cue-368
00:23:22.940 --> 00:23:27.540
it for himself, calling the other boys and
girls to dance just like the grown-ups.

cue-369
00:23:28.250 --> 00:23:32.680
They would copy the funeral, wedding, and
fetish dances, which are all quite

cue-370
00:23:32.680 --> 00:23:35.559
similar, and only a keen ear can tell them
apart.

cue-371
00:23:36.460 --> 00:23:40.040
They played house and pretended to cook
and clean, but not for long.

cue-372
00:23:40.780 --> 00:23:42.880
One day was especially exciting.

cue-373
00:23:43.700 --> 00:23:47.740
After an argument with the townspeople,
Matula's father decided to move the whole

cue-374
00:23:47.740 --> 00:23:49.620
village about a quarter of a mile away.

cue-375
00:23:50.260 --> 00:23:53.830
Matula didn't mind the quarrel. He loved
the excitement of moving,

cue-376
00:23:54.580 --> 00:23:55.700
what we call flitting.

cue-377
00:23:56.700 --> 00:24:00.720
Moving a village from one place to another
is common there. People move for many

cue-378
00:24:00.720 --> 00:24:04.860
reasons, jealousy, sickness, lack of food,
or bad neighbors.

cue-379
00:24:05.510 --> 00:24:07.180
Those planning to move help each other.

cue-380
00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:12.400
First they choose and mark the new site.
Then they take apart their old houses,

cue-381
00:24:12.400 --> 00:24:16.540
lifting off roofs, removing walls, and
carrying each piece to the new

cue-382
00:24:16.540 --> 00:24:21.160
spot.Strong men carry the uprights and
ridgepoles, and then the roofs.

cue-383
00:24:21.800 --> 00:24:26.780
In one day, they can tear down and rebuild
several houses. Matula enjoyed helping

cue-384
00:24:26.780 --> 00:24:29.480
move his father's houses for his wives
and slaves.

cue-385
00:24:30.110 --> 00:24:34.040
The quarrel that caused the move didn't
last long, and he was happy to return to

cue-386
00:24:34.040 --> 00:24:34.680
the old site.

cue-387
00:24:35.340 --> 00:24:38.779
He was a cheerful boy those days,
especially when his father took him to

cue-388
00:24:38.780 --> 00:24:43.779
market. He knew they would not come home
empty-handed. But some days he had to wait

cue-389
00:24:43.779 --> 00:24:47.700
for hours on the road while his father
drank palm wine with friends.

cue-390
00:24:48.450 --> 00:24:51.900
Sometimes the children were called to
drink too, and so they learned to be

cue-391
00:24:51.900 --> 00:24:56.240
drunkards from an early age. As a boy, his
mother never let him go to the town

cue-392
00:24:56.240 --> 00:24:58.520
dance, a dance beyond words.

cue-393
00:24:59.160 --> 00:25:04.040
He watched his parents dress for it,
wearing their finest clothes and jewelry.

cue-394
00:25:04.040 --> 00:25:08.520
His father draped a leopard skin over
himself, hung a knife at his waist, and

cue-395
00:25:08.520 --> 00:25:13.320
styled his hair in ridges or shaved
patterns with patches of red ochre on his

cue-396
00:25:13.320 --> 00:25:13.600
face.

cue-397
00:25:14.440 --> 00:25:19.320
His mother wore bright anklets, a necklace
of beads or shells, touches of red on her

cue-398
00:25:19.320 --> 00:25:24.270
cheeks, and elaborate haircuts. They
usually set off late at night, locking

cue-399
00:25:24.270 --> 00:25:28.840
the little ones inside the house. The
children fell asleep to the drum's steady

cue-400
00:25:28.840 --> 00:25:31.360
thump and the dancers' constant jingle.

cue-401
00:25:32.180 --> 00:25:35.240
It was a carefree, happy, yet touching
childhood.

cue-402
00:25:36.220 --> 00:25:39.880
Matula slept peacefully, unaware of the
future trials before him.

cue-403
00:25:40.720 --> 00:25:45.420
Oh, childhood, how many would give
anything to return to your innocence, your

cue-404
00:25:45.420 --> 00:25:46.600
playful pranks?

cue-405
00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:49.840
Yet later, Matula discovered another
childhood,

cue-406
00:25:50.480 --> 00:25:54.860
one known only to those who live under the
Gospel. That alone makes coming to the

cue-407
00:25:54.860 --> 00:25:59.760
Congo worthwhile, to bring this true
childhood even to those who hear the wild

cue-408
00:25:59.760 --> 00:26:01.960
cries of slaves sold or beaten,

cue-409
00:26:02.640 --> 00:26:05.130
or the silent groans of their murdered
victims.

cue-410
00:26:05.860 --> 00:26:10.780
Without Christ, this land remains dark and
hopeless, with no restored childhood

cue-411
00:26:10.780 --> 00:26:12.240
and no forgiveness for the guilty.

cue-412
00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:18.660
Chapter Four: Murder of His Father.

cue-413
00:26:21.040 --> 00:26:25.600
One day, Mpanzu sent his ten-year-old son
to the market with him. Matula was

cue-414
00:26:25.600 --> 00:26:30.060
overjoyed, and he never forgot that trip,
for it was the last time they went

cue-415
00:26:30.060 --> 00:26:30.370
together.

cue-416
00:26:31.180 --> 00:26:35.140
In the market, people talked about the
many deaths around them and how few

cue-417
00:26:35.140 --> 00:26:39.840
children were being born. Everyone feared
their people would disappear unless they

cue-418
00:26:39.840 --> 00:26:44.200
acted. They talked of two plans: to form a
secret society called

cue-419
00:26:44.200 --> 00:26:48.020
Ndenbo, described in Mr. Bentley's
Pioneering on the Congo,

cue-420
00:26:48.680 --> 00:26:50.860
or to find the witch they blamed for the
deaths.

cue-421
00:26:51.540 --> 00:26:56.200
After much debate, they chose the secret
society, hoping it would protect the young

cue-422
00:26:56.200 --> 00:26:57.220
if the elders died.

cue-423
00:26:57.920 --> 00:27:00.440
Matula did not hear when the Ndenbo
meeting would be,

cue-424
00:27:01.060 --> 00:27:02.520
so he and his father walked home,

cue-425
00:27:03.220 --> 00:27:03.680
carefree.

cue-426
00:27:04.520 --> 00:27:06.700
His father carried half a sheep to share
at home.

cue-427
00:27:07.400 --> 00:27:11.080
All the children sat on the ground like
puppies, watching him cut the meat.

cue-428
00:27:11.909 --> 00:27:14.620
There were so many that it was hard to
give everyone a fair share.

cue-429
00:27:15.240 --> 00:27:19.780
Matula wanted a big bone, but it went to
his older half-brother. He burst into

cue-430
00:27:19.780 --> 00:27:23.580
tears, refused the smaller piece, and was
sent to bed by his father.

cue-431
00:27:24.420 --> 00:27:26.380
He did not remain upset for long.

cue-432
00:27:27.140 --> 00:27:32.120
Before bedtime, he heard the drum and the
witch doctor's chant. He crept

cue-433
00:27:32.120 --> 00:27:34.300
outside and lay on the ground as if dead.

cue-434
00:27:35.080 --> 00:27:37.719
Others did the same, covering themselves
with cloth.

cue-435
00:27:38.460 --> 00:27:43.100
There was singing and gunfire, and then
all who died were carried to a camp in the

cue-436
00:27:43.100 --> 00:27:44.640
woods just outside town.

cue-437
00:27:45.500 --> 00:27:49.640
Matula counted about one hundred boys and
girls there, most from nearby

cue-438
00:27:49.640 --> 00:27:54.480
villages. He stayed in that camp for
nearly ten months, taking part in their

cue-439
00:27:54.480 --> 00:27:55.980
empty, sensual rituals.

cue-440
00:27:56.710 --> 00:28:00.520
The children chose him as their leader and
gave him a new name, Masamba.

cue-441
00:28:01.180 --> 00:28:05.460
No one dared come near the camp. To the
townspeople, they were truly dead.

cue-442
00:28:06.420 --> 00:28:09.020
Matula heard nothing of the world outside
until his return,

cue-443
00:28:09.700 --> 00:28:13.319
and then he learned the terrible news that
his father had been murdered.

cue-444
00:28:15.540 --> 00:28:19.680
After they formed the Ndenbo, everyone
told themselves that sickness and death

cue-445
00:28:19.680 --> 00:28:20.400
would leave them.

cue-446
00:28:21.280 --> 00:28:22.840
For a few weeks, it seemed to work.

cue-447
00:28:23.440 --> 00:28:28.220
But when the cold, dry season arrived,
like a harsh winter, it found the weak and

cue-448
00:28:28.220 --> 00:28:33.180
old, and every year it claimed its share
of graves. They asked, "How can

cue-449
00:28:33.180 --> 00:28:35.500
we stop this terrible death? Who is the
witch?"

cue-450
00:28:36.780 --> 00:28:38.520
Their suspicions fell on one man,

cue-451
00:28:39.310 --> 00:28:44.000
Mpanzu. If only he had been happy with one
wife and a small trading business,

cue-452
00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:45.500
things might have been different.

cue-453
00:28:46.220 --> 00:28:50.900
But his ambition and greed did him in, as
they have done to many, even in

cue-454
00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:55.120
Christian lands. He had over a dozen wives
and thirty or forty children.

cue-455
00:28:55.800 --> 00:28:57.780
He was a famous, wealthy trader.

cue-456
00:28:58.840 --> 00:29:02.700
So why did he have so many children when
others had none or were dying?

cue-457
00:29:03.380 --> 00:29:05.500
Why was he rich while his relatives were
poor?

cue-458
00:29:06.220 --> 00:29:08.140
To them, there was only one answer:

cue-459
00:29:08.920 --> 00:29:09.480
witchcraft.

cue-460
00:29:11.090 --> 00:29:13.230
They called a big meeting with the witch
doctor,

cue-461
00:29:14.040 --> 00:29:18.660
but they did not invite Mpanzu. In the
middle of the doctor's fierce, swirling

cue-462
00:29:18.660 --> 00:29:20.480
dance, he shouted Mpanzu's name.

cue-463
00:29:21.310 --> 00:29:26.240
"It's Mpanzu." Everyone agreed. They
planned that early the next morning, some

cue-464
00:29:26.240 --> 00:29:30.770
friends would lure the townspeople away
with a controlled bushfire while Mpanzu

cue-465
00:29:30.770 --> 00:29:35.700
would stay behind to drink palm wine with
visiting chiefs. At dawn, the hunters

cue-466
00:29:35.700 --> 00:29:40.420
set off, excited, chasing rats, wild cats,
and antelopes fleeing the

cue-467
00:29:40.420 --> 00:29:40.960
flames.

cue-468
00:29:41.900 --> 00:29:45.959
Mpanzu felt honored by the chiefs'
arrival. They came in solemn, stately

cue-469
00:29:45.960 --> 00:29:48.500
procession as if they were lords of
creation.

cue-470
00:29:49.340 --> 00:29:53.060
Mats were laid for them to sit on, and
they exchanged formal greetings.

cue-471
00:29:53.800 --> 00:29:58.560
Then the calabash of palm wine was brought
out, hands clapped, and the drink passed

cue-472
00:29:58.560 --> 00:29:59.680
around in proper order.

cue-473
00:30:00.730 --> 00:30:02.170
The calabash went around again.

cue-474
00:30:02.880 --> 00:30:07.600
When Mpanzu lifted it to his lips, his
last drink, the killer standing behind him

cue-475
00:30:07.600 --> 00:30:09.900
quietly slipped a noose over his head.

cue-476
00:30:10.690 --> 00:30:15.500
They carried him away with no wife or
child nearby to weep or plead.

cue-477
00:30:16.150 --> 00:30:21.076
Their plan was made in secret, and they
took him to an even more hidden spot.There

cue-478
00:30:21.076 --> 00:30:25.416
they did their cruel deed, thinking they
were doing right by removing a witch.

cue-479
00:30:26.056 --> 00:30:30.236
They beat him brutally, then hung him from
a tree and left his body to rot.

cue-480
00:30:30.976 --> 00:30:34.336
Truly, the darkest places on earth hide
the worst cruelty.

cue-481
00:30:34.976 --> 00:30:39.456
Oh Earth, when will you give up the blood
of your slaughtered sons? When will the

cue-482
00:30:39.456 --> 00:30:40.836
innocent be avenged?

cue-483
00:30:41.756 --> 00:30:46.576
All across the Congo, almost every hour,
the cry of some murdered victim

cue-484
00:30:46.576 --> 00:30:48.555
rose up, asking for justice.

cue-485
00:30:49.336 --> 00:30:54.015
It was a cry in the night, but God, who
never sleeps, heard it, and thank God He

cue-486
00:30:54.016 --> 00:30:54.306
answered.

cue-487
00:30:55.066 --> 00:30:59.976
Today, in part, that answer has come.
Peace declared, sin forgiven for all who

cue-488
00:30:59.976 --> 00:31:04.765
accept it, even those whose hands are
stained with blood. Many in the Congo have

cue-489
00:31:04.765 --> 00:31:09.496
atoned for their terrible sins. Through
Christ, they stand cleansed and

cue-490
00:31:09.496 --> 00:31:09.976
redeemed.

cue-491
00:31:11.256 --> 00:31:15.636
Poor Matula felt his father's murder more
deeply than any other sorrow he had known.

cue-492
00:31:16.356 --> 00:31:19.876
His father had been proud of him. Matula
was meant to be his heir.

cue-493
00:31:20.656 --> 00:31:25.496
Now he returned to find no money left, his
mother sold as a slave to another man,

cue-494
00:31:25.496 --> 00:31:28.916
and all his father's slaves and herds
scattered by sale.

cue-495
00:31:29.776 --> 00:31:34.576
Now this eleven-year-old boy must earn his
living by trading, both to avoid being

cue-496
00:31:34.576 --> 00:31:37.566
sold himself and to help free his mother
from slavery.

cue-497
00:31:41.196 --> 00:31:43.696
Chapter Five: First News of the White Man

cue-498
00:31:46.116 --> 00:31:51.116
Matula was no longer a child. He had to go
out into the world to help his mother win

cue-499
00:31:51.116 --> 00:31:54.656
her freedom and to care for his five
younger brothers and sisters.

cue-500
00:31:55.576 --> 00:32:00.036
About a year had passed since the last
chapter, and now Matula was on his way to

cue-501
00:32:00.036 --> 00:32:00.916
market with his mother.

cue-502
00:32:01.616 --> 00:32:05.916
He had become a young trader and visited
all the nearby markets. There was a

cue-503
00:32:05.916 --> 00:32:10.315
rotating daily market held in four
different towns, returning to the first

cue-504
00:32:10.316 --> 00:32:11.756
spot every fourth day.

cue-505
00:32:12.496 --> 00:32:16.796
This system meant each town had frequent
markets, and in many areas people could

cue-506
00:32:16.796 --> 00:32:19.196
reach a market every day with little
trouble.

cue-507
00:32:19.916 --> 00:32:23.996
On this particular morning, Matula and his
mother arrived early at the open market

cue-508
00:32:23.996 --> 00:32:24.316
square.

cue-509
00:32:25.176 --> 00:32:29.275
Let us join them and watch the traders
coming in from every direction. Women

cue-510
00:32:29.276 --> 00:32:34.236
carried baskets heavy with kwanga,
plantains, palm nuts, ground nuts, nezalu,

cue-511
00:32:34.236 --> 00:32:38.736
and pineapples, either balanced on their
heads or slung over their shoulders. Men

cue-512
00:32:38.736 --> 00:32:43.176
appeared too, one with cloth draped over
his shoulders, another showing off

cue-513
00:32:43.176 --> 00:32:47.995
polished anklets, one dragging a goat by
its legs, another carrying two chickens

cue-514
00:32:47.996 --> 00:32:51.136
under his arm, and yet another with a
small bag of salt.

cue-515
00:32:52.006 --> 00:32:55.396
The sellers squatted on the ground and
arranged their goods in front of them.

cue-516
00:32:56.196 --> 00:33:00.685
Buyers wove among the stalls, haggling
over small amounts of goods, yet they

cue-517
00:33:00.685 --> 00:33:05.576
wasted just as much time, breath, and
temper here as they would over large sums

cue-518
00:33:05.576 --> 00:33:06.096
back home.

cue-519
00:33:07.416 --> 00:33:12.236
Nearby, a group of palm wine drinkers held
court, and bundles of firewood lay in

cue-520
00:33:12.236 --> 00:33:12.546
waiting.

cue-521
00:33:13.666 --> 00:33:14.536
"What's happening, Matula?"

cue-522
00:33:15.556 --> 00:33:16.316
his mother asked.

cue-523
00:33:17.106 --> 00:33:17.636
"Wait and see,"

cue-524
00:33:18.616 --> 00:33:19.066
he whispered.

cue-525
00:33:20.156 --> 00:33:22.316
Soon a boy knelt to light the firewood.

cue-526
00:33:22.926 --> 00:33:24.836
The man with the goat began beating it,

cue-527
00:33:25.476 --> 00:33:29.976
not hard enough to kill at first, but with
steady strokes that drove the frightened

cue-528
00:33:29.976 --> 00:33:31.125
animal to exhaustion.

cue-529
00:33:32.276 --> 00:33:37.256
Finally, the goat collapsed, still alive.
They dragged it onto the blazing fire. It

cue-530
00:33:37.256 --> 00:33:41.476
was too cruel to watch, better to move on
before we hear its desperate bleating.

cue-531
00:33:42.236 --> 00:33:47.176
This brutal practice still goes on today
and will not end until a law forbids

cue-532
00:33:47.176 --> 00:33:47.336
it.

cue-533
00:33:48.136 --> 00:33:52.536
Our own influence, wherever it reaches,
stands firmly against such needless

cue-534
00:33:52.536 --> 00:33:52.976
cruelty.

cue-535
00:33:54.276 --> 00:33:59.016
Leaving that horrifying scene behind, we
noticed a crowd staring in another

cue-536
00:33:59.016 --> 00:33:59.496
direction.

cue-537
00:34:00.536 --> 00:34:05.196
Far off, a long line of men was marching
toward the market from Mbanza Makuta,

cue-538
00:34:05.196 --> 00:34:06.806
each carrying a gun.

cue-539
00:34:08.006 --> 00:34:09.436
"Isn't that against the law?"

cue-540
00:34:10.496 --> 00:34:11.715
some asked. "Yes,"

cue-541
00:34:12.636 --> 00:34:14.516
one replied, "but there's more to it.

cue-542
00:34:15.216 --> 00:34:19.616
I've heard there was a war at Makuta. A
white man came there months ago, then

cue-543
00:34:19.616 --> 00:34:20.356
tried to return.

cue-544
00:34:21.036 --> 00:34:22.776
Bwaka Matu wouldn't let him pass.

cue-545
00:34:23.396 --> 00:34:24.576
He drove him out and shot him."

cue-546
00:34:25.666 --> 00:34:27.346
"Is he dead?" another asked.

cue-547
00:34:28.166 --> 00:34:31.256
"I don't know," came the answer. "I hope
so."

cue-548
00:34:32.166 --> 00:34:33.596
"Was he one of the coastal traders?"

cue-549
00:34:34.386 --> 00:34:36.196
"No. They say he was a mundil,

cue-550
00:34:37.016 --> 00:34:37.655
a man of God,

cue-551
00:34:38.276 --> 00:34:38.816
a missionary."

cue-552
00:34:40.336 --> 00:34:42.175
Matula listened closely to these rumors.

cue-553
00:34:42.876 --> 00:34:46.936
Soon he heard the singer leading a
procession nearby and strained to catch

cue-554
00:34:46.936 --> 00:34:51.776
every word of the song that boasted how
the white man had been driven off and

cue-555
00:34:51.776 --> 00:34:53.296
shot by their mighty chief.

cue-556
00:34:54.136 --> 00:34:57.776
At last, the singer appeared, his forehead
and nose streaked with red.

cue-557
00:34:58.636 --> 00:35:03.416
Behind him came the chief, draped in a
long cloth and wearing a leopard-skin cap,

cue-558
00:35:04.096 --> 00:35:04.856
carrying a spear.

cue-559
00:35:05.896 --> 00:35:10.076
In single file, about a hundred warriors
followed, each with a gun or

cue-560
00:35:10.076 --> 00:35:11.976
spear. The singer began again.

cue-561
00:35:12.776 --> 00:35:15.536
"Great is our chief. Who can stand against
him?"

cue-562
00:35:16.936 --> 00:35:19.836
The chief paced before the crowd, showing
himself off,

cue-563
00:35:20.456 --> 00:35:22.076
kusonga, as Matula called it.

cue-564
00:35:22.756 --> 00:35:26.896
He challenged anyone who sided with the
white man and swore that no nunkwa malu

cue-565
00:35:26.896 --> 00:35:30.056
mole, trouser wearer, would ever enter his
land again.

cue-566
00:35:30.736 --> 00:35:31.876
Only he was chief.

cue-567
00:35:32.676 --> 00:35:37.516
The people abandoned their trading, joined
the song and dance, and declared, "Never

cue-568
00:35:37.516 --> 00:35:39.796
again shall a white man appear in our
country."

cue-569
00:35:40.816 --> 00:35:44.236
Some of the timid feared the white man
might return in force for revenge.

cue-570
00:35:44.916 --> 00:35:47.316
In truth, the chief had only wounded the
white man,

cue-571
00:35:47.936 --> 00:35:48.596
not killed him.

cue-572
00:35:49.376 --> 00:35:53.796
That man was Tom Comber, who with Hartland
had tried to build a road to Stanley

cue-573
00:35:53.796 --> 00:35:54.056
Pool.

cue-574
00:35:54.856 --> 00:35:59.216
Because of Bwaka Matu's stubbornness, the
road effort was abandoned for a time, and

cue-575
00:35:59.216 --> 00:36:01.116
Makuta stood alone for several years.

cue-576
00:36:01.976 --> 00:36:05.486
About seven or eight years later, Mr.
Bentley visited the town.

cue-577
00:36:06.156 --> 00:36:10.416
He has come twice a year on average ever
since, and his work has brought wonderful

cue-578
00:36:10.416 --> 00:36:14.096
results. Revenge was taken, but not by
sword.

cue-579
00:36:15.016 --> 00:36:18.916
Today, Makuta has one of the most thriving
sections of our native church.

cue-580
00:36:19.536 --> 00:36:24.520
Mr. Bentley describes this transformation
in his book.In August

cue-581
00:36:24.520 --> 00:36:29.460
1897, Nkonzi, nephew of Bwaka Matu, who
had ordered Komba shot,

cue-582
00:36:29.460 --> 00:36:30.680
was baptized.

cue-583
00:36:31.320 --> 00:36:35.480
A month or two later, he felt the need to
make amends for his family's great sin.

cue-584
00:36:36.110 --> 00:36:40.220
He wanted to send a gift to Komba's
father, but being far away, he could only

cue-585
00:36:40.220 --> 00:36:41.420
manage something small.

cue-586
00:36:42.300 --> 00:36:46.979
He wrote a letter expressing deep sorrow
for the wrong done to his son, who had

cue-587
00:36:46.980 --> 00:36:49.100
brought such good news from God.

cue-588
00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:54.480
He explained that his uncle Bwaka had
acted in ignorance and begged Komba's

cue-589
00:36:54.480 --> 00:36:56.620
father to forgive him and be his friend.

cue-590
00:36:57.500 --> 00:37:02.460
Nkonzi had come to know and trust Jesus
and was truly thankful that the gospel

cue-591
00:37:02.460 --> 00:37:07.360
had reached his people. This was God's
own vengeance, turning many of that

cue-592
00:37:07.360 --> 00:37:12.260
proud, wicked chief's relatives to faith.
Nkonzi himself, however, did not

cue-593
00:37:12.260 --> 00:37:13.940
live long after his misdeed.

cue-594
00:37:14.730 --> 00:37:19.340
But that is a brief aside. Returning to
Matula, this was the first time he had

cue-595
00:37:19.340 --> 00:37:22.760
ever heard of white men, so he listened
eagerly to every rumor.

cue-596
00:37:23.400 --> 00:37:27.340
He heard them called possessors of two
legs, as if other men had none.

cue-597
00:37:28.150 --> 00:37:31.919
The white men on the coast were traders,
but these two who came to Makuta were

cue-598
00:37:31.920 --> 00:37:32.380
different.

cue-599
00:37:33.060 --> 00:37:36.720
They gave away fine cloth and spoke of
Nzambi, our God,

cue-600
00:37:37.340 --> 00:37:38.520
and strange things like

cue-601
00:37:39.620 --> 00:37:39.920
love.

cue-602
00:37:41.020 --> 00:37:46.020
These Mundul, white men, were entirely
odd. They had no guns

cue-603
00:37:46.020 --> 00:37:48.220
and hadn't brought many carriers to force
a road.

cue-604
00:37:48.840 --> 00:37:53.720
No one knew who they really were or what
they wanted. Some believed their home lay

cue-605
00:37:53.720 --> 00:37:57.820
at the bottom of the sea. Perhaps they
were spirits of sold slaves come back to

cue-606
00:37:57.820 --> 00:37:58.220
haunt them.

cue-607
00:37:58.900 --> 00:38:03.480
In any case, they were said to be eaters
of men, carrying off as many as they could

cue-608
00:38:03.480 --> 00:38:05.070
to work in their strange land.

cue-609
00:38:05.770 --> 00:38:09.820
The only safe course was never to let them
return, and wherever their name was

cue-610
00:38:09.820 --> 00:38:11.840
heard, to avoid them as Ndoki,

cue-611
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:12.980
witches.

cue-612
00:38:13.920 --> 00:38:15.560
All of this terrified young Matula.

cue-613
00:38:16.250 --> 00:38:20.140
As he walked home from market that day
with his mother, he prayed he would never

cue-614
00:38:20.140 --> 00:38:21.920
meet a white man in his life.

cue-615
00:38:22.940 --> 00:38:26.460
Though he tried not to think of them by
day, he dreamed of them at night.

cue-616
00:38:27.120 --> 00:38:29.120
Sometimes in one form, sometimes another.

cue-617
00:38:29.820 --> 00:38:32.400
Always chasing him, never letting him
escape.

cue-618
00:38:33.160 --> 00:38:36.800
Yet he was destined to have much to do
with these very white men.

cue-619
00:38:37.640 --> 00:38:42.640
And, as dreams often turn out opposite to
reality, in later years Matula grew

cue-620
00:38:42.640 --> 00:38:47.040
to love white men dearly and was glad to
turn to them for help and protection.

cue-621
00:38:51.460 --> 00:38:53.240
Chapter 6. The White Man

cue-622
00:38:55.840 --> 00:38:59.820
Matula was determined to avoid contact
with white men as much as he

cue-623
00:38:59.820 --> 00:39:04.000
could. Over the next few years, he made
good progress as a trader.

cue-624
00:39:04.680 --> 00:39:09.020
Even though he was still young, people saw
him as very sharp, and he made money

cue-625
00:39:09.020 --> 00:39:09.320
quickly.

cue-626
00:39:10.020 --> 00:39:14.240
Before long, he helped his mother buy her
freedom, though the price was very high.

cue-627
00:39:15.160 --> 00:39:19.980
As he grew older, he went on longer and
longer trading trips into the countryside.

cue-628
00:39:19.980 --> 00:39:24.480
In early 1885, he joined a group
traveling to the north bank of the Congo

cue-629
00:39:24.480 --> 00:39:26.270
River, about 80 miles away.

cue-630
00:39:27.100 --> 00:39:31.320
On the way, they crossed the large road
built by Stanley from Manyanga to the

cue-631
00:39:31.320 --> 00:39:35.740
pool, which amazed them. On the other
side, they heard rumors about a railway

cue-632
00:39:35.740 --> 00:39:40.740
being built, but no one really knew what
it was or what it would do. Some in the

cue-633
00:39:40.740 --> 00:39:45.520
group had been to Boma and had seen the
big steamers there. People said, that's

cue-634
00:39:45.520 --> 00:39:45.880
the thing.

cue-635
00:39:46.610 --> 00:39:49.780
But they couldn't understand how those
steamers could ever travel over land.

cue-636
00:39:50.500 --> 00:39:51.520
It seemed like magic.

cue-637
00:39:52.700 --> 00:39:57.120
Still, they admitted that the white men
had a lot of ngangu, cleverness, and there

cue-638
00:39:57.120 --> 00:39:58.360
was no telling what they might do.

cue-639
00:39:59.240 --> 00:40:01.180
On the way back, they passed Ngombe,

cue-640
00:40:02.140 --> 00:40:06.240
Wathan, where a new station was being set
up, moved from Manyanga.

cue-641
00:40:06.980 --> 00:40:09.520
This was the first time Matula ever saw a
white man,

cue-642
00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:11.400
though only from a distance,

cue-643
00:40:12.140 --> 00:40:15.260
as they moved quickly through the area,
afraid of being cursed.

cue-644
00:40:16.080 --> 00:40:19.620
Yet Matula was very impressed with the
white man's ngangu.

cue-645
00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:25.020
He saw that the area around Ngombe was a
great place for trade, so he came back

cue-646
00:40:25.020 --> 00:40:28.360
often with sheep, goats, pigs, and other
goods,

cue-647
00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:32.620
though he stayed away from the station and
didn't go near it for about two more

cue-648
00:40:32.620 --> 00:40:37.600
years. Then he came to sell sheep at
Vunda, about two hours away, and stopped

cue-649
00:40:37.600 --> 00:40:38.660
by Nlemvo's place,

cue-650
00:40:39.260 --> 00:40:41.140
Mr. Bentley's assistant in translation.

cue-651
00:40:41.760 --> 00:40:46.100
To honor the visit, he killed a sheep and
gave the heart to Nlemvo as a sign of

cue-652
00:40:46.100 --> 00:40:46.620
friendship.

cue-653
00:40:47.420 --> 00:40:52.000
Not long before Nlemvo's own baptism, as a
committed follower of Christ, he spent a

cue-654
00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:53.480
lot of time talking to Matula.

cue-655
00:40:54.100 --> 00:40:58.720
But it was hard for Matula to believe that
the customs of his people were completely

cue-656
00:40:58.720 --> 00:41:01.550
wrong, or to stop being suspicious of the
white man.

cue-657
00:41:02.220 --> 00:41:06.540
In the morning, Nlemvo got Matula to join
him for prayers in a small grass prayer

cue-658
00:41:06.540 --> 00:41:06.940
house.

cue-659
00:41:07.700 --> 00:41:12.360
Everything felt strange to Matula. When
everyone closed their eyes to pray, he

cue-660
00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:16.580
kept his open, afraid something might be
done to him when he wasn't looking.

cue-661
00:41:17.360 --> 00:41:20.800
Still, the first seed had been planted and
the first step taken.

cue-662
00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:26.820
He went on to Vunda with his sheep, where
he met Mr. Cameron, who was visiting for

cue-663
00:41:26.820 --> 00:41:27.120
the day.

cue-664
00:41:27.980 --> 00:41:32.800
Matula was surprised at the white man's
ngemda, friendliness, toward the people.

cue-665
00:41:33.820 --> 00:41:38.220
They watched his every move, examined his
clothes and belongings, and were

cue-666
00:41:38.220 --> 00:41:42.040
especially fascinated by how his food was
prepared and the table set.

cue-667
00:41:42.740 --> 00:41:47.440
It was as if they had never seen anyone
eat before. They all crowded around to

cue-668
00:41:47.440 --> 00:41:48.880
watch him use a knife and fork.

cue-669
00:41:49.740 --> 00:41:53.380
When he gave out a few biscuits, which
were broken into pieces so everyone could

cue-670
00:41:53.380 --> 00:41:56.800
have some, they were overjoyed and burst
into laughter.

cue-671
00:41:57.620 --> 00:42:01.680
But when he started to talk about the one
in whose name he had come, it was like he

cue-672
00:42:01.680 --> 00:42:02.420
had a disease.

cue-673
00:42:03.100 --> 00:42:04.960
Everyone quickly went back to their
houses.

cue-674
00:42:05.760 --> 00:42:08.960
Still, Matula remembered his kind face and
smile,

cue-675
00:42:09.580 --> 00:42:11.680
and something began to grow in his heart.

cue-676
00:42:12.420 --> 00:42:14.800
He started to feel that the white man was
a friend.

cue-677
00:42:15.410 --> 00:42:19.090
The fear was gone, but most people still
rejected the new teaching,

cue-678
00:42:19.760 --> 00:42:22.020
and that held Matula back for several
years.

cue-679
00:42:23.380 --> 00:42:28.380
Soon after, Mr. Bentley began visiting the
Makuta district.After some time, the

cue-680
00:42:28.380 --> 00:42:33.180
people of Tungwa decided to give him a boy
to help him, which surprised and pleased

cue-681
00:42:33.180 --> 00:42:36.300
him. The chief said he would bring the boy
himself.

cue-682
00:42:37.040 --> 00:42:40.360
When Matula heard about this, he chose to
join them on a trading trip.

cue-683
00:42:41.200 --> 00:42:45.220
Everything went smoothly until they
reached Kinketa, about four or five hours

cue-684
00:42:45.220 --> 00:42:48.580
from Ningombe. As they entered the town in
single file,

cue-685
00:42:49.540 --> 00:42:50.720
Matula leading a sheep,

cue-686
00:42:51.420 --> 00:42:52.720
a man stepped out demanding,

cue-687
00:42:53.360 --> 00:42:54.060
"Pay the tax."

cue-688
00:42:55.080 --> 00:42:56.340
They ignored him and walked on.

cue-689
00:42:57.120 --> 00:42:59.319
Another man did the same, but they kept
going.

cue-690
00:43:00.080 --> 00:43:02.780
Farther ahead, they were stopped by a
group with guns.

cue-691
00:43:03.560 --> 00:43:08.550
Those in the back ran off. Matula was
caught and tied up, his sheep taken, and

cue-692
00:43:08.550 --> 00:43:13.280
he was fined five hundred brass rods to
let the others continue. They had no

cue-693
00:43:13.280 --> 00:43:17.680
choice but to pay. This happened just as
they were beginning to take interest in

cue-694
00:43:17.680 --> 00:43:22.020
the white man's teachings, making it
especially unfortunate. Thankfully, the

cue-695
00:43:22.020 --> 00:43:27.020
government later put an end to this
illegal taxation. In

cue-696
00:43:27.020 --> 00:43:31.720
1890 and 1891, Mr. Bentley passed through
Matula's

cue-697
00:43:31.720 --> 00:43:32.079
village,

cue-698
00:43:32.740 --> 00:43:37.740
but Matula was away both times. It wasn't
until 1894, after

cue-699
00:43:37.740 --> 00:43:41.500
Mr. Bentley returned from his time in
England, that they finally met again.

cue-700
00:43:42.280 --> 00:43:46.180
Matula was just setting out on another
trading journey when he met Mr. Bentley

cue-701
00:43:46.180 --> 00:43:47.280
heading toward Mongo.

cue-702
00:43:48.120 --> 00:43:51.680
Matula had a brother suffering from a
serious, long-lasting ulcer,

cue-703
00:43:52.360 --> 00:43:54.320
so he asked the missionary to come see
him.

cue-704
00:43:55.020 --> 00:43:59.300
Matula gave up his planned journey and ran
back home to tell his family that the

cue-705
00:43:59.300 --> 00:44:00.300
missionary was coming.

cue-706
00:44:00.980 --> 00:44:04.460
Then he went out to meet him and led him
into the heart of the town.

cue-707
00:44:05.160 --> 00:44:09.420
The missionary treated the ulcer, and
Matula was so pleased that he brought two

cue-708
00:44:09.420 --> 00:44:11.320
large chickens as a matabish,

cue-709
00:44:12.100 --> 00:44:12.380
gift.

cue-710
00:44:13.320 --> 00:44:18.310
But Mr. Bentley, from past experience, had
learned to refuse such gifts because

cue-711
00:44:18.310 --> 00:44:19.560
they often caused trouble.

cue-712
00:44:20.440 --> 00:44:24.420
Some people thought the missionary was
like the fetish doctors who charged far

cue-713
00:44:24.420 --> 00:44:28.120
too much, and others accused him of only
coming to take things without giving

cue-714
00:44:28.120 --> 00:44:29.040
enough in return.

cue-715
00:44:29.940 --> 00:44:34.560
So Mr. Bentley kindly declined the gift
and instead sat down to speak with the

cue-716
00:44:34.560 --> 00:44:36.400
people who seemed ready to listen.

cue-717
00:44:37.180 --> 00:44:41.820
Many had never heard the gospel before. He
told them about the God whose name they

cue-718
00:44:41.820 --> 00:44:46.609
knew, the one who made them and everything
else, who gave rain and sunshine to help

cue-719
00:44:46.609 --> 00:44:47.580
their food grow.

cue-720
00:44:48.440 --> 00:44:53.340
This God always cared for them, yet they
were ungrateful, and their

cue-721
00:44:53.340 --> 00:44:54.919
ways were wrong in his sight.

cue-722
00:44:55.680 --> 00:45:00.460
He spoke of God's love in sending Jesus to
save them from their sins and to give

cue-723
00:45:00.460 --> 00:45:05.460
them power to overcome evil and live holy
lives. He warned them of

cue-724
00:45:05.460 --> 00:45:09.620
the coming judgment when all their
actions would be brought to account, for

cue-725
00:45:09.620 --> 00:45:14.540
God sees everything. He urged them to turn
to Jesus, the only one

cue-726
00:45:14.540 --> 00:45:15.920
who could save them.

cue-727
00:45:17.140 --> 00:45:19.900
After he left, the people talked a lot
about what he said,

cue-728
00:45:20.560 --> 00:45:23.100
but their old ways and customs were
precious to them.

cue-729
00:45:23.740 --> 00:45:25.340
Why should they accept new teachings?

cue-730
00:45:26.020 --> 00:45:28.040
They said these new things were just
kindoki,

cue-731
00:45:28.920 --> 00:45:33.240
witchcraft, because their crops grew and
rain fell through the power of enkisi,

cue-732
00:45:34.280 --> 00:45:34.740
fetishes.

cue-733
00:45:35.760 --> 00:45:38.720
So they believed anything outside of
fetishism must be sorcery.

cue-734
00:45:39.500 --> 00:45:44.300
In their thinking, everything was either
witchcraft or fetishism and nothing else.

cue-735
00:45:44.300 --> 00:45:48.980
Yet one man in that crowd thought deeply
about what he had heard, and that man was

cue-736
00:45:48.980 --> 00:45:49.420
Matula.

cue-737
00:45:50.160 --> 00:45:51.860
This was another step forward for him.

cue-738
00:45:52.540 --> 00:45:56.340
He now believed that the white men were
not only friendly, but that what they

cue-739
00:45:56.340 --> 00:45:58.560
taught was good and worth remembering.

cue-740
00:45:59.440 --> 00:46:03.940
He looked for chances to learn more. He
visited Bukusu, who had recently come back

cue-741
00:46:03.940 --> 00:46:04.500
to Tungwa.

cue-742
00:46:05.220 --> 00:46:09.220
Matula became very interested in him,
looked through his books, and wished he

cue-743
00:46:09.220 --> 00:46:09.640
could read.

cue-744
00:46:10.480 --> 00:46:13.320
From then on, he made up his mind to have
his own boy taught.

cue-745
00:46:14.020 --> 00:46:18.419
When Matula returned, he told his friends
about his plan, but they were upset and

cue-746
00:46:18.420 --> 00:46:20.080
tried hard to change his mind.

cue-747
00:46:20.900 --> 00:46:25.320
Still, he made arrangements with two boys
to go with Mr. Bentley the next time he

cue-748
00:46:25.320 --> 00:46:25.720
visited.

cue-749
00:46:26.440 --> 00:46:30.420
However, Matula's mother found out and
secretly paid the boys to disappear as

cue-750
00:46:30.420 --> 00:46:35.139
soon as Mr. Bentley arrived and not to
come back until he had left. A few weeks

cue-751
00:46:35.140 --> 00:46:39.120
later, Mr. Bentley, remembering Matula's
interest, visited again.

cue-752
00:46:39.960 --> 00:46:42.080
Matula told him he had two boys ready.

cue-753
00:46:42.760 --> 00:46:47.060
Mr. Bentley stayed just one night, and in
the morning, Matula sent for the boys,

cue-754
00:46:47.760 --> 00:46:49.110
but they were nowhere to be found.

cue-755
00:46:49.880 --> 00:46:53.800
Realizing he had been tricked, he told Mr.
Bentley he would follow after him with at

cue-756
00:46:53.800 --> 00:46:58.620
least one boy. Messengers were sent out
to search, and finally one boy was

cue-757
00:46:58.620 --> 00:47:01.560
found just as Mr. Bentley was about to
leave the town.

cue-758
00:47:02.180 --> 00:47:06.760
He was a big, cheerful boy of about
thirteen, wearing a new singlet Matula had

cue-759
00:47:06.760 --> 00:47:08.940
given him and holding a rat in his hand.

cue-760
00:47:09.620 --> 00:47:10.740
His name was Mankwenya.

cue-761
00:47:11.420 --> 00:47:16.360
Matula told him he was going to become a
white black man, Mundele Anayombe,

cue-762
00:47:16.360 --> 00:47:20.960
like Bukusu, and promised to visit him,
bringing money and chickens. That was

cue-763
00:47:20.960 --> 00:47:22.320
enough to excite any boy.

cue-764
00:47:23.240 --> 00:47:27.860
With a bright smile, Mankwenya said,
"Kiyambote," goodbye, to everyone and

cue-765
00:47:27.860 --> 00:47:31.880
happily joined the small caravan on the
journey to Wathen, not worried at all

cue-766
00:47:31.880 --> 00:47:33.260
about witches or sorcery.

cue-767
00:47:35.680 --> 00:47:37.700
[upbeat music] Chapter Seven:

cue-768
00:47:38.300 --> 00:47:39.280
Matula's Conversion.

cue-769
00:47:41.360 --> 00:47:45.440
As soon as Mankwenya left Mongo, the
people began to turn against Matula.

cue-770
00:47:46.200 --> 00:47:50.480
They now saw clearly that he had broken
from their ways and joined the white man's

cue-771
00:47:50.480 --> 00:47:55.460
side. His mother cursed him and called
him a witch, so Matula stayed away from

cue-772
00:47:55.460 --> 00:47:58.060
home as much as he could, going on trading
trips.

cue-773
00:47:58.860 --> 00:48:03.320
He himself didn't fully understand the new
feelings stirring in his heart, but he

cue-774
00:48:03.320 --> 00:48:04.740
couldn't turn away from them.

cue-775
00:48:05.720 --> 00:48:10.180
Meanwhile, Mankwenya was doing fairly well
at school. He soon moved past learning

cue-776
00:48:10.180 --> 00:48:14.500
the alphabet and joined the syllable
class. He was a cheerful, laughing boy

cue-777
00:48:14.500 --> 00:48:18.520
with a good temper, and he quickly made
friends with everyone. He had arrived at

cue-778
00:48:18.520 --> 00:48:22.440
the mission station just a few months
before my own arrival, and I remember the

cue-779
00:48:22.440 --> 00:48:27.440
first time I saw him. He was wearing an
old, torn singlet, against the rules,

cue-780
00:48:27.440 --> 00:48:31.420
which he kept trying to pull back on. His
face was full of mischief and fun.

cue-781
00:48:32.100 --> 00:48:36.284
Watching him run with the other boys was
something to see.Because he was so fat and

cue-782
00:48:36.284 --> 00:48:38.844
flat-footed, he was always the one left
behind.

cue-783
00:48:39.584 --> 00:48:43.664
It was a real loss to the station when a
few months later, he went back to his town

cue-784
00:48:43.664 --> 00:48:47.354
with Mr. Bentley and never returned. We
were all quite sorry,

cue-785
00:48:47.984 --> 00:48:52.824
as we had grown fond of him. He was easily
influenced. Just as he had happily gone

cue-786
00:48:52.824 --> 00:48:57.584
to the station, drawn by Matula's promises
of gifts, he stayed behind in his

cue-787
00:48:57.584 --> 00:49:00.564
village when his mother tempted him with
her best dishes.

cue-788
00:49:01.324 --> 00:49:05.944
He listened eagerly to her story, how she
had been mourning for him, afraid he had

cue-789
00:49:05.944 --> 00:49:09.904
been eaten, and how sure she was that he
would be eaten if he went back.

cue-790
00:49:11.024 --> 00:49:13.584
He didn't really believe her story about
being eaten,

cue-791
00:49:14.264 --> 00:49:16.124
but he didn't like to see anyone sad.

cue-792
00:49:17.024 --> 00:49:21.924
Her tears and pleas convinced him to stay
and not meet Mr. Bentley as planned.

cue-793
00:49:23.224 --> 00:49:25.874
From our limited view, it seemed like a
disappointment,

cue-794
00:49:26.624 --> 00:49:31.344
but in truth, it was something to be
thankful for. Matula didn't have the heart

cue-795
00:49:31.344 --> 00:49:32.234
to fight his aunt

cue-796
00:49:32.924 --> 00:49:35.084
a second time about Mankwenya,

cue-797
00:49:36.144 --> 00:49:40.304
but he still deeply wanted to know all
that the boy had learned at Ngombe.

cue-798
00:49:41.284 --> 00:49:44.144
The two of them often sat together,
talking for hours.

cue-799
00:49:45.264 --> 00:49:50.024
Mankwenya did his best to tell Matula
about the great God he had heard of and

cue-800
00:49:50.024 --> 00:49:51.924
about Jesus Christ, his Son.

cue-801
00:49:53.154 --> 00:49:55.504
Matula tried hard to take in every word.

cue-802
00:49:56.224 --> 00:50:00.964
Then, wherever Matula went, he would tell
others about the strange and wonderful

cue-803
00:50:00.964 --> 00:50:02.684
things Mankwenya had shared with him.

cue-804
00:50:03.424 --> 00:50:05.604
Matula often saw the boy studying his

cue-805
00:50:06.564 --> 00:50:07.364
Mwelo Wazi,

cue-806
00:50:08.064 --> 00:50:10.144
Gate of Knowledge, the first Congo reading
book,

cue-807
00:50:10.744 --> 00:50:12.104
and he would sit next to him to learn.

cue-808
00:50:12.964 --> 00:50:15.544
They agreed to hold their own little
school each day.

cue-809
00:50:16.364 --> 00:50:17.304
Poor Mankwenya.

cue-810
00:50:17.944 --> 00:50:19.364
This was not easy for him.

cue-811
00:50:20.064 --> 00:50:24.104
In his cheerful and easygoing way, he had
forgotten some of the letters, so it was

cue-812
00:50:24.104 --> 00:50:28.904
no surprise when P turned into B or D, and
M looked like

cue-813
00:50:28.904 --> 00:50:31.124
W or N like U.

cue-814
00:50:32.424 --> 00:50:34.604
Somehow even F got mixed up with T,

cue-815
00:50:35.484 --> 00:50:36.964
so they didn't make much progress,

cue-816
00:50:37.744 --> 00:50:39.584
but Matula felt they were moving forward.

cue-817
00:50:41.464 --> 00:50:45.084
In the evenings, Matula would gather
everyone who was willing to come and sing

cue-818
00:50:45.084 --> 00:50:45.423
together.

cue-819
00:50:46.144 --> 00:50:51.123
Mankwenya taught them the simple songs he
had learned, like Jesus Loves Me

cue-820
00:50:51.124 --> 00:50:53.344
or Follow, Follow, I Will Follow Jesus.

cue-821
00:50:54.484 --> 00:50:57.744
Matula later said he couldn't guarantee
they sang correctly,

cue-822
00:50:58.364 --> 00:51:00.444
but he was sure they sang with all their
hearts.

cue-823
00:51:01.064 --> 00:51:04.924
He would walk about a mile in different
directions to hear if their singing

cue-824
00:51:04.924 --> 00:51:06.304
carried through the evening air.

cue-825
00:51:07.064 --> 00:51:09.324
If he couldn't hear it well, he would come
back and say,

cue-826
00:51:09.324 --> 00:51:11.504
Shout louder. Raise your voices.

cue-827
00:51:12.764 --> 00:51:15.324
If he could hear it clearly, he'd return
and say,

cue-828
00:51:15.324 --> 00:51:16.684
Wambote Kikilu,

cue-829
00:51:17.464 --> 00:51:20.504
-it is very good.
-And then they would sing it all over

cue-830
00:51:20.504 --> 00:51:20.764
again.

cue-831
00:51:21.484 --> 00:51:25.784
Is there any more touching picture than
this group of souls just stepping out of

cue-832
00:51:25.784 --> 00:51:27.804
darkness into the first light of dawn?

cue-833
00:51:28.544 --> 00:51:32.364
None of them truly understood the meaning
of the beautiful hymn they sang to the

cue-834
00:51:32.364 --> 00:51:36.164
-tune of Jesus Loves Me.
-Jizu ntu zole.

cue-835
00:51:37.004 --> 00:51:42.004
Nkand a nzambi nvovole wo. Yeto awonso

cue-836
00:51:42.004 --> 00:51:44.724
tu anandi. Okutulundanga.

cue-837
00:51:45.404 --> 00:51:50.384
Jizu ntu zolele bia. Elo ntu zolele. Jizu
ntu

cue-838
00:51:50.384 --> 00:51:54.493
-zolele. Oyandi nkundi eto.
-Translation.

cue-839
00:51:55.184 --> 00:51:56.764
Jesus, he is loving us.

cue-840
00:51:57.584 --> 00:52:02.384
The book of God has told us this. Truly we
his people are. He

cue-841
00:52:02.384 --> 00:52:03.844
keeps us with great care.

cue-842
00:52:04.744 --> 00:52:09.704
Jesus, he is loving us. Yes, he is loving
us. Jesus,

cue-843
00:52:09.704 --> 00:52:10.564
he is loving us.

cue-844
00:52:11.164 --> 00:52:12.604
Our only friend is he.

cue-845
00:52:14.864 --> 00:52:19.164
Everywhere Matula and his wife went, they
sang these simple hymns and shared with

cue-846
00:52:19.164 --> 00:52:20.504
the people what they were learning.

cue-847
00:52:21.304 --> 00:52:25.424
For a time, Matula stopped going on
trading trips so he could fully give

cue-848
00:52:25.424 --> 00:52:27.224
himself to these new experiences.

cue-849
00:52:27.924 --> 00:52:32.184
It's hard to say exactly when the
spiritual awakening of a soul truly

cue-850
00:52:32.184 --> 00:52:35.424
begins. Matula himself wasn't sure when it
happened,

cue-851
00:52:36.124 --> 00:52:40.164
but it was clear that God had started a
work of grace in his heart.

cue-852
00:52:41.464 --> 00:52:46.104
Around that time, the chief of Makuta,
where Ponda had recently begun to teach,

cue-853
00:52:46.104 --> 00:52:50.684
came to visit Mongo. He told Matula how he
had started learning to read,

cue-854
00:52:50.684 --> 00:52:53.394
ABD, since the Congo language has no C.

cue-855
00:52:54.144 --> 00:52:57.744
But he found that it led to more than just
reading. It brought him to the New

cue-856
00:52:57.744 --> 00:53:02.423
Testament, Ekangu Diampa, which spoke
against drunkenness, adultery,

cue-857
00:53:02.424 --> 00:53:04.464
lying, murder, and so on.

cue-858
00:53:05.744 --> 00:53:09.064
Since he didn't want to give up these
things, he stopped learning and turned

cue-859
00:53:09.064 --> 00:53:10.114
away from Christianity.

cue-860
00:53:10.934 --> 00:53:15.804
Matula was still unsure about many things.
He didn't yet understand it all, but was

cue-861
00:53:15.804 --> 00:53:17.844
trying to follow the little light he had.

cue-862
00:53:18.644 --> 00:53:22.704
He knew that things like murder and
adultery were against God's teaching. He

cue-863
00:53:22.704 --> 00:53:27.384
had even hated murder before ever hearing
about God. But he didn't yet realize that

cue-864
00:53:27.384 --> 00:53:32.364
drunkenness also displeased God. So in
trying to encourage the chief of

cue-865
00:53:32.364 --> 00:53:34.844
Makuta to keep learning and attending
prayers,

cue-866
00:53:35.464 --> 00:53:40.144
Matula told him that he could still read
and pray while drinking all the palm wine

cue-867
00:53:40.144 --> 00:53:40.744
he liked.

cue-868
00:53:41.724 --> 00:53:42.764
The chief agreed, saying,

cue-869
00:53:43.744 --> 00:53:45.904
All right, let's at least have some palm
wine.

cue-870
00:53:46.884 --> 00:53:49.864
A calabash was brought, and both of them
drank quite a bit.

cue-871
00:53:50.714 --> 00:53:52.194
Then Matula began to sing,

cue-872
00:53:52.824 --> 00:53:56.844
not with the filthy songs of drunkenness,
but with the beautiful words of Tom

cue-873
00:53:56.844 --> 00:54:01.364
Comber's hymn, set to the tune of Lord, a
Little Band and Lowly.

cue-874
00:54:02.084 --> 00:54:02.504
Rousseau.

cue-875
00:54:03.384 --> 00:54:04.664
Nzambi seto no

cue-876
00:54:05.584 --> 00:54:10.504
kwa ankenda no matale nsi zero konso nsi
kwa

cue-877
00:54:10.504 --> 00:54:15.164
nsoki yasibma tombe kingi kiabukowa.
Nzambi

cue-878
00:54:15.164 --> 00:54:19.844
seseto u nkwa ankenda toma tale nsi zeto.

cue-879
00:54:19.844 --> 00:54:20.954
Translation.

cue-880
00:54:21.844 --> 00:54:26.784
God our Father, full of kindness, look
upon our country, every land which

cue-881
00:54:26.784 --> 00:54:31.744
sin has cursed, and where deep darkness
still remains. God our Father,

cue-882
00:54:31.744 --> 00:54:34.384
full of kindness, look upon our country.

cue-883
00:54:35.244 --> 00:54:39.304
People thought Matula had gone mad. Who
had ever heard of a drunk man singing

cue-884
00:54:39.304 --> 00:54:44.088
hymns?His name spread across the region,
and many came from far away

cue-885
00:54:44.088 --> 00:54:44.888
just to see him.

cue-886
00:54:45.648 --> 00:54:50.088
Eventually, he came to understand that
drunkenness was shameful and a serious sin

cue-887
00:54:50.088 --> 00:54:53.148
before God, and he gave up drinking palm
wine.

cue-888
00:54:53.808 --> 00:54:58.608
In this country, as in others, drunkenness
is a deep curse, but nearly every

cue-889
00:54:58.608 --> 00:55:01.368
Christian on the Congo is a total
abstainer.

cue-890
00:55:02.248 --> 00:55:05.318
Matula was slowly growing under the
guidance of the Holy Spirit,

cue-891
00:55:05.928 --> 00:55:08.748
but the devil doesn't give up his servants
without a fight.

cue-892
00:55:09.428 --> 00:55:13.027
He followed Matula closely and seemed to
win when Matula got drunk.

cue-893
00:55:13.788 --> 00:55:17.808
But what must he have thought when that
same drunk man began singing a prayer to

cue-894
00:55:17.808 --> 00:55:18.518
God the Father?

cue-895
00:55:19.268 --> 00:55:23.728
Still, Satan believed he could win another
way. If he couldn't drag Matula down

cue-896
00:55:23.728 --> 00:55:27.768
through drunkenness, he would use pride,
the greatest snare for many.

cue-897
00:55:28.428 --> 00:55:32.408
Matula was becoming well known, and
stories of his actions spread through

cue-898
00:55:32.408 --> 00:55:36.048
every town and market. Who could resist
such fame?

cue-899
00:55:36.748 --> 00:55:40.217
But thank God, the devil does not win
every battle for the soul.

cue-900
00:55:41.008 --> 00:55:45.888
The Holy Spirit had begun a great work in
Matula's heart, and it would not fail.

cue-901
00:55:46.728 --> 00:55:50.728
To rescue Matula from his rising pride,
something too subtle for him to handle

cue-902
00:55:50.728 --> 00:55:52.708
alone, he had to be brought low.

cue-903
00:55:53.508 --> 00:55:56.668
For a while, it looked as though he had
completely given up his faith,

cue-904
00:55:57.368 --> 00:55:58.188
and so it happened.

cue-905
00:55:59.008 --> 00:56:03.188
Not long after the visit from the Makuta
chief, Matula's mother became very sick.

cue-906
00:56:03.848 --> 00:56:08.588
A deep darkness came over him. The old
superstitions he had been shedding now

cue-907
00:56:08.588 --> 00:56:12.168
clung to him more tightly than ever,
trying to hold him back.

cue-908
00:56:13.148 --> 00:56:14.848
People said his mother had been bewitched.

cue-909
00:56:15.708 --> 00:56:20.378
Matula became convinced that Manquenha was
the one who had done it. After all, he

cue-910
00:56:20.378 --> 00:56:23.628
had brought these new teachings, which
many said were witchcraft.

cue-911
00:56:24.468 --> 00:56:25.688
It was a terrible moment.

cue-912
00:56:26.388 --> 00:56:30.568
Matula gathered the people and declared
that he believed the boy was a witch.

cue-913
00:56:31.348 --> 00:56:36.308
He ordered the women not to go to the
market and forbade both them and Manquenha

cue-914
00:56:36.308 --> 00:56:38.448
from leaving the village while his mother
was ill.

cue-915
00:56:39.308 --> 00:56:44.148
And Matula, who once hated the crime of
killing someone accused of witchcraft, now

cue-916
00:56:44.148 --> 00:56:45.608
made a horrifying threat.

cue-917
00:56:46.348 --> 00:56:51.088
If his mother died, Manquenha would be
killed too. He commanded the boy to stop

cue-918
00:56:51.088 --> 00:56:54.888
singing, stop teaching, and never again
speak about God's words.

cue-919
00:56:55.748 --> 00:57:00.168
Many people supported him, glad to see
Matula returning, indeed going even

cue-920
00:57:00.168 --> 00:57:00.508
further,

cue-921
00:57:01.228 --> 00:57:02.868
into his old heathen ways.

cue-922
00:57:04.848 --> 00:57:09.468
For several days, there was deep anxiety.
It seemed as though the devil might truly

cue-923
00:57:09.468 --> 00:57:09.708
win.

cue-924
00:57:10.798 --> 00:57:13.198
Matula's mother hovered between life and
death,

cue-925
00:57:13.888 --> 00:57:18.608
but slowly she began to recover. This, for
a time, made

cue-926
00:57:18.608 --> 00:57:20.628
Matula more confident in the old ways.

cue-927
00:57:21.248 --> 00:57:26.008
Yet it was surely God's hand that kept him
from shedding blood, so that later, when

cue-928
00:57:26.008 --> 00:57:30.128
he would face accusations, he could
truthfully say he had never murdered or

cue-929
00:57:30.128 --> 00:57:31.688
even helped to kill anyone.

cue-930
00:57:32.608 --> 00:57:36.968
In the months that followed, Matula
slipped back into his old ways. He stopped

cue-931
00:57:36.968 --> 00:57:41.668
trying to learn, stopped singing, and
tried to forget about God entirely.

cue-932
00:57:42.568 --> 00:57:46.868
To distract himself, he turned heavily to
slave dealing and resumed his former

cue-933
00:57:46.868 --> 00:57:51.768
trading habits. He filled his time with
markets and the routines of his past,

cue-934
00:57:51.768 --> 00:57:53.847
trying to silence the voice of conscience.

cue-935
00:57:55.008 --> 00:57:56.968
One day, his trading brought him to
Makuta.

cue-936
00:57:57.738 --> 00:58:02.148
The chief there welcomed him warmly and
praised him for giving up God's palaver.

cue-937
00:58:03.028 --> 00:58:06.888
For the next few days, they threw
themselves into enjoying native life.

cue-938
00:58:07.668 --> 00:58:12.288
His wife, Kento, came with him. She was,
without doubt, one of the most faithful

cue-939
00:58:12.288 --> 00:58:14.528
and devoted women among the Congo people.

cue-940
00:58:15.328 --> 00:58:19.168
The evening before they left, they heard
singing from the prayer group led by

cue-941
00:58:19.168 --> 00:58:19.548
Ponde.

cue-942
00:58:20.168 --> 00:58:21.888
They were drawn to it and went to listen.

cue-943
00:58:22.728 --> 00:58:25.208
As they sat there, they were both deeply
convicted.

cue-944
00:58:25.868 --> 00:58:29.968
God's Spirit stirred their hearts. They
wept bitterly as they remembered how they

cue-945
00:58:29.968 --> 00:58:34.968
had once sung those very hymns with joy
and how happy they had been. That

cue-946
00:58:34.968 --> 00:58:38.888
memory moved them to a firm decision. They
would seek these things again

cue-947
00:58:39.548 --> 00:58:40.348
and nothing else.

cue-948
00:58:41.648 --> 00:58:45.868
Matula's first step was to make peace with
Ponde. In that culture, this was a

cue-949
00:58:45.868 --> 00:58:49.088
significant event, almost like a formal
engagement.

cue-950
00:58:49.748 --> 00:58:54.708
Matula invited Ponde to visit his town,
and Ponde gladly accepted, soon arriving

cue-951
00:58:54.708 --> 00:58:59.608
in Mongo. Matula was overjoyed. To honor
the occasion and confirm their

cue-952
00:58:59.608 --> 00:59:04.348
friendship, he prepared a generous meal
with various foods and even boiled two

cue-953
00:59:04.348 --> 00:59:04.768
chickens,

cue-954
00:59:05.408 --> 00:59:10.388
a costly gesture. He also brought a large
sheep as a gift for Ponde, though Ponde

cue-955
00:59:10.388 --> 00:59:13.048
wisely refused it to avoid gossip about
greed.

cue-956
00:59:13.808 --> 00:59:18.788
This friendship between Matula and Ponde
became deep and lasting until Ponde's

cue-957
00:59:18.788 --> 00:59:22.568
death in 1898, a story told by Meister
Bentley.

cue-958
00:59:23.408 --> 00:59:27.768
After the meal, Matula gathered the people
again, saying he wanted to restart the

cue-959
00:59:27.768 --> 00:59:30.268
teaching and singing now that Ponde was
with them.

cue-960
00:59:31.128 --> 00:59:34.408
Many came to meet him, someone they had
known since childhood.

cue-961
00:59:35.028 --> 00:59:37.028
Then followed a wonderful time of singing.

cue-962
00:59:37.948 --> 00:59:42.508
-Matula later said,
-We only knew one or two hymns, but Ponde

cue-963
00:59:42.508 --> 00:59:43.388
knew so many.

cue-964
00:59:44.488 --> 00:59:48.068
Manquenha helped where he could, and the
rest just did their best,

cue-965
00:59:48.688 --> 00:59:51.008
opening their mouths and copying the
sounds.

cue-966
00:59:51.808 --> 00:59:53.028
What a sight it must have been,

cue-967
00:59:53.628 --> 00:59:58.608
perhaps more pleasing to God than many
grand choirs dressed in fine clothes and

cue-968
00:59:58.608 --> 00:59:59.948
singing polished music.

cue-969
01:00:00.928 --> 01:00:04.908
For in that little group, there were
hearts stirred and lives awakened.

cue-970
01:00:05.588 --> 01:00:08.648
They sang not for the music, but for what
the songs meant.

cue-971
01:00:09.668 --> 01:00:14.548
From time to time, Ponde paused to explain
the words of the hymns. Then he

cue-972
01:00:14.548 --> 01:00:18.888
shared the story of his own conversion and
how he had come to trust in Jesus.

cue-973
01:00:19.908 --> 01:00:21.628
What a change it brings to life.

cue-974
01:00:22.828 --> 01:00:27.248
Ponde spoke from personal experience, how
the message of Christ could turn a sullen

cue-975
01:00:27.248 --> 01:00:31.208
man into someone kind and a quick-tempered
man into one who is gentle.

cue-976
01:00:32.048 --> 01:00:34.308
This went far deeper than Matula had
imagined.

cue-977
01:00:34.988 --> 01:00:38.988
He had understood that Christianity must
stop outward, obvious sins,

cue-978
01:00:39.588 --> 01:00:43.468
but he hadn't thought of the everyday
faults, the quiet habits and inner

cue-979
01:00:43.468 --> 01:00:45.128
struggles common to every person,

cue-980
01:00:45.788 --> 01:00:50.636
as sins too, let alone that they should be
changed.He listened eagerly.

cue-981
01:00:51.356 --> 01:00:52.856
He was learning more about Christ.

cue-982
01:00:53.536 --> 01:00:55.956
Not only that Jesus saves from the
punishment of sin,

cue-983
01:00:56.616 --> 01:00:58.416
but that he also frees from its power.

cue-984
01:00:59.416 --> 01:01:03.016
Here before him stood someone he had known
since childhood,

cue-985
01:01:03.656 --> 01:01:06.496
and now that man's life was completely
transformed.

cue-986
01:01:07.576 --> 01:01:09.196
Matula was deeply impressed.

cue-987
01:01:09.866 --> 01:01:13.536
Though his own pride was starting to be
humbled, he still struggled with fierce

cue-988
01:01:13.536 --> 01:01:18.456
bursts of anger, a weakness that would
later bring him pain. But those

cue-989
01:01:18.456 --> 01:01:23.236
days, which Matula now remembers with joy,
were days of peace before a coming

cue-990
01:01:23.236 --> 01:01:23.656
storm.

cue-991
01:01:24.556 --> 01:01:29.506
In that time, he learned much about God's
power, and a simple, firm faith was

cue-992
01:01:29.506 --> 01:01:32.256
planted in him, a faith he has never lost.

cue-993
01:01:33.036 --> 01:01:37.456
Even in his hardest trials, he could
always say with strong and sincere

cue-994
01:01:37.456 --> 01:01:38.056
conviction...

cue-995
01:01:38.826 --> 01:01:40.796
"God, my Father, knows."

cue-996
01:01:45.116 --> 01:01:47.276
Chapter Eight: Troubles and Trials.

cue-997
01:01:49.656 --> 01:01:53.976
Funerals in Congo are usually carried out
according to the customs of each town or

cue-998
01:01:53.976 --> 01:01:54.455
district.

cue-999
01:01:55.096 --> 01:01:59.096
Still, there are some common features,
especially when someone important dies.

cue-1000
01:01:59.736 --> 01:02:04.436
The body is often smoked for several days
over a small fire, then wrapped in cloth,

cue-1001
01:02:05.156 --> 01:02:06.736
sometimes only one or two pieces.

cue-1002
01:02:07.536 --> 01:02:11.776
In this state, the body might be kept for
weeks, months, or even years.

cue-1003
01:02:12.616 --> 01:02:16.896
This gives time for friends and relatives
to compete in bringing the largest gifts

cue-1004
01:02:16.896 --> 01:02:21.616
or the most cloth for wrapping the body
before burial. For great chiefs, gunshots

cue-1005
01:02:21.616 --> 01:02:26.436
are fired, drums and horns are played
almost non-stop, and the whole town

cue-1006
01:02:26.436 --> 01:02:31.276
takes part in a feast. On the day of
burial, people come from all around. The

cue-1007
01:02:31.276 --> 01:02:35.696
body, wrapped in many layers of cloth, is
buried along with nearly all the

cue-1008
01:02:35.696 --> 01:02:37.556
possessions the person had in life.

cue-1009
01:02:38.616 --> 01:02:43.476
Two or three years ago, the great chief of
this area died. While his body lay in

cue-1010
01:02:43.476 --> 01:02:48.036
state, between fifty to one hundred goats
were killed, along with many chickens.

cue-1011
01:02:48.036 --> 01:02:52.896
Around five hundred small kegs of
gunpowder were fired. His body was wrapped

cue-1012
01:02:52.896 --> 01:02:57.856
until it was the size of a dining table.
About two hundred pieces of cloth, equal

cue-1013
01:02:57.856 --> 01:03:02.656
to one thousand six hundred yards, were
buried with him, along with several heavy

cue-1014
01:03:02.656 --> 01:03:06.416
ivory tusks and expensive leopard and wild
animal skins.

cue-1015
01:03:07.216 --> 01:03:11.786
Every man hopes his funeral will be so
extravagant that people will talk about

cue-1016
01:03:11.786 --> 01:03:13.086
the amount of wealth used,

cue-1017
01:03:13.716 --> 01:03:18.015
and many begin saving for it from
childhood. On the day of the funeral,

cue-1018
01:03:18.016 --> 01:03:18.776
during the feasting,

cue-1019
01:03:19.576 --> 01:03:22.536
fights often break out, and knives are
sometimes drawn.

cue-1020
01:03:23.296 --> 01:03:27.376
In this, they're not far behind the native
Irish in knowing how to hold a dramatic

cue-1021
01:03:27.376 --> 01:03:27.716
wake.

cue-1022
01:03:28.536 --> 01:03:32.256
Just a few days after the events of the
previous chapter, one of the mothers of

cue-1023
01:03:32.256 --> 01:03:34.616
Matula's second wife died at Nzundu.

cue-1024
01:03:35.476 --> 01:03:40.136
Matula went to show respect. He brought
generous gifts and several pieces of cloth

cue-1025
01:03:40.136 --> 01:03:41.236
and stayed for the burial.

cue-1026
01:03:41.956 --> 01:03:46.556
The people were surprised that he wouldn't
drink palm wine, a habit he had given up

cue-1027
01:03:46.556 --> 01:03:48.196
after becoming friends with Ponda.

cue-1028
01:03:48.876 --> 01:03:53.516
He explained the change in his heart and
how much better it was to follow God and

cue-1029
01:03:53.516 --> 01:03:55.116
leave the old ways behind.

cue-1030
01:03:56.096 --> 01:03:57.836
But the people didn't listen closely.

cue-1031
01:03:58.596 --> 01:04:00.196
They were sure something was wrong with
him.

cue-1032
01:04:01.316 --> 01:04:03.056
Still, they didn't forget his words

cue-1033
01:04:03.776 --> 01:04:05.836
and would remember them later to use
against him.

cue-1034
01:04:06.676 --> 01:04:10.916
The day after the burial, Matula was on
his way back to Mongo and stopped at a

cue-1035
01:04:10.916 --> 01:04:11.966
market along the road.

cue-1036
01:04:12.796 --> 01:04:17.056
While he waited, a drunk man from Nzundu
approached him and asked for a piece of

cue-1037
01:04:17.056 --> 01:04:21.596
cloth. Matula refused, knowing that if he
gave in, all his

cue-1038
01:04:21.596 --> 01:04:26.156
possessions would soon be taken by lazy
relatives. But the man had been

cue-1039
01:04:26.156 --> 01:04:27.836
encouraged to provoke Matula.

cue-1040
01:04:28.586 --> 01:04:32.616
He followed him home, and after some
insistence, Matula gave him just enough

cue-1041
01:04:32.616 --> 01:04:33.836
cloth to cover himself.

cue-1042
01:04:34.596 --> 01:04:38.916
Instead of being grateful, the man
insulted Matula, calling him stingy and

cue-1043
01:04:38.916 --> 01:04:43.856
accusing him of using the new god's
palavers to bewitch people and get rich.

cue-1044
01:04:43.856 --> 01:04:47.216
His anger boiled over, and he struck
Matula on the head with a stick.

cue-1045
01:04:47.956 --> 01:04:52.855
Caught off guard and overcome with rage,
Matula rushed inside, grabbed his gun,

cue-1046
01:04:52.856 --> 01:04:53.716
and fired at the man,

cue-1047
01:04:54.376 --> 01:04:59.176
but missed. He immediately regretted it.
The man fled, yelling to his

cue-1048
01:04:59.176 --> 01:05:03.496
people that Matula had shot him. He said
nothing about the provocation. This was

cue-1049
01:05:03.496 --> 01:05:08.256
enough to stir the whole town to fury.
Armed with guns, they stormed over to

cue-1050
01:05:08.256 --> 01:05:08.596
Mongo.

cue-1051
01:05:09.205 --> 01:05:13.636
As the women fled into the forest and only
a few men remained, Matula tried to

cue-1052
01:05:13.636 --> 01:05:16.836
resolve the situation by talking and
offering to pay a fine,

cue-1053
01:05:17.876 --> 01:05:19.036
but they refused to listen.

cue-1054
01:05:20.026 --> 01:05:24.756
They captured him and locked him in a
house, planning to kill him that evening.

cue-1055
01:05:24.756 --> 01:05:29.336
They believed the house was secure. It
didn't have the usual second exit and sat

cue-1056
01:05:29.336 --> 01:05:30.076
down to watch.

cue-1057
01:05:31.316 --> 01:05:35.936
Matula prayed desperately, comforting
himself with the words, "God knows."

cue-1058
01:05:37.076 --> 01:05:40.976
Searching for a way out, he noticed a
corner of the gable end that wasn't

cue-1059
01:05:40.976 --> 01:05:41.816
tightly bound.

cue-1060
01:05:42.956 --> 01:05:46.996
Quietly lifting one of the small cross
rods and parting the grass, he slipped

cue-1061
01:05:46.996 --> 01:05:49.076
through into the thick woods behind the
house.

cue-1062
01:05:49.756 --> 01:05:53.856
There, he found a small trail leading to a
river. He walked in the water to avoid

cue-1063
01:05:53.856 --> 01:05:54.716
leaving footprints.

cue-1064
01:05:55.556 --> 01:05:59.416
Soon after, his captors checked the house
and were stunned to find it empty.

cue-1065
01:06:00.136 --> 01:06:01.516
"He must have used witchcraft,"

cue-1066
01:06:02.356 --> 01:06:04.336
they exclaimed. "What a witch he is."

cue-1067
01:06:05.016 --> 01:06:08.536
They believed he had been too scared to
run, as many had been before.

cue-1068
01:06:09.336 --> 01:06:09.965
They called out,

cue-1069
01:06:10.576 --> 01:06:11.356
but no one answered.

cue-1070
01:06:12.046 --> 01:06:15.956
Then they looted everything they could
find and searched for the women.

cue-1071
01:06:15.956 --> 01:06:19.736
Eventually, they found Maluvunu, Matula's
sister, and took her with them.

cue-1072
01:06:20.536 --> 01:06:25.196
When they reached Nzundu, they fired guns
and wasted powder to celebrate her capture

cue-1073
01:06:25.196 --> 01:06:28.256
and stir courage for a planned attack on
Mongo the next day.

cue-1074
01:06:28.936 --> 01:06:31.336
They expected Matula's friends would try
to rescue her.

cue-1075
01:06:32.056 --> 01:06:34.336
Meanwhile, Matula remained in hiding.

cue-1076
01:06:35.116 --> 01:06:36.356
He barely slept that night.

cue-1077
01:06:37.016 --> 01:06:40.536
When he heard the gunfire from Nzundu, he
guessed they had returned,

cue-1078
01:06:41.156 --> 01:06:45.556
but he could only wonder what they had
done to his town. The next morning, as

cue-1079
01:06:45.556 --> 01:06:49.876
Matula cautiously made his way back toward
Mongo, he spotted the Nzundu people

cue-1080
01:06:49.876 --> 01:06:51.176
marching toward his town.

cue-1081
01:06:51.836 --> 01:06:55.816
-He boldly called out...
-"Wait for me, and I will go along with

cue-1082
01:06:55.856 --> 01:06:55.976
you."

cue-1083
01:06:56.972 --> 01:07:01.612
Hearing Matula's voice suddenly and not
seeing him, they were seized with panic.

cue-1084
01:07:02.512 --> 01:07:06.192
In fear and confusion, they all turned and
fled back to Nzundu.

cue-1085
01:07:07.072 --> 01:07:07.792
Once they were gone,

cue-1086
01:07:08.432 --> 01:07:10.912
Matula rose from hiding and continued his
journey.

cue-1087
01:07:11.532 --> 01:07:15.932
As he neared Mongo, he met his relatives
armed and ready to march, determined to

cue-1088
01:07:15.932 --> 01:07:18.732
rescue Malovunu and avenge the attack on
Matula.

cue-1089
01:07:19.532 --> 01:07:23.452
He tried to stop them, urging peace and
saying it was wrong to fight.

cue-1090
01:07:24.532 --> 01:07:27.072
He encouraged them to find another way to
settle the conflict,

cue-1091
01:07:27.712 --> 01:07:30.212
but they wouldn't listen and went on
without him.

cue-1092
01:07:31.312 --> 01:07:36.312
Warfare in Congo tends to be more dramatic
than deadly. A simple rain shower

cue-1093
01:07:36.312 --> 01:07:41.052
can delay a battle indefinitely. What
they truly seek is noise. If enough

cue-1094
01:07:41.052 --> 01:07:43.272
gunpowder is fired, they call it a great
battle.

cue-1095
01:07:43.912 --> 01:07:47.832
Since no one wants to be shot, everyone
tries to stay out of harm's way.

cue-1096
01:07:48.492 --> 01:07:50.372
Injuries, let alone deaths, are rare.

cue-1097
01:07:51.012 --> 01:07:55.492
These two groups met the next day, and
after much firing, one man on the Nzundu

cue-1098
01:07:55.492 --> 01:08:00.432
side was slightly wounded. Blood had been
drawn, so the next day they tried to

cue-1099
01:08:00.432 --> 01:08:01.392
even the score.

cue-1100
01:08:02.432 --> 01:08:07.102
This time, they succeeded beyond their
intent. One of Matula's people was killed.

cue-1101
01:08:07.102 --> 01:08:08.912
That put an end to the fighting,

cue-1102
01:08:09.672 --> 01:08:14.472
for now. They paused to figure out what
had caused the man's death. Tragically,

cue-1103
01:08:14.472 --> 01:08:17.872
the people still believed in witchcraft
and accused Matula of murder.

cue-1104
01:08:18.612 --> 01:08:21.542
Even though he wasn't present at the
battle, they blamed him.

cue-1105
01:08:22.252 --> 01:08:27.232
To a reasonable person, it would make no
sense. Why would Matula want one of his

cue-1106
01:08:27.232 --> 01:08:28.112
own men dead?

cue-1107
01:08:28.892 --> 01:08:32.312
But they reasoned that because he had
caused the war, he was responsible.

cue-1108
01:08:33.152 --> 01:08:37.072
Also, they feared that if they didn't
accuse him, he might demand heavy damages

cue-1109
01:08:37.072 --> 01:08:38.632
from the man who had killed his relative.

cue-1110
01:08:39.452 --> 01:08:43.892
So the war stopped for the time being, and
the focus shifted entirely to Matula.

cue-1111
01:08:44.652 --> 01:08:46.862
They labeled him a witch and called for
his death.

cue-1112
01:08:47.632 --> 01:08:49.792
Now he faced a different kind of battle,

cue-1113
01:08:50.432 --> 01:08:55.312
not one fought with guns, but a spiritual
war against the deep darkness that

cue-1114
01:08:55.312 --> 01:08:56.272
sought to destroy him.

cue-1115
01:08:58.682 --> 01:09:00.672
[upbeat music] Chapter Nine:

cue-1116
01:09:01.612 --> 01:09:02.212
Persecution.

cue-1117
01:09:05.412 --> 01:09:09.672
Now everyone remembered everything Matula
had ever said about God's palavers,

cue-1118
01:09:10.332 --> 01:09:14.412
and rightly so, for he had never hidden
the light he had received, and he had

cue-1119
01:09:14.412 --> 01:09:16.772
never been ashamed to speak of Christ
before others.

cue-1120
01:09:17.682 --> 01:09:18.902
But to most of the natives,

cue-1121
01:09:19.512 --> 01:09:20.852
these teachings were sorcery.

cue-1122
01:09:21.632 --> 01:09:25.512
So when poverty, sickness, and death
spread among his relatives, they blamed

cue-1123
01:09:25.512 --> 01:09:25.642
him.

cue-1124
01:09:26.392 --> 01:09:30.732
Unless he gave up these new beliefs and
returned to his old ways, they said, he

cue-1125
01:09:30.732 --> 01:09:31.772
would have to be killed.

cue-1126
01:09:32.632 --> 01:09:36.442
Most of his old friends abandoned him and
joined those who accused him of being a

cue-1127
01:09:36.442 --> 01:09:36.692
witch.

cue-1128
01:09:37.472 --> 01:09:42.092
One old chief, who had once been a close
friend to Matula, now decided it was his

cue-1129
01:09:42.092 --> 01:09:44.252
duty to lead the first attack on him.

cue-1130
01:09:45.212 --> 01:09:47.992
The chief was cunning and laid his plan
carefully.

cue-1131
01:09:48.612 --> 01:09:53.512
He announced a great fetish ceremony to
renew the power of his nkisi for hunting

cue-1132
01:09:53.512 --> 01:09:54.072
and fighting.

cue-1133
01:09:54.852 --> 01:09:59.212
But secretly, he told his people the real
purpose was to kill Matula when he

cue-1134
01:09:59.212 --> 01:10:03.992
came. The plan was to pretend the chief
was sick or come up with another excuse to

cue-1135
01:10:03.992 --> 01:10:04.772
summon Matula.

cue-1136
01:10:05.512 --> 01:10:09.692
Then they would kill him. Everyone
involved was sworn to secrecy. Everything

cue-1137
01:10:09.692 --> 01:10:12.192
was prepared, and they waited for the
appointed day.

cue-1138
01:10:13.012 --> 01:10:16.492
But there was one true friend among them
who pretended loyalty to the chief.

cue-1139
01:10:17.132 --> 01:10:20.872
He flattered him and asked for permission
to go to the market to fetch some palm

cue-1140
01:10:20.872 --> 01:10:21.212
wine.

cue-1141
01:10:22.112 --> 01:10:27.052
Taking a roundabout route, he stopped at
Mongo to warn Matula not to go, no matter

cue-1142
01:10:27.052 --> 01:10:28.072
what message came.

cue-1143
01:10:29.092 --> 01:10:33.192
That evening, a messenger arrived saying
the chief was seriously ill and wanted to

cue-1144
01:10:33.192 --> 01:10:33.792
see Matula.

cue-1145
01:10:34.512 --> 01:10:36.672
But Matula's brother would not allow him
to go.

cue-1146
01:10:37.392 --> 01:10:38.932
Instead, he went himself

cue-1147
01:10:39.552 --> 01:10:41.912
and found the chief genuinely very sick.

cue-1148
01:10:42.532 --> 01:10:43.712
He had suddenly fallen ill.

cue-1149
01:10:45.272 --> 01:10:50.252
The next day, the very day he had planned
Matula's murder, the chief died. It

cue-1150
01:10:50.252 --> 01:10:52.112
was a direct intervention by God.

cue-1151
01:10:52.892 --> 01:10:54.572
Let others explain it how they wish.

cue-1152
01:10:55.592 --> 01:10:59.072
Not long after, the older brother who had
gone in Matula's place died.

cue-1153
01:10:59.832 --> 01:11:03.432
Before his death, he gathered his brothers
and gave each a stick, saying,

cue-1154
01:11:04.112 --> 01:11:06.932
"It is your place to settle matters and
fight if needed,

cue-1155
01:11:07.672 --> 01:11:08.852
but leave Matula alone.

cue-1156
01:11:09.572 --> 01:11:12.412
Let him live in peace, trade, and pray to
God,"

cue-1157
01:11:13.052 --> 01:11:13.892
Sambila Nzambi.

cue-1158
01:11:14.791 --> 01:11:19.371
In Congo, the words of a dying man are
deeply respected, even more than in many

cue-1159
01:11:19.372 --> 01:11:19.942
other cultures.

cue-1160
01:11:20.572 --> 01:11:25.492
So Matula's immediate family largely left
him in peace. However, his enemies, who

cue-1161
01:11:25.492 --> 01:11:29.672
came from the senior branch of his family,
only saw more reason to persecute him.

cue-1162
01:11:30.372 --> 01:11:31.772
How could they attack him now?

cue-1163
01:11:32.432 --> 01:11:37.072
They had already tried murder twice, and
each time he had escaped in astonishing

cue-1164
01:11:37.072 --> 01:11:37.372
ways.

cue-1165
01:11:38.332 --> 01:11:42.942
So these servants of darkness invented a
charge of adultery against him and four of

cue-1166
01:11:42.942 --> 01:11:47.472
his younger brothers. They found a woman
willing to accept a large bribe to lie,

cue-1167
01:11:47.472 --> 01:11:52.472
and she accused Matula. He was brought
before two powerful chiefs, one

cue-1168
01:11:52.472 --> 01:11:56.232
the chief of the woman, the other a
leader who had recently lost many people

cue-1169
01:11:56.232 --> 01:11:56.792
to illness.

cue-1170
01:11:57.472 --> 01:12:01.772
The first fined him forty men for the
deaths, and the second fined him three

cue-1171
01:12:01.772 --> 01:12:05.912
hundred thousand nzimbu, roughly
twenty-six pounds, for adultery.

cue-1172
01:12:06.632 --> 01:12:11.092
It was an absurd judgment, but there was
no way to fight it. His enemies believed

cue-1173
01:12:11.092 --> 01:12:15.072
they had finally succeeded, that Matula
would be sold into slavery.

cue-1174
01:12:15.872 --> 01:12:20.632
Matula feared the same and told his wife,
Kento, to return to her people for her

cue-1175
01:12:20.632 --> 01:12:20.992
safety.

cue-1176
01:12:21.892 --> 01:12:25.772
But she replied, like someone from
scripture she had never heard of, "Where

cue-1177
01:12:25.772 --> 01:12:29.092
you go, I will go. If you go into slavery,
so will I."

cue-1178
01:12:30.092 --> 01:12:34.732
Nothing could persuade her to leave him.
To the surprise of his enemies, Matula

cue-1179
01:12:34.732 --> 01:12:36.872
began doing all he could to pay the fine.

cue-1180
01:12:37.492 --> 01:12:41.832
He managed to pay half the money and
surrender five men. He also had many sheep

cue-1181
01:12:41.832 --> 01:12:44.512
scattered across the country that he
hoped not to lose.

cue-1182
01:12:45.232 --> 01:12:48.372
It became clear he would likely succeed in
paying the full fine.

cue-1183
01:12:49.172 --> 01:12:51.002
So his enemies began plotting again,

cue-1184
01:12:51.692 --> 01:12:56.332
this time determined to create a new
accusation that would surely cost him his

cue-1185
01:12:56.332 --> 01:12:56.592
life.

cue-1186
01:12:57.432 --> 01:13:01.392
One man remembered that some years
earlier, a woman had died under unusual

cue-1187
01:13:01.392 --> 01:13:06.212
circumstances, though it was actually
smallpox that killed her.Now they

cue-1188
01:13:06.212 --> 01:13:10.812
planned to use that incident against
Matula. Their goal was to accuse him of

cue-1189
01:13:10.812 --> 01:13:11.112
murder.

cue-1190
01:13:11.852 --> 01:13:16.111
The state had recently arrived in Tumba,
about six hours away, and had begun

cue-1191
01:13:16.112 --> 01:13:17.392
enforcing new laws,

cue-1192
01:13:18.012 --> 01:13:21.472
one of which threatened death by hanging
for anyone convicted of murder.

cue-1193
01:13:22.172 --> 01:13:26.112
So if Matula could be formally charged and
handed over to the authorities, his

cue-1194
01:13:26.112 --> 01:13:29.971
enemies believed they could finally be rid
of him without laying a hand on him

cue-1195
01:13:29.972 --> 01:13:30.592
themselves.

cue-1196
01:13:31.272 --> 01:13:34.772
They bound him and took him to Tumba as a
criminal, accusing him of murder.

cue-1197
01:13:35.432 --> 01:13:37.152
At the beginning of eighteen ninety-six,

cue-1198
01:13:37.772 --> 01:13:38.912
Tumba was a wilderness.

cue-1199
01:13:39.632 --> 01:13:43.812
By midsummer, it had become a bustling
construction site, and by the end of the

cue-1200
01:13:43.812 --> 01:13:46.972
year, it had transformed into a thriving
town.

cue-1201
01:13:47.772 --> 01:13:52.232
Traders' shops sprang up like mushrooms,
an almost unbelievable number for the

cue-1202
01:13:52.232 --> 01:13:52.512
area.

cue-1203
01:13:53.372 --> 01:13:56.152
A residence was built for the
commissioner, along with government

cue-1204
01:13:56.152 --> 01:13:58.632
buildings and barracks for over fifty
soldiers.

cue-1205
01:13:59.472 --> 01:14:03.712
Some readers may recall Tumba as the site
of one of the most heartbreaking stories

cue-1206
01:14:03.712 --> 01:14:05.402
in the history of the Congo mission.

cue-1207
01:14:06.242 --> 01:14:09.752
Mr. Stephen started the station there in
May eighteen ninety-six.

cue-1208
01:14:10.392 --> 01:14:15.032
At the end of the year, when Mr. and Mrs.
Popel arrived, he moved upriver to Yacusu

cue-1209
01:14:15.032 --> 01:14:15.852
for further work.

cue-1210
01:14:16.592 --> 01:14:20.192
Mr. Popel struggled with illness for
months and died the following April.

cue-1211
01:14:21.052 --> 01:14:25.092
Just six weeks later, his wife died too
and was buried beside him.

cue-1212
01:14:25.892 --> 01:14:30.552
Early that same year, Matula was taken to
Tumba to stand trial, accused of

cue-1213
01:14:30.552 --> 01:14:35.512
murder and adultery. At the time, the
judge only visited the town occasionally

cue-1214
01:14:35.512 --> 01:14:39.672
and depended heavily on a native
interpreter, who was easily bribed. In

cue-1215
01:14:39.672 --> 01:14:43.912
fact, most non-Christian natives were
known to accept bribes as readily as

cue-1216
01:14:43.912 --> 01:14:45.312
flowers receive sunlight.

cue-1217
01:14:45.992 --> 01:14:50.752
Skilled speakers and often bold liars,
they could convincingly make evil appear

cue-1218
01:14:50.752 --> 01:14:54.512
good and twist an innocent person's
character into that of a villain.

cue-1219
01:14:55.302 --> 01:14:59.232
Their performance could deceive even the
sharpest defense counsel unfamiliar with

cue-1220
01:14:59.232 --> 01:14:59.812
their ways.

cue-1221
01:15:00.692 --> 01:15:05.012
Matula's enemies prepared their case
carefully. Along with the murder charge

cue-1222
01:15:05.012 --> 01:15:09.732
involving two women, they revived the old
accusation of adultery, though they

cue-1223
01:15:09.732 --> 01:15:11.172
didn't emphasize it as much.

cue-1224
01:15:11.832 --> 01:15:14.012
Still, the woman was present to testify
against him.

cue-1225
01:15:14.821 --> 01:15:18.592
They quickly found the interpreter and
offered him a generous bribe, promising

cue-1226
01:15:18.592 --> 01:15:20.502
more if Matula were sentenced to death.

cue-1227
01:15:21.922 --> 01:15:26.252
A few days later, Matula's case was
brought before the court. The interpreter

cue-1228
01:15:26.252 --> 01:15:30.692
presented the charges to the judge and
gave a detailed account based entirely on

cue-1229
01:15:30.692 --> 01:15:35.212
the version from Matula's accusers of the
events and of Matula's supposed character.

cue-1230
01:15:35.932 --> 01:15:39.292
Witnesses were called, all of them false,
to support the accusations.

cue-1231
01:15:40.002 --> 01:15:44.932
Their testimony painted Matula as an
umpwimbihi, a wild, lawless man,

cue-1232
01:15:44.932 --> 01:15:48.892
and claimed the country would be better
without him. Then came the defense

cue-1233
01:15:48.892 --> 01:15:52.592
witnesses. They could only speak of
Matula's character and say they believed

cue-1234
01:15:52.592 --> 01:15:56.552
he was innocent. But under
cross-examination, it came out that Matula

cue-1235
01:15:56.552 --> 01:16:01.192
had been fined on several occasions and
was seen by local chiefs as an umpwimbulu,

cue-1236
01:16:01.192 --> 01:16:05.832
a troublemaker. Their testimony, instead
of helping, strengthened the

cue-1237
01:16:05.832 --> 01:16:06.952
prosecution's case.

cue-1238
01:16:07.712 --> 01:16:11.272
Things looked very bad for Matula. His
enemies were rejoicing.

cue-1239
01:16:12.192 --> 01:16:14.652
Then the judge called on Matula to speak
for himself.

cue-1240
01:16:15.432 --> 01:16:20.112
Calmly and plainly, Matula gave a truthful
account of his relationship with those

cue-1241
01:16:20.112 --> 01:16:20.952
who were accusing him.

cue-1242
01:16:21.592 --> 01:16:22.472
He ended by saying...

cue-1243
01:16:23.242 --> 01:16:28.152
"My Lord, these people have sought my life
and have tried to kill me many times.

cue-1244
01:16:28.812 --> 01:16:31.172
God knows I am innocent of these charges.

cue-1245
01:16:31.792 --> 01:16:34.132
I have never killed nor helped to kill

cue-1246
01:16:34.772 --> 01:16:35.232
anyone."

cue-1247
01:16:36.642 --> 01:16:41.472
The judge was deeply impressed by his
honest and simple words. He found himself

cue-1248
01:16:41.472 --> 01:16:45.212
torn. Should he accept one man's word
against many witnesses?

cue-1249
01:16:45.872 --> 01:16:48.412
He knew his interpreter believed Matula
was guilty.

cue-1250
01:16:49.152 --> 01:16:53.172
During the lunch break, the judge weighed
his decision. He was scheduled to leave

cue-1251
01:16:53.172 --> 01:16:53.812
the next morning.

cue-1252
01:16:54.672 --> 01:16:56.632
Should he sentence Matula to be hanged
now?

cue-1253
01:16:57.352 --> 01:17:02.112
No, he decided not to. Instead, he would
give Matula a chance to prove his

cue-1254
01:17:02.112 --> 01:17:02.592
innocence.

cue-1255
01:17:03.212 --> 01:17:06.742
When court resumed, the judge called
Matula forward and said...

cue-1256
01:17:06.742 --> 01:17:10.892
"Your case is very serious, but as you
said, God knows whether you are innocent

cue-1257
01:17:10.892 --> 01:17:15.312
or not. I'm going to release you for a few
months, but when you are summoned again,

cue-1258
01:17:15.312 --> 01:17:19.472
you must come. And unless you bring more
evidence of your innocence, the judgment

cue-1259
01:17:19.472 --> 01:17:20.352
will go against you."

cue-1260
01:17:21.532 --> 01:17:26.052
Matula thanked the judge and, much to the
anger of his enemies, walked out of the

cue-1261
01:17:26.052 --> 01:17:29.352
court a free man, at least until the judge
returned.

cue-1262
01:17:30.172 --> 01:17:35.012
When Matula returned to Mungo, his wives
and sisters, exhausted from crying and

cue-1263
01:17:35.012 --> 01:17:38.972
having given him up for dead, were
overjoyed to see him alive.

cue-1264
01:17:39.992 --> 01:17:43.612
But their joy quickly faded when he told
them he would have to return to Tumba.

cue-1265
01:17:44.392 --> 01:17:46.352
He saw no way to strengthen his defense.

cue-1266
01:17:47.152 --> 01:17:51.892
His accusers were confused by the delay.
They began to worry that Matula might

cue-1267
01:17:51.892 --> 01:17:53.452
escape judgment altogether.

cue-1268
01:17:54.182 --> 01:17:58.402
Not willing to leave the matter in the
state's hands, they resumed harassing him.

cue-1269
01:17:58.402 --> 01:18:02.372
They sent messengers again and again to
see if he was still in town, though none

cue-1270
01:18:02.372 --> 01:18:06.172
dared approach too closely, fearing he was
in league with evil spirits.

cue-1271
01:18:06.952 --> 01:18:11.711
Still, they resolved to form a strong
party to capture him, and a friend warned

cue-1272
01:18:11.712 --> 01:18:13.892
Matula that they would arrive in two days.

cue-1273
01:18:15.172 --> 01:18:15.872
Poor Matula.

cue-1274
01:18:16.482 --> 01:18:21.472
Though he believed God was with him, he
felt weary from being constantly hunted.

cue-1275
01:18:21.472 --> 01:18:24.552
In that moment of deep need, he longed for
someone,

cue-1276
01:18:25.172 --> 01:18:27.592
anyone, to stand by him and help.

cue-1277
01:18:28.712 --> 01:18:29.492
But who was there?

cue-1278
01:18:30.372 --> 01:18:33.412
Pond, though faithful, had no influence to
protect him.

cue-1279
01:18:34.172 --> 01:18:39.072
Matula feared that even going to him would
only stir up more anger from his enemies.

cue-1280
01:18:39.692 --> 01:18:43.492
It was a time of great testing for his
faith. If he turned his back on

cue-1281
01:18:43.492 --> 01:18:47.112
Christianity and gave up all he had to his
accusers, they would let him live.

cue-1282
01:18:47.892 --> 01:18:49.572
The question now stood before him.

cue-1283
01:18:50.212 --> 01:18:51.552
Should he give in to save his life?

cue-1284
01:18:54.192 --> 01:18:57.632
Chapter 10: Exodus.

cue-1285
01:18:59.912 --> 01:19:04.352
The temptation was very real. Unless he
made peace with his enemies, there seemed

cue-1286
01:19:04.352 --> 01:19:07.648
to be no hope of escape.At least from a
human perspective.

cue-1287
01:19:08.288 --> 01:19:13.098
He had only two days to decide. He thought
and prayed deeply about it.

cue-1288
01:19:13.098 --> 01:19:15.728
Then, as if by revelation, the thought
came,

cue-1289
01:19:16.728 --> 01:19:17.788
"What about the missionaries?"

cue-1290
01:19:18.768 --> 01:19:20.488
At that, he danced with joy.

cue-1291
01:19:21.128 --> 01:19:22.608
Why hadn't he thought of it before?

cue-1292
01:19:23.448 --> 01:19:28.388
To us, it seems strange, and must be
counted among those odd lapses that happen

cue-1293
01:19:28.388 --> 01:19:29.808
in almost every life.

cue-1294
01:19:30.588 --> 01:19:35.247
As soon as the idea came, he resolved to
act on it. He told Manquenha to go ahead

cue-1295
01:19:35.248 --> 01:19:39.728
and let Mr. Bentley know he was coming,
bringing with him as many of his people as

cue-1296
01:19:39.728 --> 01:19:40.288
would join.

cue-1297
01:19:40.968 --> 01:19:45.467
Then he visited his closest relatives and
shared his decision to go and settle at

cue-1298
01:19:45.468 --> 01:19:50.368
Ngombe. His two wives agreed right away,
as did most of his family, though

cue-1299
01:19:50.368 --> 01:19:53.868
some preferred to stay home rather than
move to an unfamiliar place.

cue-1300
01:19:54.728 --> 01:19:58.788
They packed quickly, prepared food for the
journey, and were ready to leave the

cue-1301
01:19:58.788 --> 01:20:01.507
night before his enemies were expected to
capture him.

cue-1302
01:20:02.588 --> 01:20:03.648
They set off in the dark,

cue-1303
01:20:04.288 --> 01:20:08.928
a small group of thirty-seven, including
his nearly sixty-year-old mother and a

cue-1304
01:20:08.928 --> 01:20:10.608
baby just a few months old.

cue-1305
01:20:11.448 --> 01:20:16.328
Some had severe leg ulcers, one was lame,
and another hadn't walked in weeks.

cue-1306
01:20:17.128 --> 01:20:21.348
What a mixed group they were. It's a
mystery how they managed to travel the

cue-1307
01:20:21.348 --> 01:20:26.308
sixty miles without accident or injury.
Surely God was with them. They

cue-1308
01:20:26.308 --> 01:20:29.208
walked all night and rested near the
railway at dawn.

cue-1309
01:20:30.068 --> 01:20:32.568
While eating breakfast, someone shouted,
"Soldiers!"

cue-1310
01:20:33.488 --> 01:20:36.668
The women ran into the tall grass, and the
men looked frightened.

cue-1311
01:20:37.388 --> 01:20:42.268
But it was a false alarm. Just one soldier
passed by, not recognizing them, and

cue-1312
01:20:42.268 --> 01:20:45.408
simply greeted them with a "Good morning"
before moving on.

cue-1313
01:20:46.128 --> 01:20:50.588
They walked a little farther along the
railway and met some white men who asked

cue-1314
01:20:50.588 --> 01:20:54.268
where they were going. They said they were
heading to their friends at Ngombe.

cue-1315
01:20:55.388 --> 01:20:56.758
"Oui, oui, to Monsieur Bentley,"

cue-1316
01:20:57.578 --> 01:20:59.818
the men replied, then continued on their
way.

cue-1317
01:21:00.668 --> 01:21:05.368
The journey from there was exhausting, up
hills and down valleys, through marshes

cue-1318
01:21:05.368 --> 01:21:10.288
and swamps, until they finally reached
Kinkete, the place where Matula had paid

cue-1319
01:21:10.288 --> 01:21:12.308
taxes back in 1891.

cue-1320
01:21:13.048 --> 01:21:17.428
They rested there for a while. The locals
urged Matula to settle among them and even

cue-1321
01:21:17.428 --> 01:21:19.688
returned the unjust tax they had taken.

cue-1322
01:21:20.548 --> 01:21:24.468
But since there were no Christians there,
and he did not feel safe among others,

cue-1323
01:21:25.148 --> 01:21:25.728
he refused.

cue-1324
01:21:26.468 --> 01:21:29.368
Still, one or two of his group stayed
behind for a time.

cue-1325
01:21:30.268 --> 01:21:34.268
About an hour from Kinkete lived
Selulundi, one of the most remarkable and

cue-1326
01:21:34.268 --> 01:21:38.708
upright chiefs in the area. He knew Matula
well and tried to persuade him to settle

cue-1327
01:21:38.708 --> 01:21:38.968
with him.

cue-1328
01:21:39.668 --> 01:21:44.288
But Matula was eager to be near the white
missionary. However, he left the weaker

cue-1329
01:21:44.288 --> 01:21:48.988
ones with Selulundi and continued the
journey with the rest to Ngombe, about

cue-1330
01:21:48.988 --> 01:21:49.928
four hours further.

cue-1331
01:21:50.888 --> 01:21:54.148
Matula was not disappointed in the welcome
he and his group received.

cue-1332
01:21:54.788 --> 01:21:59.228
He immediately felt that, as far as human
help could reach, the missionary would do

cue-1333
01:21:59.228 --> 01:22:00.188
all he could for them.

cue-1334
01:22:00.868 --> 01:22:03.688
So he looked for a place and began
building a home.

cue-1335
01:22:04.808 --> 01:22:09.108
A few days later, Matula went back for the
rest of his large family, who had stayed

cue-1336
01:22:09.108 --> 01:22:14.088
behind to rest. He found that one of his
sisters had given birth to a child,

cue-1337
01:22:14.088 --> 01:22:17.268
a bright little girl who now runs happily
around the station.

cue-1338
01:22:18.188 --> 01:22:22.307
To his surprise, he also met nine of his
brothers who hadn't been in Mongo when he

cue-1339
01:22:22.308 --> 01:22:26.528
left. When they heard where he had gone,
they decided to follow and settle with

cue-1340
01:22:26.528 --> 01:22:26.648
him.

cue-1341
01:22:27.388 --> 01:22:30.928
This was a great encouragement and showed
how much they trusted him.

cue-1342
01:22:31.788 --> 01:22:35.568
The next day, they all set out for Ngombe
and arrived in the evening,

cue-1343
01:22:36.228 --> 01:22:39.348
feeling they had finally found a place of
peace and safety,

cue-1344
01:22:39.988 --> 01:22:41.428
free from the threat of enemies.

cue-1345
01:22:42.428 --> 01:22:46.788
It was a great joy for us to welcome such
a large group to the little village of

cue-1346
01:22:46.788 --> 01:22:51.728
Vyanga Vyanga, named after Tom Comber, now
being built just outside our

cue-1347
01:22:51.728 --> 01:22:52.248
grounds.

cue-1348
01:22:53.148 --> 01:22:57.428
We were especially glad because we want
the village to grow with new people rather

cue-1349
01:22:57.428 --> 01:23:02.228
than just those already at the station,
to bring fresh energy and avoid forming a

cue-1350
01:23:02.228 --> 01:23:05.128
closed circle that might hinder rather
than help.

cue-1351
01:23:06.388 --> 01:23:10.248
What Matula did was a courageous act. He
had received a call,

cue-1352
01:23:10.888 --> 01:23:12.908
just as clearly as Abraham long ago,

cue-1353
01:23:13.588 --> 01:23:16.808
"Leave your country, your people, and your
father's house."

cue-1354
01:23:17.808 --> 01:23:20.368
And didn't he obey that call just as
faithfully?

cue-1355
01:23:21.108 --> 01:23:25.308
It was no small thing to place all his
trust in a missionary, someone he had been

cue-1356
01:23:25.308 --> 01:23:27.208
taught to see as an enemy of his people.

cue-1357
01:23:28.008 --> 01:23:31.248
Some might say he simply chose the lesser
of two evils.

cue-1358
01:23:32.408 --> 01:23:33.228
But could that be?

cue-1359
01:23:34.268 --> 01:23:35.468
If he had stayed in Mongo,

cue-1360
01:23:36.128 --> 01:23:37.428
only he would have been killed.

cue-1361
01:23:38.308 --> 01:23:42.628
But by leaving, he placed himself and all
his loved ones in the hands of God's

cue-1362
01:23:42.628 --> 01:23:43.088
servants.

cue-1363
01:23:43.768 --> 01:23:48.768
It was a pure, simple, and honest faith,
and God has greatly blessed

cue-1364
01:23:48.768 --> 01:23:49.328
him for it.

cue-1365
01:23:50.438 --> 01:23:54.748
They arrived near the end of the wet
season, a poor time to start planting, but

cue-1366
01:23:54.748 --> 01:23:59.668
a good time to begin building. Everyone
threw themselves eagerly into the task of

cue-1367
01:23:59.668 --> 01:24:01.068
creating a new village.

cue-1368
01:24:01.828 --> 01:24:06.248
During the remaining rainy days, the women
worked at digging and planting manioc,

cue-1369
01:24:06.248 --> 01:24:10.528
while the men gathered sticks and grass
for constructing houses. It was a very

cue-1370
01:24:10.528 --> 01:24:15.388
busy season. We supported them as best we
could, allowing them to buy food from our

cue-1371
01:24:15.388 --> 01:24:19.888
daily stock when they couldn't get enough
from the local people. Yet they never

cue-1372
01:24:19.888 --> 01:24:22.948
became too busy to miss the daily prayer
meetings.

cue-1373
01:24:23.688 --> 01:24:28.228
All of them came regularly, and for us,
having over forty people join in daily

cue-1374
01:24:28.228 --> 01:24:30.128
worship was a great encouragement.

cue-1375
01:24:30.728 --> 01:24:35.328
It brought real joy to see them grow more
attentive, and over time, to

cue-1376
01:24:35.328 --> 01:24:39.128
witness many of them openly take their
stand for the Lord.

cue-1377
01:24:40.008 --> 01:24:42.008
But I am getting ahead of the story.

cue-1378
01:24:43.028 --> 01:24:47.828
By mid-August, all their houses were built
and their gardens ready for planting, a

cue-1379
01:24:47.828 --> 01:24:49.908
record time for natives in the Congo.

cue-1380
01:24:51.068 --> 01:24:55.988
During these months, Matula remained
surprisingly calm and cheerful. The women

cue-1381
01:24:55.988 --> 01:25:00.268
would sometimes break down in tears,
fearing he might have to return to Tumba

cue-1382
01:25:00.268 --> 01:25:02.048
to face the judge and his accusers.

cue-1383
01:25:02.718 --> 01:25:06.108
There still seemed no way to strengthen
his case to prove his innocence.

cue-1384
01:25:06.768 --> 01:25:11.436
We, of course, could only speak to the
character we had observed.But Matula never

cue-1385
01:25:11.436 --> 01:25:15.416
became discouraged. He saw clear signs of
God's help and blessing.

cue-1386
01:25:16.036 --> 01:25:20.036
Being innocent, he firmly believed that
God would one day reveal the truth.

cue-1387
01:25:20.736 --> 01:25:22.656
It was this confidence that gave him
peace.

cue-1388
01:25:26.856 --> 01:25:29.596
Chapter Eleven: Revisiting His People.

cue-1389
01:25:32.416 --> 01:25:36.616
From the time Matula arrived at Ngombe, he
worked hard to make his people happy and

cue-1390
01:25:36.616 --> 01:25:37.036
comfortable.

cue-1391
01:25:37.816 --> 01:25:41.996
As we've seen, by mid-August, they were
well settled. Then his thoughts turned

cue-1392
01:25:41.996 --> 01:25:44.896
from those who were safe to those who were
still in danger.

cue-1393
01:25:45.656 --> 01:25:50.096
He didn't know how long he himself would
be spared. He could be summoned to Tumba

cue-1394
01:25:50.096 --> 01:25:53.156
at any time, and it seemed there could
only be one outcome.

cue-1395
01:25:53.976 --> 01:25:54.836
But this he knew,

cue-1396
01:25:55.496 --> 01:25:59.736
if he were hanged, his enemies would steal
everything he had left behind in Mongo

cue-1397
01:25:59.736 --> 01:26:02.596
and secretly sell his closest relatives
into slavery.

cue-1398
01:26:03.376 --> 01:26:07.576
Longing to protect them physically, but
even more spiritually, he decided to

cue-1399
01:26:07.576 --> 01:26:12.406
return once more to the place of his
trials and make another effort to save his

cue-1400
01:26:12.406 --> 01:26:12.716
people.

cue-1401
01:26:13.816 --> 01:26:17.956
When word spread that he was going back to
Mongo, his friends tried hard to change

cue-1402
01:26:17.956 --> 01:26:22.736
his mind. His poor old mother clung to him
and begged him with tears not to risk it

cue-1403
01:26:22.736 --> 01:26:23.016
again.

cue-1404
01:26:23.836 --> 01:26:26.776
To them, it seemed like a sure path to
death.

cue-1405
01:26:27.656 --> 01:26:30.776
But like Paul, he would not be persuaded
to turn back.

cue-1406
01:26:31.516 --> 01:26:32.846
Two of his brothers went with him.

cue-1407
01:26:33.496 --> 01:26:37.476
After two days of good travel, they
arrived on the evening of the third day

cue-1408
01:26:37.476 --> 01:26:39.586
and quietly entered the house of a friend.

cue-1409
01:26:40.396 --> 01:26:44.396
In the morning, when he went out, his
relatives, who never expected to see him

cue-1410
01:26:44.396 --> 01:26:44.636
again,

cue-1411
01:26:45.276 --> 01:26:49.226
were overjoyed. They ran about shouting,
"Matula has returned!"

cue-1412
01:26:49.956 --> 01:26:54.056
But he cautioned them not to make too much
noise. He told them why he had come and

cue-1413
01:26:54.056 --> 01:26:58.555
pleaded with them to leave everything and
come hear the Nsangu Zambote, the good

cue-1414
01:26:58.556 --> 01:27:00.076
news, at the mission station.

cue-1415
01:27:01.316 --> 01:27:02.076
But they refused.

cue-1416
01:27:02.906 --> 01:27:03.516
"No, no,"

cue-1417
01:27:04.556 --> 01:27:05.536
they said. "Not us.

cue-1418
01:27:06.376 --> 01:27:08.936
We're living in the abundance you fools
ran away from.

cue-1419
01:27:09.676 --> 01:27:12.616
There are plenty of gardens, goats, sheep,
and chickens.

cue-1420
01:27:13.276 --> 01:27:14.016
We're not going."

cue-1421
01:27:15.336 --> 01:27:18.356
He warned them that if he was killed, they
might be sold into slavery.

cue-1422
01:27:19.116 --> 01:27:21.476
But like Lot's sons-in-law, they mocked
him.

cue-1423
01:27:22.096 --> 01:27:25.485
As is common among natives, they only
thought of the present moment.

cue-1424
01:27:26.425 --> 01:27:30.996
They took quite literally our Lord's
words, "Do not be anxious about tomorrow.

cue-1425
01:27:31.756 --> 01:27:34.336
Sufficient unto the day is the evil
thereof."

cue-1426
01:27:35.196 --> 01:27:39.396
They made no distinction between being
overanxious and simply being prepared.

cue-1427
01:27:39.996 --> 01:27:42.676
To them, worry of any kind was pointless.

cue-1428
01:27:43.336 --> 01:27:44.996
They chose to live one day at a time,

cue-1429
01:27:45.636 --> 01:27:48.176
carefree, yes, but not without
consequence.

cue-1430
01:27:49.016 --> 01:27:52.456
Matula was not there long before word
spread that he had returned.

cue-1431
01:27:53.226 --> 01:27:57.336
People came to see him and accused him of
betraying them to the white men at Ngombe.

cue-1432
01:27:58.196 --> 01:28:02.376
Mr. Bentley happened to be in the area at
the time, so they were too afraid to harm

cue-1433
01:28:02.376 --> 01:28:02.756
Matula.

cue-1434
01:28:03.616 --> 01:28:07.736
Still, he knew he needed to act quickly.
He wanted to take a few of his sheep with

cue-1435
01:28:07.736 --> 01:28:09.296
him, but found only nine.

cue-1436
01:28:09.936 --> 01:28:11.876
Many had already been stolen and sold.

cue-1437
01:28:13.196 --> 01:28:15.516
He asked one of his brothers to lead the
sheep ahead.

cue-1438
01:28:16.236 --> 01:28:20.096
When his enemies heard this, they went
ahead of him and set fire to the tall

cue-1439
01:28:20.096 --> 01:28:24.976
grass in a narrow, enclosed area. The
sheep panicked and ran through the

cue-1440
01:28:24.976 --> 01:28:29.766
flames. One died, and the rest were badly
singed. Grass

cue-1441
01:28:29.766 --> 01:28:32.756
fires occasionally lead to deaths, though
not often.

cue-1442
01:28:33.416 --> 01:28:36.776
In 1901, a woman and her child were burned
alive.

cue-1443
01:28:37.596 --> 01:28:41.576
However, the wider roads enforced by the
government have helped prevent such

cue-1444
01:28:41.576 --> 01:28:46.556
tragedies. It became clear that Matula's
enemies were still very active,

cue-1445
01:28:47.276 --> 01:28:51.156
so he gathered his people again and
pleaded with them not to remain behind.

cue-1446
01:28:51.956 --> 01:28:54.056
After much discussion, they took a vote.

cue-1447
01:28:54.776 --> 01:28:57.956
Many who just days earlier had said, "We
will not go,"

cue-1448
01:28:58.596 --> 01:29:00.956
now voted eagerly to leave the hostile
region.

cue-1449
01:29:01.616 --> 01:29:05.675
This change of heart, typical of their
shifting feelings, was prompted by

cue-1450
01:29:05.676 --> 01:29:10.586
whatever seemed most urgent at the moment.
A group of them soon left, but Matula

cue-1451
01:29:10.586 --> 01:29:12.436
and his two companions stayed behind.

cue-1452
01:29:13.076 --> 01:29:17.996
He still hoped to speak once more with
those who had been persecuting him and

cue-1453
01:29:17.996 --> 01:29:22.996
try to make peace, for he had learned to
love even his enemies, a hard

cue-1454
01:29:22.996 --> 01:29:25.556
lesson for even the most mature
Christians.

cue-1455
01:29:26.376 --> 01:29:28.576
He went to see Ponde and asked for advice.

cue-1456
01:29:29.275 --> 01:29:33.496
There he saw the work progressing well.
The people of Makuta were eagerly

cue-1457
01:29:33.496 --> 01:29:38.295
learning, and it lifted his spirits. It
made him long even more for the people of

cue-1458
01:29:38.296 --> 01:29:40.756
his own town to desire the same knowledge.

cue-1459
01:29:41.696 --> 01:29:45.496
After discussing the matter with Ponde,
they decided to return together and try to

cue-1460
01:29:45.496 --> 01:29:49.436
bring back one or two boys from Mongo to
be trained at the mission station.

cue-1461
01:29:50.206 --> 01:29:54.076
This was their way of showing their zeal
to help and save the people.

cue-1462
01:29:54.876 --> 01:29:59.345
Whether their effort was guided by wisdom
or not, readers may judge for themselves.

cue-1463
01:30:00.146 --> 01:30:04.816
They returned to Mongo, full of love for
the people and a deep desire to help

cue-1464
01:30:04.816 --> 01:30:08.776
them. Both friends and enemies gathered to
welcome Ponde.

cue-1465
01:30:09.526 --> 01:30:14.196
Then they spoke to them about God's love,
how He cares for us and sent His Son Jesus

cue-1466
01:30:14.196 --> 01:30:19.076
to show that love by dying for us and
bearing our sins in His own body

cue-1467
01:30:19.076 --> 01:30:22.556
so that even the worst sinner might be
saved through Him.

cue-1468
01:30:23.536 --> 01:30:28.376
Matula, with tears in his eyes, shared how
he now believed and spoke of

cue-1469
01:30:28.376 --> 01:30:30.736
all the good news he had heard at Ngombe.

cue-1470
01:30:31.516 --> 01:30:36.036
He told them he held no bitterness in his
heart against them and fully forgave them

cue-1471
01:30:36.036 --> 01:30:37.196
for how they had treated him.

cue-1472
01:30:37.796 --> 01:30:40.976
He pleaded with them to turn from their
evil ways and seek God.

cue-1473
01:30:41.616 --> 01:30:45.956
He also spoke of how the people at Makuta
were growing in knowledge and gaining

cue-1474
01:30:45.956 --> 01:30:50.686
wisdom, and how it would be good if they
too sent some boys to the mission station,

cue-1475
01:30:51.316 --> 01:30:55.916
boys who could return and teach them like
Ponde was doing. The people listened with

cue-1476
01:30:55.916 --> 01:31:00.396
great interest and attention. Matula was
convinced their hearts were softening.

cue-1477
01:31:00.396 --> 01:31:04.576
They spoke openly afterward and promised
to send a boy or two back with him to be

cue-1478
01:31:04.576 --> 01:31:04.956
trained.

cue-1479
01:31:05.816 --> 01:31:09.876
That evening, Ponde departed, feeling very
pleased with the outcome of the visit.

cue-1480
01:31:10.576 --> 01:31:14.656
But had he known what was about to happen
to Matula, he would surely have stayed

cue-1481
01:31:14.656 --> 01:31:16.716
until his friend had safely returned to

cue-1482
01:31:16.716 --> 01:31:21.606
Ngombe.Chapter

cue-1483
01:31:21.606 --> 01:31:21.966
12:

cue-1484
01:31:22.606 --> 01:31:23.106
Treachery.

cue-1485
01:31:25.386 --> 01:31:29.386
The morning after Ponda left, some of the
locals came to Matula and asked when he

cue-1486
01:31:29.386 --> 01:31:30.786
planned to return to Ngombe.

cue-1487
01:31:31.456 --> 01:31:35.906
He told them he would go the next day.
They then invited him to Mbanza, the main

cue-1488
01:31:35.906 --> 01:31:36.626
village of Mongo.

cue-1489
01:31:37.466 --> 01:31:40.866
That afternoon, saying they had arranged
to send four boys with him.

cue-1490
01:31:41.486 --> 01:31:46.176
Two were ready, and the other two would
follow later. Matula was overjoyed.

cue-1491
01:31:46.826 --> 01:31:50.485
In his simple faith, he truly believed
they were beginning to change.

cue-1492
01:31:51.276 --> 01:31:54.286
He thanked God for what he saw as a sign
of his blessing.

cue-1493
01:31:55.246 --> 01:31:57.446
That afternoon, he went with his two
companions.

cue-1494
01:31:58.206 --> 01:32:02.086
When they entered the chief's compound,
they were surprised to see a large group

cue-1495
01:32:02.086 --> 01:32:05.076
of people armed with guns, knives, and
sticks.

cue-1496
01:32:05.766 --> 01:32:10.406
Matula realized he had been betrayed, but
he sat down among them, trying to remain

cue-1497
01:32:10.406 --> 01:32:12.346
calm, and began talking with them.

cue-1498
01:32:13.066 --> 01:32:16.146
They asked questions about the white man
and the white man's God.

cue-1499
01:32:16.786 --> 01:32:21.146
As Matula answered, telling them again of
God's love and his own love for them,

cue-1500
01:32:21.826 --> 01:32:23.526
murmuring rose among the crowd.

cue-1501
01:32:24.566 --> 01:32:26.726
They couldn't understand such selfless
love.

cue-1502
01:32:27.926 --> 01:32:28.246
"Yes,"

cue-1503
01:32:28.966 --> 01:32:29.376
some said,

cue-1504
01:32:30.086 --> 01:32:34.646
"that's why our people are dying. Matula
is selling them all to the white man, who

cue-1505
01:32:34.646 --> 01:32:36.826
takes them away by some secret means."

cue-1506
01:32:38.096 --> 01:32:39.016
"We must get rid of him,"

cue-1507
01:32:39.646 --> 01:32:42.146
others said. "Let's take him to the river
and kill him."

cue-1508
01:32:42.906 --> 01:32:44.266
"No," one objected.

cue-1509
01:32:44.866 --> 01:32:46.906
"There are witches there. He might
escape."

cue-1510
01:32:48.366 --> 01:32:50.405
These things they whispered among
themselves.

cue-1511
01:32:51.366 --> 01:32:55.566
-Then one bold man said aloud ...
-"Well, Matula, what you've told us is

cue-1512
01:32:55.566 --> 01:33:00.186
good, and we want to learn too. We have
two boys up the river. Let's go and fetch

cue-1513
01:33:00.186 --> 01:33:00.386
them."

cue-1514
01:33:01.426 --> 01:33:04.446
Everyone agreed, and Matula and his
companions went along.

cue-1515
01:33:05.046 --> 01:33:09.366
They passed through a wooded area to a
lonely house, where they stopped to rest

cue-1516
01:33:09.366 --> 01:33:10.606
and called for the boys.

cue-1517
01:33:11.246 --> 01:33:15.526
They called repeatedly and even pretended
to go fetch them, but it was all a trick.

cue-1518
01:33:16.206 --> 01:33:17.466
No boys ever came.

cue-1519
01:33:18.306 --> 01:33:22.726
Meanwhile, Matula and his two friends sat
under the eaves of the house and began to

cue-1520
01:33:22.726 --> 01:33:24.826
read from their Mivelo Azai,

cue-1521
01:33:25.466 --> 01:33:26.146
New Testaments.

cue-1522
01:33:26.746 --> 01:33:28.666
But this only enraged the crowd.

cue-1523
01:33:29.406 --> 01:33:33.866
To them, those books held the names of all
they believed Matula had sold.

cue-1524
01:33:34.646 --> 01:33:39.086
One man jumped up and struck Matula on the
head. He stood up, but couldn't defend

cue-1525
01:33:39.086 --> 01:33:43.406
himself as another man stabbed him in the
forehead. Blood gushed down his face.

cue-1526
01:33:44.506 --> 01:33:46.886
His two friends ran, shouting, "Matula is
murdered!"

cue-1527
01:33:47.786 --> 01:33:51.366
The others then stripped him of his
clothes, bound him with ropes, fastened a

cue-1528
01:33:51.366 --> 01:33:55.125
forked stick around his neck, and led him
away in this shameful condition.

cue-1529
01:33:55.926 --> 01:33:59.506
At first, Matula could hardly stand, and
blood nearly blinded him.

cue-1530
01:34:00.526 --> 01:34:01.676
"Ah," he said,

cue-1531
01:34:02.346 --> 01:34:03.206
"God forgive you.

cue-1532
01:34:03.886 --> 01:34:05.186
Why do you want to kill me?

cue-1533
01:34:05.846 --> 01:34:09.986
I am going to die, but I'm not afraid. If
you kill me, you will suffer.

cue-1534
01:34:10.646 --> 01:34:13.586
Some of you won't even be allowed to bury
your own mothers."

cue-1535
01:34:14.386 --> 01:34:16.936
Referring to one of the greatest tragedies
in their culture.

cue-1536
01:34:17.606 --> 01:34:18.306
But they answered ...

cue-1537
01:34:18.986 --> 01:34:22.846
"You've killed and eaten so many. Think of
all those who died because of you.

cue-1538
01:34:23.446 --> 01:34:26.446
Why should you live? A traitor like you
doesn't deserve to live."

cue-1539
01:34:27.086 --> 01:34:27.586
He replied

cue-1540
01:34:28.246 --> 01:34:31.706
-...
-"You accuse me of killing Luvuma, Nzevo,

cue-1541
01:34:31.706 --> 01:34:35.886
and my mother, Mundele, but they are alive
and well at Ngombe.

cue-1542
01:34:36.626 --> 01:34:39.446
As for the others who have died, it was by
God's will."

cue-1543
01:34:40.386 --> 01:34:41.466
They refused to listen.

cue-1544
01:34:42.166 --> 01:34:43.626
They dragged him to a small river.

cue-1545
01:34:44.306 --> 01:34:46.046
There, he begged them to kill him.

cue-1546
01:34:46.686 --> 01:34:48.966
As he crossed the water, he stumbled over
a stone.

cue-1547
01:34:49.646 --> 01:34:53.706
They tied another stick around his neck
and pulled him up the other side. Then

cue-1548
01:34:53.706 --> 01:34:55.006
they led him to another village.

cue-1549
01:34:55.826 --> 01:34:59.576
The chief there, an old friend, pretended
to object, saying ...

cue-1550
01:34:59.576 --> 01:35:02.226
"Don't kill him here. I don't want to see
blood."

cue-1551
01:35:02.846 --> 01:35:06.486
When Matula begged for a piece of cloth to
cover himself, the chief refused.

cue-1552
01:35:07.275 --> 01:35:08.806
"No," he said. "Take him away."

cue-1553
01:35:10.206 --> 01:35:14.156
Matula cried and pleaded to be killed then
and there, but they ignored him.

cue-1554
01:35:14.806 --> 01:35:18.466
Others came to help drag him down into a
deep valley, where they tied him to a

cue-1555
01:35:18.466 --> 01:35:22.626
tree. Some ran off to fetch a chief and
others to approve his execution.

cue-1556
01:35:23.646 --> 01:35:28.646
Two chiefs and four men remained, sitting
around a small fire. To them, Matula,

cue-1557
01:35:28.646 --> 01:35:31.146
though weak and suffering, tried to speak.

cue-1558
01:35:32.456 --> 01:35:35.946
"Now I am dying," he said, "but I am not
afraid.

cue-1559
01:35:37.026 --> 01:35:39.976
I rejoice, for when I die, I go to God.

cue-1560
01:35:40.646 --> 01:35:43.046
You cannot kill me unless God allows it."

cue-1561
01:35:44.066 --> 01:35:45.146
He begged them to repent.

cue-1562
01:35:45.846 --> 01:35:49.106
-Their only response was ...
-"Let's have something to drink."

cue-1563
01:35:49.106 --> 01:35:53.866
One had brought a large calabash of palm
wine, and they sat drinking, trying to get

cue-1564
01:35:53.866 --> 01:35:57.706
drunk, while Matula, beaten and bleeding,
watched them in pity.

cue-1565
01:35:58.526 --> 01:36:02.446
What a scene! It brings to mind the
suffering of our Lord Jesus.

cue-1566
01:36:03.166 --> 01:36:07.646
Yet thank God, there are still those
willing to suffer for his name.

cue-1567
01:36:08.726 --> 01:36:12.506
The messengers returned, but they hadn't
found those most involved in the case.

cue-1568
01:36:13.336 --> 01:36:15.426
-"What shall we do?"
-One asked.

cue-1569
01:36:15.426 --> 01:36:17.166
-"Let's sell him,"
-Suggested someone.

cue-1570
01:36:17.846 --> 01:36:19.446
-"No,"
-Others replied.

cue-1571
01:36:19.446 --> 01:36:23.466
"That will only cause more problems later.
Better to kill him. Let's take him to

cue-1572
01:36:23.466 --> 01:36:25.126
Chief Kwenkeze and kill him there."

cue-1573
01:36:26.006 --> 01:36:30.906
They all agreed. As they went on, some old
acquaintances came by, mocking him. He

cue-1574
01:36:30.906 --> 01:36:32.206
begged one for a piece of cloth.

cue-1575
01:36:33.036 --> 01:36:35.046
-"Not me,"
-The man sneered.

cue-1576
01:36:35.046 --> 01:36:38.566
-"I'm going to buy you."
-When they reached another stream, Matula

cue-1577
01:36:38.566 --> 01:36:39.686
couldn't go any farther.

cue-1578
01:36:40.386 --> 01:36:42.266
He lay down and begged through tears.

cue-1579
01:36:43.046 --> 01:36:47.106
"Kill me, for the angels are waiting to
carry my spirit to heaven."

cue-1580
01:36:47.866 --> 01:36:51.826
This only made them more furious. They
beat him with sticks and ropes.

cue-1581
01:36:51.826 --> 01:36:54.945
-"Have mercy. Kill me with a gani,"
-He pleaded.

cue-1582
01:36:54.946 --> 01:36:59.705
But they had no such mercy in mind. Like a
cat playing with a mouse, they

cue-1583
01:36:59.706 --> 01:37:04.606
dragged him further along a rough path.
Blood seeped from his wounds, but these

cue-1584
01:37:04.606 --> 01:37:06.006
cruel men showed no pity.

cue-1585
01:37:06.766 --> 01:37:10.286
When they reached the next village, they
summoned a man who had been secretly

cue-1586
01:37:10.286 --> 01:37:14.586
assigned to kill Matula. He came forward,
sharpening a large knife.

cue-1587
01:37:15.226 --> 01:37:18.166
He reached out his hand to Matula and gave
him a kiembote,

cue-1588
01:37:18.986 --> 01:37:19.526
a farewell.

cue-1589
01:37:20.446 --> 01:37:25.288
Then, with cold determination, he raised
the knife high to strike.But just before

cue-1590
01:37:25.288 --> 01:37:29.318
he could bring it down, someone stopped
him, saying, "Chief Kwenkesi is not here,

cue-1591
01:37:29.318 --> 01:37:30.298
and he must be present."

cue-1592
01:37:31.098 --> 01:37:35.957
More discussion followed. They then took
Matula on to Kwenkesi's place. The

cue-1593
01:37:35.958 --> 01:37:40.878
chief was surprised to see them so late,
for the sun had long since set. He

cue-1594
01:37:40.878 --> 01:37:44.318
welcomed them with a feast, though Matula
could barely eat.

cue-1595
01:37:45.588 --> 01:37:50.338
That night, they bound him inside a house.
He was laid on his back, arms and

cue-1596
01:37:50.338 --> 01:37:53.168
legs stretched out and tied to opposite
walls.

cue-1597
01:37:53.998 --> 01:37:57.978
Ropes around his waist were connected to
guards on either side, and the forked

cue-1598
01:37:57.978 --> 01:38:00.858
stick around his neck was fastened to the
low roof beam.

cue-1599
01:38:01.698 --> 01:38:06.458
In his misery, Matula prayed to God,
asking for help, for a quick death

cue-1600
01:38:06.458 --> 01:38:08.898
or for deliverance in some other way.

cue-1601
01:38:10.998 --> 01:38:12.548
It was a long and sleepless night,

cue-1602
01:38:13.238 --> 01:38:15.078
but at last, the dawn came.

cue-1603
01:38:15.798 --> 01:38:16.698
No help arrived,

cue-1604
01:38:17.338 --> 01:38:19.218
yet his faith in God did not waver.

cue-1605
01:38:20.178 --> 01:38:24.318
Soon, a messenger came from Makuta,
warning them that word had spread.

cue-1606
01:38:25.078 --> 01:38:27.798
If the state found out, there would be
consequences.

cue-1607
01:38:28.797 --> 01:38:32.678
Though they ignored the warning, they did
slightly loosen the bindings on his legs

cue-1608
01:38:32.678 --> 01:38:33.998
and relaxed the ropes a bit.

cue-1609
01:38:34.668 --> 01:38:39.218
Then they led him to the village where the
judgment or palaver was to take place.

cue-1610
01:38:39.878 --> 01:38:42.438
There, Matula begged the chief for a piece
of cloth.

cue-1611
01:38:43.438 --> 01:38:48.418
The chief, moved perhaps by a trace of
mercy, tore his own cloth in two

cue-1612
01:38:48.418 --> 01:38:49.378
and gave him half.

cue-1613
01:38:50.558 --> 01:38:54.858
Matula again pleaded with them, warning of
the evil they were committing and saying

cue-1614
01:38:54.858 --> 01:38:58.278
that if they killed him, they would face
punishment, if not now,

cue-1615
01:38:58.918 --> 01:38:59.738
then eventually.

cue-1616
01:39:00.618 --> 01:39:02.058
But his words had no effect.

cue-1617
01:39:03.138 --> 01:39:05.678
That night, they tied him again just as
before.

cue-1618
01:39:06.318 --> 01:39:08.478
In the morning, a large gathering was
held.

cue-1619
01:39:09.188 --> 01:39:13.518
The old accusations of witchcraft were
raised once more. He had associated with

cue-1620
01:39:13.518 --> 01:39:18.218
the missionary, given him a boy, and had
taken his people to Ngombe, where they

cue-1621
01:39:18.218 --> 01:39:21.038
were starting to follow God and this new
teaching.

cue-1622
01:39:22.058 --> 01:39:23.438
It was enough evidence, they said.

cue-1623
01:39:24.078 --> 01:39:27.538
He must be a witch, and witches, of
course, must be killed.

cue-1624
01:39:28.818 --> 01:39:31.258
The chief presiding over the council
called for a vote.

cue-1625
01:39:31.958 --> 01:39:33.738
Every vote was cast against Matula.

cue-1626
01:39:34.378 --> 01:39:37.978
They agreed to send for an executioner to
carry out the sentence the next day,

cue-1627
01:39:38.658 --> 01:39:43.357
and Matula's body was to be thrown into
the river Kwilu. Not a single voice, not

cue-1628
01:39:43.358 --> 01:39:45.698
even a faint one, spoke in his defense.

cue-1629
01:39:46.658 --> 01:39:50.218
That evening, some women noticed a
stranger in the woods preparing long

cue-1630
01:39:50.218 --> 01:39:55.038
cords, and they wondered at his actions.
He was the hired killer, getting

cue-1631
01:39:55.038 --> 01:39:59.338
ready to tie Matula securely for the night
to ensure he would not escape before

cue-1632
01:39:59.338 --> 01:40:02.618
morning. That night, Matula was bound
again,

cue-1633
01:40:03.228 --> 01:40:07.998
his feet tied to heavy iron clogs, his
arms fastened together beneath his head,

cue-1634
01:40:07.998 --> 01:40:12.758
the forked stick once more attached to the
low ridge pole, and his waist secured to

cue-1635
01:40:12.758 --> 01:40:17.738
guards on either side. He was surrounded
by six guards. To his left

cue-1636
01:40:17.738 --> 01:40:22.658
lay the murderer, well paid to carry out
the execution. To the native mind,

cue-1637
01:40:22.658 --> 01:40:26.898
everything had been done according to
custom. There was no chance of escape.

cue-1638
01:40:27.718 --> 01:40:32.558
Believing this to be the final night of
his life, Matula cried out to God, though

cue-1639
01:40:32.558 --> 01:40:33.338
with little hope.

cue-1640
01:40:34.078 --> 01:40:36.778
Unless a miracle happened, he would die in
the morning.

cue-1641
01:40:40.818 --> 01:40:41.518
Chapter Thirteen:

cue-1642
01:40:42.138 --> 01:40:42.518
Escape.

cue-1643
01:40:44.338 --> 01:40:49.018
In September 1897, I was traveling to
Tumba to visit Mr. and Mrs. Graham,

cue-1644
01:40:49.018 --> 01:40:52.578
who had come from San Salvador to
temporarily replace Mr. Popple.

cue-1645
01:40:53.478 --> 01:40:57.718
As we neared Tumba, we saw Matula's two
companions running toward us in great

cue-1646
01:40:57.718 --> 01:41:02.448
haste. Their faces showed alarm, and
before we could speak, they cried out,

cue-1647
01:41:02.448 --> 01:41:04.658
"Matula is murdered," with tears in their
eyes.

cue-1648
01:41:05.598 --> 01:41:07.038
"Surely not," I said.

cue-1649
01:41:07.978 --> 01:41:09.138
"There must be some mistake."

cue-1650
01:41:10.008 --> 01:41:14.298
"No, no," they insisted. "We saw him
beaten and stabbed with a knife. There is

cue-1651
01:41:14.298 --> 01:41:14.898
no mistake."

cue-1652
01:41:15.598 --> 01:41:19.158
"All right," I said. "Mr. Bentley has
returned. Go and tell him quickly."

cue-1653
01:41:20.058 --> 01:41:23.498
We needed to report to the state
authorities, for we were responsible for

cue-1654
01:41:23.498 --> 01:41:28.198
ensuring Matula would appear at Tumba if
summoned. The two men ran off without

cue-1655
01:41:28.198 --> 01:41:33.038
waiting to hear more, and we continued our
journey, heavy-hearted. None of the

cue-1656
01:41:33.038 --> 01:41:34.958
boys with us could speak a word.

cue-1657
01:41:35.618 --> 01:41:40.318
We had all grown to love Matula. His calm,
gentle spirit was so

cue-1658
01:41:40.318 --> 01:41:41.478
different from most others.

cue-1659
01:41:42.218 --> 01:41:45.178
When we arrived at Tumba, it was the first
thing we talked about.

cue-1660
01:41:45.788 --> 01:41:50.378
The two men had also spoken with Mr.
Graham. He and Mrs. Graham were as grieved

cue-1661
01:41:50.378 --> 01:41:51.018
as I was.

cue-1662
01:41:51.698 --> 01:41:55.478
Though they had only met Matula a few
times, they had been deeply impressed by

cue-1663
01:41:55.478 --> 01:41:55.638
him

cue-1664
01:41:56.278 --> 01:41:59.778
and surprised to learn he had not yet been
received into church fellowship.

cue-1665
01:42:01.178 --> 01:42:05.058
A day or two later, a letter arrived from
Mr. Bentley, addressed to the

cue-1666
01:42:05.058 --> 01:42:08.058
commissioner, and Mr. Graham was preparing
to deliver it.

cue-1667
01:42:08.838 --> 01:42:11.218
Just then, astonishing news came.

cue-1668
01:42:11.838 --> 01:42:16.298
Matula had escaped. We questioned the boy
who brought the report, but he had only

cue-1669
01:42:16.298 --> 01:42:18.678
heard it from some travelers coming from
the Makuta area.

cue-1670
01:42:19.338 --> 01:42:23.858
At first, we found it hard to believe. It
sounded too miraculous, especially in our

cue-1671
01:42:23.858 --> 01:42:26.858
skeptical times when people say the age of
miracles is over.

cue-1672
01:42:28.718 --> 01:42:33.458
Soon after, we met some of the men who had
tied Matula up, though we didn't realize

cue-1673
01:42:33.458 --> 01:42:36.638
it at the time, and Mr. Graham questioned
them closely.

cue-1674
01:42:37.298 --> 01:42:41.778
We still feared the escape story was a
cover-up for murder, but our doubts didn't

cue-1675
01:42:41.778 --> 01:42:42.538
last long.

cue-1676
01:42:43.358 --> 01:42:47.798
Within an hour or two, Ponde arrived. He
confirmed the news, saying he had seen

cue-1677
01:42:47.798 --> 01:42:51.598
Matula himself after he escaped and that
he had come straight to Makuta.

cue-1678
01:42:52.398 --> 01:42:56.878
Matula was too weak to travel far, so
Ponde had left him behind to rest.

cue-1679
01:42:57.698 --> 01:42:59.858
I had to leave that day with my small
caravan,

cue-1680
01:43:00.478 --> 01:43:05.418
but our hearts were overflowing with
gratitude to God for sparing Matula's life

cue-1681
01:43:05.418 --> 01:43:06.498
and showing his power.

cue-1682
01:43:07.618 --> 01:43:11.958
We spent another ten days on the road,
visiting villages in my district about 40

cue-1683
01:43:11.958 --> 01:43:15.038
miles east of Tumba, and then returned to
Ngombe.

cue-1684
01:43:15.918 --> 01:43:19.798
My colleagues were expecting Matula's
arrival at any moment, and many of his

cue-1685
01:43:19.798 --> 01:43:21.878
people had gone out to meet him at
Kimpete.

cue-1686
01:43:23.738 --> 01:43:25.278
A few days later, they returned,

cue-1687
01:43:26.178 --> 01:43:30.258
Matula leading them, accompanied by Mr.
and Mrs. Graham, who were visiting

cue-1688
01:43:30.258 --> 01:43:34.750
Ngombe.Poor man. He looked utterly
exhausted.

cue-1689
01:43:35.550 --> 01:43:39.330
He said he had delayed coming because he
was ashamed for us to see how thin he had

cue-1690
01:43:39.330 --> 01:43:39.630
become.

cue-1691
01:43:40.350 --> 01:43:44.150
His people were overcome with joy, and the
boys and girls at the station could not

cue-1692
01:43:44.150 --> 01:43:46.489
have been more thrilled if he had been a
white man.

cue-1693
01:43:47.290 --> 01:43:51.370
Later, he gave us a detailed account of
his capture and being dragged from town to

cue-1694
01:43:51.370 --> 01:43:56.370
town over two days and nights. The story
you've already read. That's where we

cue-1695
01:43:56.370 --> 01:43:57.550
left him on the third night,

cue-1696
01:43:58.170 --> 01:44:02.050
bound hand and foot, awaiting the morning
with no hope of rescue,

cue-1697
01:44:02.670 --> 01:44:04.069
sure that his death was near.

cue-1698
01:44:04.970 --> 01:44:08.990
With no help left on earth, Matula
committed himself to God's care.

cue-1699
01:44:09.750 --> 01:44:13.370
He prayed for deliverance if it was God's
will or else for restful sleep.

cue-1700
01:44:14.210 --> 01:44:19.030
All six guards had fallen asleep, and
Matula himself began to drift off

cue-1701
01:44:19.030 --> 01:44:21.610
until he woke with a strange feeling in
his feet.

cue-1702
01:44:22.350 --> 01:44:23.950
What was it? They were burning.

cue-1703
01:44:24.980 --> 01:44:29.300
Then he realized the truth. His feet had
been bound over the ashes of the fire from

cue-1704
01:44:29.300 --> 01:44:34.110
the night before. Fires in the Congo,
like the ancient Druid fires, are

cue-1705
01:44:34.110 --> 01:44:39.110
rarely fully extinguished. With a bit of
dry grass and a breeze, a flame can be

cue-1706
01:44:39.110 --> 01:44:40.590
rekindled at any time.

cue-1707
01:44:41.430 --> 01:44:46.090
Rope made from fibrous materials will
slowly smolder and eventually break.

cue-1708
01:44:46.090 --> 01:44:50.330
That's what happened to the cords binding
Matula's feet. They smoldered and burned

cue-1709
01:44:50.330 --> 01:44:50.610
through.

cue-1710
01:44:51.310 --> 01:44:52.370
What freedom he felt.

cue-1711
01:44:53.190 --> 01:44:57.690
Though his waist, hands, and neck were
still tied, the ability to move his feet

cue-1712
01:44:57.690 --> 01:44:58.730
gave him leverage.

cue-1713
01:44:59.470 --> 01:45:03.690
Slowly, he worked his hands forward. The
cord slipped off the forked stick.

cue-1714
01:45:04.430 --> 01:45:07.010
He brought his hands in front of him and
managed to free them.

cue-1715
01:45:07.790 --> 01:45:10.830
Still, he had to move carefully. His
guards were stirring.

cue-1716
01:45:11.550 --> 01:45:12.170
Were they awake?

cue-1717
01:45:12.870 --> 01:45:15.650
He tested them by calling out, asking to
be tied again.

cue-1718
01:45:16.470 --> 01:45:20.420
They made no reply. Whether they were
asleep or too afraid to move,

cue-1719
01:45:21.050 --> 01:45:21.690
he didn't know.

cue-1720
01:45:22.810 --> 01:45:25.570
Quietly, he wriggled out of the cords
around his waist.

cue-1721
01:45:26.270 --> 01:45:31.030
Now only the iron clogs on his feet
remained. He crept to the door and slipped

cue-1722
01:45:31.030 --> 01:45:32.950
outside into the cool night air.

cue-1723
01:45:33.670 --> 01:45:34.410
It was refreshing.

cue-1724
01:45:35.290 --> 01:45:39.890
Looking around for tools, he found a
hatchet and a large knife and used them to

cue-1725
01:45:39.890 --> 01:45:42.620
break free from the irons. Then he ran,

cue-1726
01:45:43.270 --> 01:45:48.270
any direction, just to get away from that
place. He tried to find the road to Tumba,

cue-1727
01:45:48.270 --> 01:45:52.310
but disoriented and unsure of his
location, he couldn't tell which way to

cue-1728
01:45:52.310 --> 01:45:52.470
go.

cue-1729
01:45:53.099 --> 01:45:57.950
He followed the first visible path, which
led to a cassava garden. Fires

cue-1730
01:45:57.950 --> 01:46:02.470
burned and voices could be heard. Natives
were out guarding the fields from

cue-1731
01:46:02.470 --> 01:46:02.970
elephants.

cue-1732
01:46:03.730 --> 01:46:05.770
He skirted the area to avoid being
spotted.

cue-1733
01:46:06.590 --> 01:46:11.450
Ahead, he came upon an elephant track and
saw a mother elephant with her calf. He

cue-1734
01:46:11.450 --> 01:46:13.330
knew he couldn't risk going that way.

cue-1735
01:46:13.970 --> 01:46:17.890
He quickly turned aside and found a narrow
path that led him to the Kwilu River.

cue-1736
01:46:18.670 --> 01:46:23.110
As he stood on the bank, he heard the
ominous sounds of crocodiles below. He

cue-1737
01:46:23.110 --> 01:46:25.450
remembered how many people had been killed
by them.

cue-1738
01:46:26.470 --> 01:46:27.650
Terrified, he turned back.

cue-1739
01:46:28.370 --> 01:46:28.950
What could he do?

cue-1740
01:46:29.550 --> 01:46:31.020
Returning meant recapture.

cue-1741
01:46:31.680 --> 01:46:34.610
Going along the elephant path meant facing
wild beasts.

cue-1742
01:46:35.250 --> 01:46:37.400
Entering the river meant risking the
crocodiles.

cue-1743
01:46:38.150 --> 01:46:40.330
Staying in place could bring a buffalo
attack.

cue-1744
01:46:41.030 --> 01:46:42.390
Every option seemed deadly.

cue-1745
01:46:43.050 --> 01:46:47.810
In desperation, Matula prayed earnestly,
asking God, who had just

cue-1746
01:46:47.810 --> 01:46:51.710
delivered him from his enemies, to now
guide his next step.

cue-1747
01:46:53.010 --> 01:46:54.710
As he prayed, peace came.

cue-1748
01:46:55.470 --> 01:46:56.610
He felt God's answer.

cue-1749
01:46:57.330 --> 01:47:00.690
It is better to fall into the hands of God
than into those of wicked men.

cue-1750
01:47:01.510 --> 01:47:05.430
Beasts obey their creator. They are less
dangerous than evil men.

cue-1751
01:47:06.630 --> 01:47:11.430
With renewed faith, he stepped into the
river and swam safely to the other side.

cue-1752
01:47:11.430 --> 01:47:12.550
The water revived him.

cue-1753
01:47:13.210 --> 01:47:16.270
He paused to wash away the clotted blood
that covered his body.

cue-1754
01:47:16.970 --> 01:47:21.670
As he did, an antelope and its young came
and looked at him, leaving and returning

cue-1755
01:47:21.730 --> 01:47:22.510
several times.

cue-1756
01:47:23.170 --> 01:47:27.370
It was as if God had sent this gentle
creature as a sign of peace and

cue-1757
01:47:27.370 --> 01:47:28.070
reassurance.

cue-1758
01:47:28.850 --> 01:47:30.470
He climbed up the far bank of the river.

cue-1759
01:47:31.170 --> 01:47:35.890
Now more aware of his surroundings, he
carefully continued on, avoiding every

cue-1760
01:47:35.890 --> 01:47:36.270
village.

cue-1761
01:47:37.050 --> 01:47:40.090
As dawn approached, he had to be even more
cautious.

cue-1762
01:47:40.890 --> 01:47:44.590
Whenever travelers came near, Matula would
hide in the tall grass.

cue-1763
01:47:45.490 --> 01:47:47.490
He asked several people the way to Makuta,

cue-1764
01:47:48.090 --> 01:47:52.270
but they were too frightened to answer
him. As the morning progressed, more

cue-1765
01:47:52.270 --> 01:47:55.490
travelers appeared, all heading to the
district's large market.

cue-1766
01:47:56.170 --> 01:47:58.910
Matula saw a group approaching and hid in
the woods.

cue-1767
01:47:59.570 --> 01:48:03.290
Peering through the branches, he
recognized two of Ponde's boys leading a

cue-1768
01:48:03.290 --> 01:48:07.770
goat. When he called to them, they were
startled, having heard he was dead.

cue-1769
01:48:08.670 --> 01:48:12.570
But they stopped and listened as he
explained and then told him Ponde was at

cue-1770
01:48:12.570 --> 01:48:12.830
home.

cue-1771
01:48:13.670 --> 01:48:17.830
Encouraged, Matula hurried to Makuta and
headed straight for the prayer house,

cue-1772
01:48:17.830 --> 01:48:21.770
expecting to find Ponde there. He opened
the door and called out,

cue-1773
01:48:21.770 --> 01:48:23.470
"Ponde.

cue-1774
01:48:25.270 --> 01:48:25.650
Friend.

cue-1775
01:48:26.410 --> 01:48:26.850
Ponde."

cue-1776
01:48:27.690 --> 01:48:31.650
But a small boy, terrified, rushed out,
crying, "Matula's ghost has come."

cue-1777
01:48:32.390 --> 01:48:34.010
Ponde came quickly to see for himself,

cue-1778
01:48:34.750 --> 01:48:39.010
and to his joy and amazement, there stood
Matula, alive.

cue-1779
01:48:39.930 --> 01:48:41.770
The two embraced out of sheer joy,

cue-1780
01:48:42.470 --> 01:48:44.490
something very uncommon among the Congo
people.

cue-1781
01:48:45.150 --> 01:48:48.869
Hot water and medicine were quickly
brought, and his many wounds were washed

cue-1782
01:48:48.870 --> 01:48:49.450
and dressed.

cue-1783
01:48:50.050 --> 01:48:50.230
Then,

cue-1784
01:48:50.930 --> 01:48:55.850
relieved and safe with a friend, Matula
lay down on a mat and soon fell

cue-1785
01:48:55.850 --> 01:48:57.770
into a deep, peaceful sleep.

cue-1786
01:48:58.990 --> 01:49:03.790
He remained indoors for several days,
lovingly cared for by Ponde as tenderly as

cue-1787
01:49:03.790 --> 01:49:05.650
a mother would nurse her own child.

cue-1788
01:49:06.550 --> 01:49:09.030
Word soon spread that Matula had escaped,

cue-1789
01:49:10.030 --> 01:49:13.010
but his pursuers were too afraid to try
capturing him again.

cue-1790
01:49:13.710 --> 01:49:17.130
They assumed the state would finish the
job they had failed to carry out.

cue-1791
01:49:18.110 --> 01:49:22.890
Matula also anticipated the upcoming
trial, but this time with more hope and

cue-1792
01:49:22.890 --> 01:49:27.370
confidence, for he had experienced a clear
sign of God's power and protection.

cue-1793
01:49:31.490 --> 01:49:36.434
Chapter 14: Trial at TumbaNot long after
Matula

cue-1794
01:49:36.434 --> 01:49:41.403
returned to Ngombe, Mr. Graham wrote to
Mr. Cameron, Mr. Bentley having gone back

cue-1795
01:49:41.403 --> 01:49:46.334
to England, asking that Matula be sent to
Tumba to appear before the judge, expected

cue-1796
01:49:46.334 --> 01:49:47.574
in three or four days.

cue-1797
01:49:48.234 --> 01:49:52.994
In his letter, Mr. Graham also requested
earnest prayer for Matula. His

cue-1798
01:49:52.994 --> 01:49:57.334
enemies had carefully prepared their
accusations, while Matula, because of the

cue-1799
01:49:57.334 --> 01:49:59.684
nature of the charges, had no witnesses,

cue-1800
01:50:00.374 --> 01:50:03.104
only those who could testify to his gentle
character.

cue-1801
01:50:03.884 --> 01:50:07.694
The commissioner said the case looked bad,
and unless Matula could prove his

cue-1802
01:50:07.694 --> 01:50:10.714
innocence, he would certainly be hanged as
a warning to others.

cue-1803
01:50:11.634 --> 01:50:15.714
Still, Matula went fearlessly to Tumba,
confident in his innocence.

cue-1804
01:50:16.514 --> 01:50:19.734
Though he saw no path forward, he trusted
God was with him.

cue-1805
01:50:20.974 --> 01:50:25.814
At Ngombe, we lifted him up daily in
prayer, asking our wise and loving Father

cue-1806
01:50:25.814 --> 01:50:26.854
to defend the innocent,

cue-1807
01:50:27.494 --> 01:50:32.174
for we were convinced Matula was indeed
innocent. When Matula arrived at

cue-1808
01:50:32.174 --> 01:50:36.234
Tumba, he was shocked to find some of his
former accusers in chains.

cue-1809
01:50:37.024 --> 01:50:40.553
The government had learned about their
attempt to murder him and had sent a

cue-1810
01:50:40.553 --> 01:50:42.614
sergeant and soldiers to arrest them.

cue-1811
01:50:43.474 --> 01:50:47.114
The troops arrived in Mongo just as the
people were gathering for the burial of

cue-1812
01:50:47.114 --> 01:50:50.334
the chief's mother, who had remained
unburied for months.

cue-1813
01:50:51.054 --> 01:50:55.394
Several pigs had been slaughtered for the
occasion and many cloths collected. The

cue-1814
01:50:55.394 --> 01:50:59.734
soldiers seized these and took the accused
men to Tumba. Even in custody, they

cue-1815
01:50:59.734 --> 01:51:04.014
repeated the same accusation against
Matula, claiming they had only tied him up

cue-1816
01:51:04.014 --> 01:51:05.734
to ensure his appearance in court.

cue-1817
01:51:06.374 --> 01:51:07.684
In truth, they were terrified,

cue-1818
01:51:08.354 --> 01:51:11.294
especially since Matula had warned them
that punishment would come.

cue-1819
01:51:13.134 --> 01:51:17.234
The details of what followed in Tumba were
best told by Meister Graham of San

cue-1820
01:51:17.234 --> 01:51:21.454
Salvador, who witnessed the trial
firsthand. He explained that the delay in

cue-1821
01:51:21.454 --> 01:51:26.294
Matula's trial had been so long it seemed
the government had forgotten the case,

cue-1822
01:51:26.294 --> 01:51:28.774
likely due to illness and changes in
judges.

cue-1823
01:51:29.494 --> 01:51:33.174
The arrest of Matula's would-be murderer
may have revived interest in the matter.

cue-1824
01:51:33.854 --> 01:51:37.534
Soon afterward, Mr. Graham was notified
that the trial would be held on December

cue-1825
01:51:37.534 --> 01:51:37.874
ninth.

cue-1826
01:51:38.474 --> 01:51:41.734
Matula was brought to Tumba on December
eighth to await the hearing.

cue-1827
01:51:42.434 --> 01:51:46.634
But the judge failed to arrive. Again,
they were told the judge was coming, and

cue-1828
01:51:46.634 --> 01:51:48.564
again they brought Matula and his
witnesses,

cue-1829
01:51:49.214 --> 01:51:53.574
but the judge was sick, and the case was
postponed a second time on December

cue-1830
01:51:53.574 --> 01:51:54.114
sixteenth.

cue-1831
01:51:55.394 --> 01:51:59.574
On the following day, December
seventeenth, Mr. Graham wrote to the judge

cue-1832
01:51:59.574 --> 01:52:03.874
explaining that they had twice
transported Matula and his witnesses only

cue-1833
01:52:03.874 --> 01:52:08.554
to return again and asking who would be
appointed as Matula's defense and when

cue-1834
01:52:08.554 --> 01:52:13.554
they should come back once more. On
Sunday, December nineteenth, I received a

cue-1835
01:52:13.554 --> 01:52:17.864
wire from the judge stating that Monsieur
L had been appointed Matula's defender and

cue-1836
01:52:17.864 --> 01:52:19.624
the trial would take place on Thursday.

cue-1837
01:52:20.534 --> 01:52:25.054
On Monday, I met with M. L and explained
the entire case to him. Then I reviewed

cue-1838
01:52:25.054 --> 01:52:28.294
the notes from the earlier trial and
discovered that the translator had

cue-1839
01:52:28.294 --> 01:52:30.414
completely misrepresented the facts.

cue-1840
01:52:31.294 --> 01:52:35.054
After reading the supposed evidence
presented to the judge, M. L believed that

cue-1841
01:52:35.054 --> 01:52:37.394
guilty or not, Matula would be hanged.

cue-1842
01:52:38.054 --> 01:52:41.754
I too feared that unless the Lord
intervened, this would end in judicial

cue-1843
01:52:41.754 --> 01:52:42.054
murder.

cue-1844
01:52:42.874 --> 01:52:45.874
Needless to say, I slept little until the
trial concluded.

cue-1845
01:52:46.774 --> 01:52:51.634
That same day, by what seemed divine
providence, I found two witnesses who had

cue-1846
01:52:51.634 --> 01:52:55.274
been with Matula at another location
during the time of the alleged murder.

cue-1847
01:52:56.274 --> 01:52:58.443
I almost forced them to stay and testify

cue-1848
01:52:59.134 --> 01:53:01.214
in case the key witnesses failed to
arrive,

cue-1849
01:53:01.984 --> 01:53:02.794
and it was well I did.

cue-1850
01:53:03.994 --> 01:53:07.734
Meanwhile, we interviewed every possible
witness and sent for others.

cue-1851
01:53:08.434 --> 01:53:11.374
The most crucial of these was a woman who
had cared for her sister,

cue-1852
01:53:12.074 --> 01:53:17.054
one of the two women Matula was accused of
killing. Both had died of smallpox, and

cue-1853
01:53:17.054 --> 01:53:19.503
this had occurred years before the
supposed attack.

cue-1854
01:53:20.434 --> 01:53:24.634
On Wednesday afternoon, the judge and the
prosecuting attorney arrived from Matadi

cue-1855
01:53:24.634 --> 01:53:25.174
by train.

cue-1856
01:53:25.874 --> 01:53:30.554
Unfortunately, the most vital witnesses
were delayed by a storm and didn't arrive

cue-1857
01:53:30.554 --> 01:53:32.874
until after the trial had ended the next
day.

cue-1858
01:53:33.694 --> 01:53:36.874
Then came the morning on which Matula's
fate was to be decided.

cue-1859
01:53:37.674 --> 01:53:42.194
By mid-morning, people had gathered
outside the plain-looking grass building

cue-1860
01:53:42.194 --> 01:53:45.394
marked with the grand title, Tumba Palais
de Justice.

cue-1861
01:53:46.454 --> 01:53:51.214
Soon, the judge, prosecuting attorney,
clerk, defense counsel, interpreter,

cue-1862
01:53:51.214 --> 01:53:56.153
prisoner, soldiers, witnesses, and Mr.
Graham were seen arriving from different

cue-1863
01:53:56.154 --> 01:54:00.974
directions and filing into the courtroom.
Mr. Graham brought up the

cue-1864
01:54:00.974 --> 01:54:05.094
rear, carefully scanning the area to see
if any expected witnesses had arrived.

cue-1865
01:54:05.794 --> 01:54:08.114
Guards took their positions outside the
door.

cue-1866
01:54:08.754 --> 01:54:13.213
The natives stood in silent awe at the
solemn formality with which the judge and

cue-1867
01:54:13.214 --> 01:54:16.604
counsel took their seats and prepared for
the day's proceedings.

cue-1868
01:54:17.634 --> 01:54:21.954
Everything at the Tumba trial was carried
out as far as possible with the formality

cue-1869
01:54:21.954 --> 01:54:26.814
and dignity of a European court, much like
it would be in Brussels. The

cue-1870
01:54:26.814 --> 01:54:31.814
contrast with native justice was extreme.
In traditional native courts, proceedings

cue-1871
01:54:31.814 --> 01:54:33.534
are typically held in the open air.

cue-1872
01:54:34.314 --> 01:54:38.294
The highest-ranking chief sits on the
ground atop a leopard skin, sometimes

cue-1873
01:54:38.294 --> 01:54:39.094
draped in a cloth,

cue-1874
01:54:39.734 --> 01:54:41.494
holding a spear or having it nearby.

cue-1875
01:54:42.394 --> 01:54:46.994
Other chiefs sit squatting around him, all
trying to look as important as possible.

cue-1876
01:54:46.994 --> 01:54:50.254
Such native trials often begin with
offerings of malavu,

cue-1877
01:54:51.004 --> 01:54:55.574
palm wine, and heavy bribes, and cases are
frequently postponed due to

cue-1878
01:54:55.574 --> 01:54:59.274
confusion, argument, and chaos between the
parties involved.

cue-1879
01:55:00.094 --> 01:55:04.574
So imagine the awe of those used to that
system when they entered a formal

cue-1880
01:55:04.574 --> 01:55:09.414
courtroom. State officials in dark robes
and white collars, solemn-faced,

cue-1881
01:55:09.414 --> 01:55:11.324
questioning and cross-questioning.

cue-1882
01:55:12.064 --> 01:55:16.884
It's no wonder native witnesses quaked,
stumbled, and gave confused answers,

cue-1883
01:55:17.594 --> 01:55:21.914
just as some had during Matula's earlier
hearing. Returning to Mr. Graham's

cue-1884
01:55:21.914 --> 01:55:26.334
account, he explained that he attended the
trial only as a visitor, though in

cue-1885
01:55:26.334 --> 01:55:31.314
practice he served as an informal legal
advisor to Monsieur L, Matula's appointed

cue-1886
01:55:31.314 --> 01:55:31.794
defender.

cue-1887
01:55:32.954 --> 01:55:35.534
A major setback was the absence of key
witnesses.

cue-1888
01:55:36.214 --> 01:55:40.774
However, witnesses from the opposing side
also failed to appear, balancing things

cue-1889
01:55:40.774 --> 01:55:45.770
somewhat.Mr. Graham had emphasized several
key points to Monsieur L

cue-1890
01:55:45.770 --> 01:55:46.750
in Matula's defense.

cue-1891
01:55:47.830 --> 01:55:52.820
A woman from Matente, not Matembe, no such
place exists, had been captured

cue-1892
01:55:52.820 --> 01:55:57.590
years earlier by Yalala, a friend of
Matula's family, in revenge for Matente

cue-1893
01:55:57.590 --> 01:56:02.090
capturing his son. This woman, Kinziona,
was sold to Kuba of

cue-1894
01:56:02.090 --> 01:56:06.970
Kwilu and later died there of smallpox
along with another woman. The sister of

cue-1895
01:56:06.970 --> 01:56:11.630
one of the women had nursed them both to
the end. This caregiver and others who

cue-1896
01:56:11.630 --> 01:56:14.000
knew the case were on their way to
testify.

cue-1897
01:56:14.900 --> 01:56:19.550
This incident, including the capture and
death of Kinziona, clearly occurred long

cue-1898
01:56:19.550 --> 01:56:24.450
before late 1896, before the Congo Railway
arrived and before the state's

cue-1899
01:56:24.450 --> 01:56:25.830
law extended over the area.

cue-1900
01:56:26.500 --> 01:56:30.810
Therefore, any actions involved were part
of a native conflict and could not be

cue-1901
01:56:30.810 --> 01:56:33.410
judged under laws that had not yet been
established.

cue-1902
01:56:34.290 --> 01:56:38.110
As for Matula, he was well known to
Reverend W.H. Bentley and other

cue-1903
01:56:38.110 --> 01:56:41.070
missionaries, both before and after the
supposed murder.

cue-1904
01:56:41.790 --> 01:56:44.380
All gave a strong testimony of his good
character.

cue-1905
01:56:45.110 --> 01:56:48.930
Moreover, despite their knowledge of the
region, none of the missionaries had heard

cue-1906
01:56:48.930 --> 01:56:52.330
any rumor or report of such a murder
around the time in question.

cue-1907
01:56:53.140 --> 01:56:57.910
Matula firmly denied ever visiting Matente
and denied ever killing

cue-1908
01:56:57.910 --> 01:57:01.480
anyone or striking any woman as the
charges claimed.

cue-1909
01:57:02.790 --> 01:57:06.750
The clearest evidence showed he had no
part in the quarrel during which Kinziona

cue-1910
01:57:06.750 --> 01:57:08.410
was captured by Yalala's group.

cue-1911
01:57:09.290 --> 01:57:13.430
At that time, Matula had been away trading
in another area and only heard of the

cue-1912
01:57:13.430 --> 01:57:14.790
conflict upon his return.

cue-1913
01:57:15.610 --> 01:57:16.930
Two witnesses confirmed this.

cue-1914
01:57:17.550 --> 01:57:21.329
A man who gave evidence against Matula
under the name Weo, better known as

cue-1915
01:57:21.330 --> 01:57:26.070
Kwenkezi, was not Weo at all, but Masamba,
either his son or slave,

cue-1916
01:57:26.070 --> 01:57:28.010
who falsely claimed to be Weo.

cue-1917
01:57:28.670 --> 01:57:33.300
The real Weo, afraid his lie would be
exposed, did not appear at the trial.

cue-1918
01:57:33.910 --> 01:57:38.790
In contrast, Matula, though he could
easily have avoided trial, chose to appear

cue-1919
01:57:38.790 --> 01:57:43.790
three separate times, each with great
inconvenience to himself and his family.

cue-1920
01:57:44.630 --> 01:57:49.270
Moreover, Mafuku, Weo's nephew and heir,
along with others, had recently

cue-1921
01:57:49.270 --> 01:57:50.790
attempted to murder Matula.

cue-1922
01:57:51.409 --> 01:57:53.870
Mafuku was now in prison on that charge.

cue-1923
01:57:54.550 --> 01:57:58.950
Clearly, it was not Matula, but his
enemies who had broken the law and acted

cue-1924
01:57:58.950 --> 01:57:59.850
against the state.

cue-1925
01:58:00.750 --> 01:58:04.540
Matula's defense counsel took these facts
and presented a powerful speech.

cue-1926
01:58:05.190 --> 01:58:09.510
He convinced both the judge and the
prosecuting attorney so thoroughly that

cue-1927
01:58:09.510 --> 01:58:11.660
they chose to hear Matula's own testimony.

cue-1928
01:58:12.530 --> 01:58:15.430
Matula spoke with clarity, calm, and
integrity.

cue-1929
01:58:16.130 --> 01:58:20.550
In his closing remarks, the judge stated
that there had been much false testimony

cue-1930
01:58:20.550 --> 01:58:25.130
against the accused and rejoiced that the
weight of evidence clearly supported

cue-1931
01:58:25.130 --> 01:58:30.050
Matula's innocence. He then dismissed the
case and declared Matula free with a clean

cue-1932
01:58:30.050 --> 01:58:30.510
record.

cue-1933
01:58:31.270 --> 01:58:35.290
Upon leaving the courtroom, Mr. Graham and
the others met the delayed witnesses,

cue-1934
01:58:35.930 --> 01:58:37.030
too late to testify.

cue-1935
01:58:37.850 --> 01:58:42.370
The prosecuting attorney sternly rebuked
Masamba and Diamoni, Weo's wife.

cue-1936
01:58:42.370 --> 01:58:47.030
And when his knowledge of the language
failed, Mr. Graham took over. They both

cue-1937
01:58:47.030 --> 01:58:51.330
made sure the false witnesses understood
the gravity of their actions, and they

cue-1938
01:58:51.330 --> 01:58:55.590
likely won't risk perjury again. When
Matula reunited with his friends, who

cue-1939
01:58:55.590 --> 01:58:59.430
arrived in style as if they owned the
street, he told them.

cue-1940
01:58:59.430 --> 01:59:04.430
Yes, I am free, but no thanks to you. If I
had trusted in you instead

cue-1941
01:59:04.430 --> 01:59:09.170
-of God, I might have been hanged.
-The trial for Mafuku and the others who

cue-1942
01:59:09.170 --> 01:59:13.750
had tried to kill Matula was brief. They
had been imprisoned for months, and Matula

cue-1943
01:59:13.750 --> 01:59:18.670
did not want harsh punishment. After a
stern warning and being bound over to

cue-1944
01:59:18.670 --> 01:59:23.410
keep the peace, they were released. Once
everything was settled at Tumba, Matula

cue-1945
01:59:23.410 --> 01:59:25.090
wasted no time returning home.

cue-1946
01:59:25.910 --> 01:59:30.870
That day of his return to the station was
unforgettable. As word spread, crowds

cue-1947
01:59:30.870 --> 01:59:35.449
rushed out to meet him. Guns were fired in
celebration, and the people danced with

cue-1948
01:59:35.450 --> 01:59:35.750
joy.

cue-1949
01:59:36.470 --> 01:59:38.890
At the Thanksgiving service, emotion ran
high.

cue-1950
01:59:39.570 --> 01:59:44.370
Tears of joy filled many eyes as everyone
recognized that God had truly

cue-1951
01:59:44.370 --> 01:59:45.870
heard and answered prayer.

cue-1952
01:59:46.810 --> 01:59:51.110
Matula has often returned to his old town,
sincerely wanting to show his relatives

cue-1953
01:59:51.110 --> 01:59:52.670
that he had truly forgiven them.

cue-1954
01:59:53.360 --> 01:59:56.730
His trials had shaped him into a man full
of love and gentleness.

cue-1955
01:59:57.350 --> 02:00:02.280
He became known as a true gentleman, one
of the most genuine and sincere men in

cue-1956
02:00:02.280 --> 02:00:03.090
all Congo.

cue-1957
02:00:03.970 --> 02:00:05.310
Mr. Pinnock once said of him,

cue-1958
02:00:05.980 --> 02:00:10.150
"He is the only one-eyed fellow I know in
Congo," meaning he lived with a single

cue-1959
02:00:10.150 --> 02:00:12.850
focus to glorify God in all things.

cue-1960
02:00:16.730 --> 02:00:18.870
Chapter 15: Days of Peace.

cue-1961
02:00:20.590 --> 02:00:25.530
In 1899, Matula was received into church
fellowship. His life was

cue-1962
02:00:25.530 --> 02:00:29.950
above reproach, and his simple, unwavering
faith in the Lord Jesus made it

cue-1963
02:00:29.950 --> 02:00:32.290
impossible to withhold communion from him.

cue-1964
02:00:33.170 --> 02:00:37.290
Because the African people are so
impressionable, leaders must be cautious

cue-1965
02:00:37.290 --> 02:00:39.570
about publicly recognizing new disciples.

cue-1966
02:00:40.350 --> 02:00:45.070
But Matula had already passed through a
long season of trial and suffering and had

cue-1967
02:00:45.070 --> 02:00:49.550
remained faithful, even to the brink of
death, for the sake of Christ.

cue-1968
02:00:50.330 --> 02:00:54.749
Not long after his baptism, his remaining
wife, Kento, was also baptized after

cue-1969
02:00:54.750 --> 02:00:56.410
professing her faith in Christ.

cue-1970
02:00:57.110 --> 02:01:01.470
She had been a faithful support to him in
all his hardships, and through it all, her

cue-1971
02:01:01.470 --> 02:01:02.750
faith had never wavered.

cue-1972
02:01:03.410 --> 02:01:08.350
She was his first wife, married in 1889
when she was about sixteen years old.

cue-1973
02:01:08.990 --> 02:01:13.710
According to native custom, he had taken
two other wives but never felt deeply

cue-1974
02:01:13.710 --> 02:01:14.650
attached to them.

cue-1975
02:01:15.450 --> 02:01:19.890
One abandoned him during the persecution.
The other died shortly after they arrived

cue-1976
02:01:19.890 --> 02:01:24.790
at Ngombe. She had been happy with Matula,
for even by native standards, he had

cue-1977
02:01:24.790 --> 02:01:27.130
always been a kind and considerate
husband.

cue-1978
02:01:27.910 --> 02:01:32.369
Yet one cannot help feeling her passing
was merciful, for the heart of a man

cue-1979
02:01:32.370 --> 02:01:34.230
always cleaves to his first love.

cue-1980
02:01:35.730 --> 02:01:39.850
For years, they had passed through
troubled waters, often close to despair.

cue-1981
02:01:40.750 --> 02:01:45.710
But now the Lord had brought them into a
peaceful harbor.Every visitor

cue-1982
02:01:45.710 --> 02:01:46.730
to their home felt it,

cue-1983
02:01:47.410 --> 02:01:49.170
peace and quietness.

cue-1984
02:01:50.030 --> 02:01:55.010
Their neat houses, tidy fences, clean
paths, and well-kept gardens all

cue-1985
02:01:55.010 --> 02:01:57.590
reflected a home where it was a joy to
live.

cue-1986
02:01:58.730 --> 02:02:03.250
In the mornings, the sound of the pestle
pounding dried cassava into flour, the

cue-1987
02:02:03.250 --> 02:02:07.690
clucking of hens, and the bleating of
goats spoke of a rare industriousness

cue-1988
02:02:07.690 --> 02:02:09.130
worth noting in the Congo.

cue-1989
02:02:09.870 --> 02:02:14.150
And in the evening, in a culture where men
often feel ashamed to even acknowledge

cue-1990
02:02:14.150 --> 02:02:19.070
their wives in public, this warm,
contented couple could be seen walking

cue-1991
02:02:19.070 --> 02:02:23.590
together around Vianga, Vianga or entering
the missionary's house side by side.

cue-1992
02:02:24.330 --> 02:02:29.070
Wherever we met them, there was always a
cheerful smile, a kind greeting, and a

cue-1993
02:02:29.070 --> 02:02:31.670
native courtesy that was a delight to
witness.

cue-1994
02:02:32.630 --> 02:02:35.759
I often wondered if they had some noble
blood in their veins,

cue-1995
02:02:36.370 --> 02:02:40.230
for their expressions and behavior were so
unlike the average Congolese.

cue-1996
02:02:41.270 --> 02:02:45.810
In Lower Congo, there are indeed a number
of natives with refined manners, graceful

cue-1997
02:02:45.810 --> 02:02:50.250
movements, and delicate features, making
one wonder if they are descendants of a

cue-1998
02:02:50.250 --> 02:02:51.710
nobler lineage than most.

cue-1999
02:02:52.430 --> 02:02:54.900
But that, of course, remains speculation.

cue-2000
02:02:56.120 --> 02:03:00.600
Matula was richly blessed after coming to
live among the believers at Ngombe. He and

cue-2001
02:03:00.600 --> 02:03:04.810
his wife attended school faithfully and
soon learned to read and write quite well.

cue-2002
02:03:05.650 --> 02:03:08.570
Matula found great comfort in reading his
Ekangu Diampha

cue-2003
02:03:09.270 --> 02:03:13.690
Bible and had the joy of seeing more than
twelve members of his household received

cue-2004
02:03:13.690 --> 02:03:14.750
into church fellowship.

cue-2005
02:03:15.470 --> 02:03:18.610
Two of his sisters married native
evangelists and were blessed with

cue-2006
02:03:18.610 --> 02:03:18.990
children.

cue-2007
02:03:19.830 --> 02:03:24.080
One particular joy and weight of
responsibility was their only surviving

cue-2008
02:03:24.080 --> 02:03:26.690
child, a bright ten-year-old girl.

cue-2009
02:03:27.510 --> 02:03:32.070
Matula also had a son, but it was this
little girl who was their constant

cue-2010
02:03:32.070 --> 02:03:33.350
delight and concern.

cue-2011
02:03:34.390 --> 02:03:38.610
Above all, Matula rejoiced most in the
great transformation that came over his

cue-2012
02:03:38.610 --> 02:03:39.650
home village of Mongo.

cue-2013
02:03:40.430 --> 02:03:44.980
In early eighteen ninety-nine, Mr. Cameron
visited the district and, to his

cue-2014
02:03:44.980 --> 02:03:49.930
surprise and joy, found the people asking
for a teacher to show them the way to God.

cue-2015
02:03:50.610 --> 02:03:55.350
The old chief had died and was succeeded
by a young man named Lunenga, who was

cue-2016
02:03:55.350 --> 02:04:00.050
eager to learn and follow God, just as the
people of Makuta had done for years.

cue-2017
02:04:00.970 --> 02:04:04.910
Lunenga had not been present during
Matula's persecution, but when he heard

cue-2018
02:04:04.910 --> 02:04:06.980
about it, he was deeply ashamed.

cue-2019
02:04:07.710 --> 02:04:10.850
From then on, he became one of Matula's
truest friends.

cue-2020
02:04:11.590 --> 02:04:16.330
A capable and earnest teacher was sent to
Mongo, and soon a prayer house was built

cue-2021
02:04:16.330 --> 02:04:17.310
and later expanded.

cue-2022
02:04:18.010 --> 02:04:22.930
Around sixty to seventy students attended
regularly, and Lunenga himself, along with

cue-2023
02:04:22.930 --> 02:04:24.690
several others, was baptized.

cue-2024
02:04:25.410 --> 02:04:29.750
In nineteen hundred, Lunenga accompanied
the missionary to a neighboring town where

cue-2025
02:04:29.750 --> 02:04:32.110
he had lived during Matula's time of
suffering.

cue-2026
02:04:33.230 --> 02:04:37.390
Because of his earlier heartfelt appeals
and strong witness for the truth, the

cue-2027
02:04:37.390 --> 02:04:40.030
people there were now eager to receive a
teacher as well.

cue-2028
02:04:40.750 --> 02:04:45.029
A young man was left to teach them, and
the people enthusiastically built a fine

cue-2029
02:04:45.030 --> 02:04:48.190
house of worship, which was soon filled
for daily prayers.

cue-2030
02:04:49.070 --> 02:04:53.110
Nearly seventy students enrolled in the
school, and many began to seek God

cue-2031
02:04:53.110 --> 02:04:53.650
earnestly.

cue-2032
02:04:54.330 --> 02:04:58.610
From both Mongo and this new town,
Kinsende, there is hope that the spiritual

cue-2033
02:04:58.610 --> 02:05:00.710
fire will spread to many more towns,

cue-2034
02:05:01.510 --> 02:05:06.110
fires kindled by the flames of persecution
once directed at the innocent and

cue-2035
02:05:06.110 --> 02:05:06.970
faithful Matula.

cue-2036
02:05:11.530 --> 02:05:13.910
Chapter sixteen: Signs of Coming Trouble.

cue-2037
02:05:16.250 --> 02:05:20.650
In nineteen hundred, many were sick with
chest and throat infections, and Matula

cue-2038
02:05:20.650 --> 02:05:21.249
was among them.

cue-2039
02:05:21.970 --> 02:05:26.630
One night, I was woken by Nlemvo, who told
me Matula was very ill and feared he

cue-2040
02:05:26.630 --> 02:05:27.570
might be dying.

cue-2041
02:05:28.330 --> 02:05:29.950
I quickly dressed and went to his home.

cue-2042
02:05:30.570 --> 02:05:32.250
The room was quiet when I arrived.

cue-2043
02:05:32.910 --> 02:05:37.590
Matula was breathing fast, and his face
looked anxious and troubled. At first, I

cue-2044
02:05:37.590 --> 02:05:38.670
thought he was near death.

cue-2045
02:05:39.430 --> 02:05:44.230
As we stood watching, to our surprise, he
began singing softly. "Follow, follow,

cue-2046
02:05:44.230 --> 02:05:45.450
I will follow Jesus."

cue-2047
02:05:46.170 --> 02:05:47.540
Then confused, he murmured,

cue-2048
02:05:48.170 --> 02:05:50.870
"Oh, kill me now. Kill me now with a gun.

cue-2049
02:05:51.530 --> 02:05:54.310
I want to be free. The angels are waiting
for me."

cue-2050
02:05:55.310 --> 02:05:57.410
It seemed he was reliving his past
suffering.

cue-2051
02:05:58.230 --> 02:06:03.030
Later, he awoke and gently told his wife,
who hadn't slept in two nights, not to

cue-2052
02:06:03.030 --> 02:06:04.830
cry, but to try to rest.

cue-2053
02:06:05.520 --> 02:06:06.430
"Don't cry.

cue-2054
02:06:07.250 --> 02:06:07.940
If I die,

cue-2055
02:06:08.650 --> 02:06:11.330
I am going to heaven, and you will soon
follow me."

cue-2056
02:06:12.110 --> 02:06:17.030
Then turning to others nearby, he said,
"If I go, your father will be gone,

cue-2057
02:06:17.030 --> 02:06:18.030
but don't weep for me.

cue-2058
02:06:18.850 --> 02:06:20.470
Stay here and continue your work.

cue-2059
02:06:21.110 --> 02:06:25.230
You young women only marry Christians and
go where they go."

cue-2060
02:06:27.050 --> 02:06:28.180
His words came slowly.

cue-2061
02:06:28.830 --> 02:06:29.730
He was very weak.

cue-2062
02:06:30.390 --> 02:06:33.490
His cough was severe, and at times he
seemed like he would choke.

cue-2063
02:06:34.330 --> 02:06:39.190
I stayed at his bedside for two hours,
giving him soothing medicine, but I truly

cue-2064
02:06:39.190 --> 02:06:43.930
didn't think he would recover. He remained
in this condition for two or three days.

cue-2065
02:06:43.930 --> 02:06:48.270
We fought hard, and by God's grace, he
pulled through, though I always sensed he

cue-2066
02:06:48.270 --> 02:06:51.110
was disappointed as he had wanted to go
home to God.

cue-2067
02:06:51.830 --> 02:06:54.910
His recovery was slow and took nearly six
weeks.

cue-2068
02:06:55.790 --> 02:06:59.970
Even after that, he never regained his old
strength, and I began to worry that he

cue-2069
02:06:59.970 --> 02:07:01.590
wouldn't be with us much longer.

cue-2070
02:07:02.290 --> 02:07:06.310
Some of those who came with him had
returned to Mongo after the teacher left,

cue-2071
02:07:06.310 --> 02:07:09.790
while others were taken by the dreadful
disease, sleeping sickness.

cue-2072
02:07:10.770 --> 02:07:12.930
Before Matula became ill, Mankwenia,

cue-2073
02:07:13.670 --> 02:07:16.820
the boy he had first given to Mr. Bentley,
died from it,

cue-2074
02:07:17.490 --> 02:07:21.010
and the two companions who had traveled
with him on that unforgettable journey

cue-2075
02:07:21.010 --> 02:07:22.330
also became victims.

cue-2076
02:07:23.150 --> 02:07:26.050
His mother had died not long after his
return from Tumba.

cue-2077
02:07:26.670 --> 02:07:28.330
These losses weighed heavily on him.

cue-2078
02:07:29.210 --> 02:07:32.550
Sleeping sickness is a terrible,
heartbreaking disease.

cue-2079
02:07:33.450 --> 02:07:38.030
Thousands die from it every year in Congo.
It is sweeping through the land at a

cue-2080
02:07:38.030 --> 02:07:41.380
frightening pace, and yet no one knows how
to stop it.

cue-2081
02:07:42.680 --> 02:07:46.030
The illness has been studied in medical
journals and in London hospitals,

cue-2082
02:07:46.790 --> 02:07:48.460
but no solution has been found.

cue-2083
02:07:49.250 --> 02:07:53.190
It is heartbreaking to hear of faithful
Christian believers suddenly being struck

cue-2084
02:07:53.190 --> 02:07:58.140
down by it.The thought that Matula might
now have it is too painful. Oh,

cue-2085
02:07:58.140 --> 02:08:02.320
that someone skilled and compassionate
would hear the cry of these suffering

cue-2086
02:08:02.320 --> 02:08:03.740
people and come to help.

cue-2087
02:08:04.670 --> 02:08:09.540
Even if such a mission brought little
fame, the reward would be immense. To

cue-2088
02:08:09.540 --> 02:08:14.130
discover the cause of these countless
deaths and to stop this dreadful disease

cue-2089
02:08:14.130 --> 02:08:19.040
would be a work worthy of the brightest
minds. But this must be studied among the

cue-2090
02:08:19.040 --> 02:08:22.460
victims themselves, where the disease is
doing its damage.

cue-2091
02:08:24.120 --> 02:08:29.000
One Sunday, Matula came to me wrapped in
an old blanket, looking weak and unlike

cue-2092
02:08:29.000 --> 02:08:29.460
himself.

cue-2093
02:08:30.660 --> 02:08:31.160
'What's wrong?'

cue-2094
02:08:31.880 --> 02:08:32.240
I asked.

cue-2095
02:08:33.200 --> 02:08:37.180
-'I came to talk to you about myself,'
-he replied.

cue-2096
02:08:37.180 --> 02:08:39.480
'You white men are my friends.

cue-2097
02:08:40.400 --> 02:08:44.420
I want you to tell me honestly, do I have
sleeping sickness?

cue-2098
02:08:45.090 --> 02:08:49.120
I've heard people talking. I think
Christians shouldn't hide things. I'd

cue-2099
02:08:49.120 --> 02:08:54.080
rather know so I can prepare myself. I
feel pain in my legs, and I don't sleep

cue-2100
02:08:54.080 --> 02:08:57.540
well at night. I only half doze and dream.

cue-2101
02:08:58.780 --> 02:08:59.370
Last night,

cue-2102
02:09:00.360 --> 02:09:05.320
I had a dream, not something I heard or
read, but I thought we're like trees in

cue-2103
02:09:05.320 --> 02:09:05.890
the forest.

cue-2104
02:09:06.570 --> 02:09:09.950
They grow up toward heaven. They may get
trimmed,

cue-2105
02:09:10.680 --> 02:09:14.440
but they keep growing until someone cuts
them down to plant something else.

cue-2106
02:09:15.340 --> 02:09:17.920
Then their roots wither, and their
branches are burned.

cue-2107
02:09:18.640 --> 02:09:19.320
We're like that.

cue-2108
02:09:20.060 --> 02:09:21.180
We grow and thrive,

cue-2109
02:09:21.800 --> 02:09:22.700
suffer for a while,

cue-2110
02:09:23.680 --> 02:09:27.920
then go on until God cuts down the ones
who aren't useful to plant others.'

cue-2111
02:09:29.680 --> 02:09:34.540
He kept talking, and I thanked God for
this one precious life transformed by the

cue-2112
02:09:34.540 --> 02:09:38.440
-gospel.
-'I also dreamed of water,'

cue-2113
02:09:38.440 --> 02:09:42.160
-he continued.
-'It flowed gently, sometimes loudly over

cue-2114
02:09:42.160 --> 02:09:44.740
rocks, saying, 'I cannot stay.

cue-2115
02:09:45.380 --> 02:09:46.260
I must go on.'

cue-2116
02:09:47.340 --> 02:09:50.620
But as it passed, someone could drink and
be refreshed.

cue-2117
02:09:51.420 --> 02:09:53.680
I think I'm like that, passing quickly.

cue-2118
02:09:54.320 --> 02:09:59.320
Maybe God used me like the water to bless
someone. I'm not afraid to go into

cue-2119
02:09:59.320 --> 02:10:01.210
glory. But if I die,

cue-2120
02:10:02.140 --> 02:10:03.800
what will happen to my roots,

cue-2121
02:10:04.480 --> 02:10:05.820
my wife, and children?'

cue-2122
02:10:06.820 --> 02:10:07.580
He became quiet,

cue-2123
02:10:08.220 --> 02:10:09.780
and I sensed he had more to say.

cue-2124
02:10:10.880 --> 02:10:14.720
'Now, when I go to school, the children
laugh at me because I'm slow.

cue-2125
02:10:15.420 --> 02:10:18.500
I feel some pride rise in me against the
teacher,

cue-2126
02:10:19.220 --> 02:10:20.460
Sue, who's just a boy.

cue-2127
02:10:21.500 --> 02:10:26.500
But I ask God to forgive me. I try hard,
but sometimes I spend a whole hour on one

cue-2128
02:10:26.500 --> 02:10:26.840
sum.

cue-2129
02:10:27.560 --> 02:10:30.400
They think I don't want to learn, but it's
not true.

cue-2130
02:10:31.100 --> 02:10:35.980
Sometimes the devil tells me not to go
back, but I pray for strength and go

cue-2131
02:10:35.980 --> 02:10:37.760
because I know it pleases Jesus.

cue-2132
02:10:38.480 --> 02:10:38.870
Still,

cue-2133
02:10:39.600 --> 02:10:40.320
I feel weaker.'

cue-2134
02:10:41.260 --> 02:10:46.160
Poor Matula. The fear of sleeping sickness
seemed to haunt him, which was itself a

cue-2135
02:10:46.160 --> 02:10:46.540
sign.

cue-2136
02:10:47.600 --> 02:10:51.900
I told him we couldn't be certain yet, but
reminded him how God had cared for him

cue-2137
02:10:51.900 --> 02:10:56.600
before. Just as his enemies couldn't kill
him, neither could this disease if it

cue-2138
02:10:56.600 --> 02:10:57.620
wasn't God's will.

cue-2139
02:10:58.360 --> 02:11:00.040
We would pray earnestly for him.

cue-2140
02:11:00.680 --> 02:11:05.460
I reminded him that God blesses the one
who delights to do his will, like a tree

cue-2141
02:11:05.460 --> 02:11:07.100
planted by streams of water.

cue-2142
02:11:07.900 --> 02:11:11.520
Our bodies, though, are like grass or
trees that are cut down.

cue-2143
02:11:12.640 --> 02:11:14.340
-'Is that in the Bible?'
-he asked.

cue-2144
02:11:14.960 --> 02:11:18.030
I turned to 1 Peter and read the last
verses of chapter 1.

cue-2145
02:11:18.660 --> 02:11:23.560
He asked to see it, so I read from verse
13 to the end. He was delighted

cue-2146
02:11:23.560 --> 02:11:27.920
by the truth that we were bought not with
perishable things, but with the precious

cue-2147
02:11:27.920 --> 02:11:29.000
blood of Christ.

cue-2148
02:11:29.720 --> 02:11:32.060
I had to read the whole chapter to satisfy
him.

cue-2149
02:11:32.720 --> 02:11:36.200
It was a revelation to him that his
sufferings had been a test of faith

cue-2150
02:11:36.200 --> 02:11:41.100
allowed by God. He had thought it was only
the devil's doing. His face lit

cue-2151
02:11:41.100 --> 02:11:44.640
up with joy as he realized God had been
guiding him through it all.

cue-2152
02:11:45.380 --> 02:11:49.240
Like Job, he had suffered much, but the
devil could not take his life.

cue-2153
02:11:49.960 --> 02:11:54.960
Matula now saw all his trials as small
things in light of what he now knew of

cue-2154
02:11:54.960 --> 02:11:57.360
God's love, power, and goodness.

cue-2155
02:11:58.560 --> 02:11:59.800
It was a joyful morning.

cue-2156
02:12:00.450 --> 02:12:04.280
The gloom he brought with him disappeared,
and he left beaming with peace.

cue-2157
02:12:05.060 --> 02:12:09.720
He returned to live quietly in his home,
near his wife's, burdened by what we

cue-2158
02:12:09.720 --> 02:12:12.620
feared was an incurable and contagious
illness.

cue-2159
02:12:13.240 --> 02:12:16.680
He was extremely careful not to infect his
wife or children.

cue-2160
02:12:17.540 --> 02:12:22.300
At communion, it was touching to see him
use his own glass for wine and ask his

cue-2161
02:12:22.300 --> 02:12:27.260
neighbor to place a piece of bread before
him, afraid even to touch the plate and

cue-2162
02:12:27.260 --> 02:12:28.520
risk contaminating it.

cue-2163
02:12:29.560 --> 02:12:31.380
Simple, sincere-hearted Matula.

cue-2164
02:12:32.010 --> 02:12:33.600
There are sadly too few like him.

cue-2165
02:12:37.340 --> 02:12:39.640
Chapter 17. Matula's Last Days.

cue-2166
02:12:42.240 --> 02:12:46.160
After the earlier chapters were written, I
was overjoyed to read that a medical

cue-2167
02:12:46.160 --> 02:12:49.940
commission had been sent to Uganda to
investigate the cause of the dreadful

cue-2168
02:12:49.940 --> 02:12:50.700
sleep sickness.

cue-2169
02:12:51.540 --> 02:12:56.260
May God grant success to their work so
that thousands of lives may be saved and

cue-2170
02:12:56.260 --> 02:12:58.080
brighter days come to Central Africa.

cue-2171
02:12:59.000 --> 02:13:03.620
To our deep sorrow, Matula became one of
the victims of this terrible disease.

cue-2172
02:13:04.500 --> 02:13:08.960
Sleep sickness affects people differently.
In those who are naturally slow and

cue-2173
02:13:08.960 --> 02:13:13.440
quiet, it dulls every sense like a strong
sedative, leaving them

cue-2174
02:13:13.440 --> 02:13:15.020
dazed and half-conscious.

cue-2175
02:13:15.940 --> 02:13:20.640
In the active and lively, it fights hard
to take over, like a strong man trying to

cue-2176
02:13:20.640 --> 02:13:23.540
overpower another. They resist and fight,

cue-2177
02:13:24.140 --> 02:13:29.000
but gradually, as the mind weakens, their
efforts become wild and irrational.

cue-2178
02:13:29.920 --> 02:13:34.920
Fits of temper, bursts of madness, and
unreasonable behavior in otherwise gentle

cue-2179
02:13:34.920 --> 02:13:39.660
people are almost always early signs of
the disease, showing the mind's attempt to

cue-2180
02:13:39.660 --> 02:13:40.140
resist.

cue-2181
02:13:41.140 --> 02:13:45.950
These strong-willed patients usually take
longer to be overcome, especially if they

cue-2182
02:13:45.950 --> 02:13:48.000
are well cared for in the early stages.

cue-2183
02:13:48.740 --> 02:13:53.500
The illness can seem to lie hidden for a
time, then suddenly show itself through a

cue-2184
02:13:53.500 --> 02:13:58.076
storm of emotion or madness.This was how
it happened with Matula.

cue-2185
02:13:58.956 --> 02:14:02.696
For many months, we suspected he had the
disease, though it remained hidden.

cue-2186
02:14:03.376 --> 02:14:08.356
His faithful wife, Kento, cared for him
with love and gentleness. But many of his

cue-2187
02:14:08.356 --> 02:14:13.156
dear friends and family died, and others
longed to return to their home at Mongo,

cue-2188
02:14:13.156 --> 02:14:14.186
now a place of peace.

cue-2189
02:14:14.936 --> 02:14:19.856
They left reluctantly, and Matula was left
with only his wife, a sister, and three

cue-2190
02:14:19.856 --> 02:14:20.556
young children.

cue-2191
02:14:21.396 --> 02:14:25.646
This loneliness, combined with the effects
of the illness on his mind, caused him to

cue-2192
02:14:25.646 --> 02:14:30.476
turn on his wife, accusing her of being
the cause of his pain, and he began to

cue-2193
02:14:30.476 --> 02:14:35.416
beat her. Then he would break down,
weeping, full of guilt and sorrow.

cue-2194
02:14:36.856 --> 02:14:39.676
Eventually, he became too violent to be
kept at home safely.

cue-2195
02:14:40.336 --> 02:14:43.256
Fearing for his wife's safety, we
suggested restraining him.

cue-2196
02:14:43.956 --> 02:14:47.496
But as soon as he heard the word chain, he
ran off without a word.

cue-2197
02:14:48.276 --> 02:14:52.156
Later, we learned he had returned to his
old home, traveling day and night.

cue-2198
02:14:52.776 --> 02:14:55.576
Soon after, his wife and sister followed
to care for him there.

cue-2199
02:14:56.176 --> 02:14:57.936
He lived only about two more months.

cue-2200
02:14:58.576 --> 02:15:01.416
During most of that time, he was not in
his right mind.

cue-2201
02:15:02.036 --> 02:15:06.616
But in moments of clarity, it was clear
his heart still trusted the one in whom he

cue-2202
02:15:06.616 --> 02:15:08.716
had believed for so many years.

cue-2203
02:15:10.216 --> 02:15:13.136
Kento herself shared the account of
Matula's final days.

cue-2204
02:15:13.856 --> 02:15:17.576
News of his illness and episodes of
madness had reached Mongo before he

cue-2205
02:15:17.576 --> 02:15:22.256
arrived. The people expected outbursts of
rage, but at first, Matula

cue-2206
02:15:22.256 --> 02:15:26.696
remained calm. He rejoiced in the daily
gatherings for morning worship and the

cue-2207
02:15:26.696 --> 02:15:30.796
singing of praise to God in the very place
where he had suffered so deeply.

cue-2208
02:15:32.076 --> 02:15:36.136
But when he noticed many staying away from
prayers, he began visiting the nearby

cue-2209
02:15:36.136 --> 02:15:38.576
hamlets to bring them in, and in doing so,

cue-2210
02:15:39.176 --> 02:15:40.916
found himself beating some of them.

cue-2211
02:15:41.676 --> 02:15:45.616
Realizing his danger, he begged his
friends to tie him up before he harmed

cue-2212
02:15:45.616 --> 02:15:50.336
anyone. With heavy hearts, they tied him
loosely, but after he broke free, they had

cue-2213
02:15:50.336 --> 02:15:55.236
no choice but to secure him more firmly,
his neck, hands, and feet bound.

cue-2214
02:15:57.136 --> 02:15:59.716
Why did God allow this to happen to
Matula?

cue-2215
02:16:00.636 --> 02:16:01.716
It is a great mystery,

cue-2216
02:16:02.356 --> 02:16:05.156
one understood only by the light of
Christian suffering.

cue-2217
02:16:06.036 --> 02:16:11.016
In his sane moments, Matula continued to
teach about God's love and the importance

cue-2218
02:16:11.016 --> 02:16:11.576
of worship.

cue-2219
02:16:12.336 --> 02:16:16.496
Once, he told his sister he had seen Jesus
coming for him with a host of angels.

cue-2220
02:16:17.156 --> 02:16:20.756
His body, once so strong, could no longer
endure.

cue-2221
02:16:21.656 --> 02:16:26.536
He grew too weak to stand, and the end
drew near. The cords were loosened, the

cue-2222
02:16:26.536 --> 02:16:31.296
stick removed, and he was laid gently
down, surrounded by those who loved and

cue-2223
02:16:31.296 --> 02:16:32.215
honored him deeply.

cue-2224
02:16:33.496 --> 02:16:36.596
During his final days, he was only
occasionally conscious.

cue-2225
02:16:37.616 --> 02:16:41.156
But in those moments, he would raise his
hand toward heaven and say,

cue-2226
02:16:41.796 --> 02:16:42.156
Tala,

cue-2227
02:16:43.236 --> 02:16:43.496
look.

cue-2228
02:16:44.576 --> 02:16:48.276
His eyes would shine, and he seemed to
listen to something beyond the reach of

cue-2229
02:16:48.276 --> 02:16:48.576
others.

cue-2230
02:16:49.216 --> 02:16:52.176
Surely he saw the king in his glory,
calling him home.

cue-2231
02:16:53.096 --> 02:16:56.876
On his last morning, a bright and
beautiful day broke over the earth,

cue-2232
02:16:57.536 --> 02:17:01.356
and for Matula, it marked the beginning of
the eternal day of peace.

cue-2233
02:17:02.356 --> 02:17:06.176
Though his end was a mystery, his life
remained a powerful testimony.

cue-2234
02:17:06.936 --> 02:17:11.336
Even as these words were written, an
elderly woman, about sixty, told a

cue-2235
02:17:11.336 --> 02:17:15.116
messenger that it was Matula who had
taught her to trust in the loving Savior.

cue-2236
02:17:16.016 --> 02:17:18.716
She had once found joy in spiritual
things,

cue-2237
02:17:19.356 --> 02:17:21.536
but after losing her only daughter, she
withdrew,

cue-2238
02:17:22.136 --> 02:17:23.836
convinced God did not love her.

cue-2239
02:17:24.956 --> 02:17:29.476
One day, Matula found her weeping and
shared with her the story of the widow of

cue-2240
02:17:29.476 --> 02:17:34.376
Nayan in his own vivid way. He described
how the grieving mother had cared for her

cue-2241
02:17:34.376 --> 02:17:38.916
only son, watching over him with deep love
until the day he

cue-2242
02:17:38.916 --> 02:17:39.416
died.

cue-2243
02:17:40.336 --> 02:17:44.776
In her sorrow, she cried out, beat her
head on the ground, and cut herself in

cue-2244
02:17:44.776 --> 02:17:45.096
grief.

cue-2245
02:17:45.836 --> 02:17:50.496
But then, a man full of majesty and
gentleness appeared. He told her not to

cue-2246
02:17:50.496 --> 02:17:52.296
weep. Her son was only sleeping.

cue-2247
02:17:52.936 --> 02:17:55.936
He touched the casket, and at once her son
lived again.

cue-2248
02:17:56.716 --> 02:18:00.056
Overwhelmed with joy, she received her boy
back from the grave.

cue-2249
02:18:00.796 --> 02:18:05.776
This story, so tenderly and powerfully
told by Matula, brought comfort

cue-2250
02:18:05.776 --> 02:18:07.436
and faith to that grieving woman.

cue-2251
02:18:08.316 --> 02:18:12.796
It was one of many ways he continued to
bless others, even in his final days.

cue-2252
02:18:13.896 --> 02:18:15.196
-Then,
-said Matula,

cue-2253
02:18:15.916 --> 02:18:20.676
I cannot say your child will return, but
Jesus remains as loving and

cue-2254
02:18:20.676 --> 02:18:25.316
kind as ever. He has taken your child and
is keeping her safe for you.

cue-2255
02:18:26.016 --> 02:18:26.576
Don't cry.

cue-2256
02:18:27.296 --> 02:18:29.736
Trust him, and you will see your daughter
again.

cue-2257
02:18:30.816 --> 02:18:31.296
Since then,

cue-2258
02:18:32.216 --> 02:18:33.316
said the elderly convert,

cue-2259
02:18:34.056 --> 02:18:35.436
my tears have ceased.

cue-2260
02:18:36.396 --> 02:18:38.756
I've trusted the Savior and never doubted
his love.

cue-2261
02:18:40.236 --> 02:18:44.856
Just a few weeks ago, Mr. Frame had the
joy of baptizing her in her own village.

cue-2262
02:18:45.656 --> 02:18:49.856
As the sleep sickness began to turn into
madness, Matula spoke at a church meeting,

cue-2263
02:18:49.856 --> 02:18:51.656
sensing his time was short.

cue-2264
02:18:52.296 --> 02:18:56.616
He urged the believers to care for the
sick and suffering, especially those

cue-2265
02:18:56.616 --> 02:19:00.876
afflicted with sleep sickness, who were
like those already under sentence of

cue-2266
02:19:00.876 --> 02:19:05.696
death. He encouraged them to serve these
people with compassion, knowing that in

cue-2267
02:19:05.696 --> 02:19:09.136
doing so, they were serving Christ, who
would reward them.

cue-2268
02:19:10.076 --> 02:19:13.576
But if they showed no mercy, how could
they expect mercy themselves?

cue-2269
02:19:14.476 --> 02:19:15.356
-Hell,
-he said,

cue-2270
02:19:16.156 --> 02:19:20.436
is not a place made just for bad people,
but a place people prepare for

cue-2271
02:19:20.436 --> 02:19:22.136
themselves by their actions.

cue-2272
02:19:22.856 --> 02:19:26.756
With their evil deeds, they carry their
own firewood to fuel their torment.

cue-2273
02:19:27.656 --> 02:19:32.256
This vivid image, likely heard from a
missionary, had taken root in his heart

cue-2274
02:19:32.256 --> 02:19:33.156
and stayed with him.

cue-2275
02:19:34.356 --> 02:19:36.916
You were a kind and Christ-like soul,
Matula.

cue-2276
02:19:37.776 --> 02:19:39.516
On this earth, we shall not see you again,

cue-2277
02:19:40.196 --> 02:19:43.956
but we will meet once more when the dawn
breaks and the shadows vanish.

cue-2278
02:19:44.856 --> 02:19:47.036
Matula has entered heaven's eternal light.

cue-2279
02:19:47.776 --> 02:19:52.316
Surely the angels have already rejoiced
over this precious soul, drawn out of the

cue-2280
02:19:52.316 --> 02:19:53.846
darkness of Congo's soil.

cue-2281
02:19:54.556 --> 02:19:59.356
For all the love, labor, sacrifice, and
tears poured into the work in

cue-2282
02:19:59.356 --> 02:20:03.916
Congo, this one life redeemed by Christ's
blood is a worthy return.

cue-2283
02:20:04.756 --> 02:20:09.336
And yet Matula was not alone. A noble one,
yes, but just one among many.

cue-2284
02:20:10.476 --> 02:20:14.316
We thank God for the growing multitude
from Congo joining the ranks of the

cue-2285
02:20:14.316 --> 02:20:19.296
redeemed, lifting their voices in the
great anthem. To him who loved us, to

cue-2286
02:20:19.296 --> 02:20:24.216
him who conquered, to him who holds power
over death and darkness, glory

cue-2287
02:20:24.216 --> 02:20:25.196
forever. Amen.

cue-2288
02:20:28.556 --> 02:20:31.916
You have finished listening to A Miracle
of Modern Missions.

cue-2289
02:20:32.896 --> 02:20:35.316
The story of Matula, a Congo convert.

cue-2290
02:20:37.166 --> 02:20:39.596
Audiobook produced by scrollreader.com.

cue-2291
02:20:40.276 --> 02:20:44.196
Listen to our audiobooks for free on our
site, YouTube, or Spotify.
